('Bosu Ball Single Leg Hip Thrust',2,'Drive hips upward, squeezing glutes, one leg extended.'),
('Bosu Ball Single Leg Hip Thrust',3,'Lower hips back down and switch legs.'),
('Bosu Ball Situp',1,'Lie on back, bosu elevated toward the ceiling.'),
('Bosu Ball Situp',2,'Sit up, engaging core muscles.'),
('Bosu Ball Situp',3,'Lower back down to complete one situp.'),
('Bosu Ball Split Squat',1,'Stand in front of Bosu, one foot on the center.'),
('Bosu Ball Split Squat',2,'Lower into a lunge position, knee at 90 degrees.'),
('Bosu Ball Split Squat',3,'Push off the front foot to return to starting position.'),
('Bosu Ball Squat',1,'Stand on Bosu, feet shoulder-width apart.'),
('Bosu Ball Squat',2,'Squat down, keeping knees aligned with toes.'),
('Bosu Ball Squat',3,'Push through heels to stand back up.'),
('Bosu Ball Superman',1,'Lie face down on Bosu, arms extended.'),
('Bosu Ball Superman',2,'Lift arms, chest, and legs off the Bosu.'),
('Bosu Ball Superman',3,'Hold for a moment, then lower back down.'),
('Bosu Ball Toe Tap',1,'Stand on Bosu, lift one foot, tap it on the Bosu.'),
('Bosu Ball Toe Tap',2,'Alternate tapping feet while maintaining balance.'),
('Bosu Ball Toe Tap',3,'Keep the movement controlled and steady.'),
('Bosu Ball Up And Over',1,'Stand next to Bosu, step up and over it.'),
('Bosu Ball Up And Over',2,'Repeat, moving laterally side to side.'),
('Bosu Ball Up And Over',3,'Keep a steady pace, engaging core muscles.'),
('Bosu Ball Walkover Pushup',1,'Place both hands on Bosu, wider than shoulder-width.'),
('Bosu Ball Walkover Pushup',2,'Perform a pushup, then walk hands to the other side.'),
('Bosu Ball Walkover Pushup',3,'Perform another pushup, repeat back and forth.'),
('Bosu Ball Wood Chopper',1,'Stand tall holding the bosu.'),
('Bosu Ball Wood Chopper',2,'Swing bosu diagonally across the body.'),
('Bosu Serratus Activation Active Plank',1,'Support your weight on your forearms and toes (plank).'),
('Bosu Serratus Activation Active Plank',2,'Allow your upper back to sink in between the shoulder blades.'),
('Bosu Serratus Activation Active Plank',3,'Push your elbows into the ground and slightly forward, and move the shoulder blades away from the spine.'),
('Bosu Serratus Activation Plank',1,'Support your weight with your forearms on the bosu and toes on the floor (plank).'),
('Bosu Serratus Activation Plank',2,'Allow your upper back to sink in between the shoulder blades.'),
('Bosu Serratus Activation Plank',3,'Push your elbows into the ground and slightly forward, and move the shoulder blades away from the spine.'),
('Bow Pose',1,'Lie on your stomach with your arms at your sides.'),
('Bow Pose',2,'Bend your knees and bring your heels towards your buttocks.'),
('Bow Pose',3,'Reach back with your hands and grab your ankles.'),
('Bow Pose',4,'Inhale and lift your chest off the ground, pulling your legs up and back with your hands.'),
('Bow Pose',5,'Keep your gaze forward and hold the pose for a few breaths before releasing back to the ground.'),
('Box Dips',1,'Hold your body with arms locked above the equipment'),
('Box Dips',2,'Lower your body slowly while leaning forward, flare out your elbows'),
('Box Dips',3,'Raise your body above the bars until your arms are locked.'),
('Box Jump',1,'Stand in front of a box.'),
('Box Jump',2,'*Start with a low box if this is your first time*'),
('Box Jump',3,'Sink into a quarter of half squat and then pop your hips forward.'),
('Box Jump',4,'Try to land in the middle of the box as softly as possible to minimise impact on your joints.'),
('Bulgarian Split Squat',1,'Stand with your back to a bench (or raised surface) and place one of your feet on the bench.'),
('Bulgarian Split Squat',2,'Squat down until your front leg is about parallel to the floor.'),
('Bulgarian Split Squat',3,'Go back to the starting position. After completing the desired amount of reps, switch legs and repeat.'),
('Burpee',1,'Start standing with your feet hip-width apart. Lower your body into a squat position, placing your hands on the ground in front of you.'),
('Burpee',2,'Quickly jump your feet back into a plank position, keeping your body in a straight line from your head to your toes.'),
('Burpee',3,'Perform a push-up, keeping your core tight and your elbows close to your body.'),
('Burpee',4,'Jump your feet back towards your hands, and then jump up into the air, reaching your arms overhead.'),
('Burpee',5,'Land softly and immediately lower your body back into the squat position to repeat the movement.'),
('Butt Kick',1,'Stand tall, jog in place, bringing heels toward your glutes.'),
('Butt Kick',2,'Keep your core tight and swing arms naturally.'),
('Butt Kick',3,'Alternate legs quickly, maintaining a steady rhythm.'),
('Cable 30 Degree Shrug',1,'Use a handle attachment on both sides of crossover. With cable attachment set all the way to the bottom.'),
('Cable 30 Degree Shrug',2,'Grab both handles and make sure you are centered in the machine. Let your arms hang freely.'),
('Cable 30 Degree Shrug',3,'Pull your shoulder blades up and in towards your ears. Let your shoulder blades depress back to the starting position.'),
('Cable Alternating Bench Chest Fly',1,'Lie on bench, hold cable handles above chest, palms facing inward.'),
('Cable Alternating Bench Chest Fly',2,'Lower one arm outward with slight elbow bend, keeping opposite arm extended.'),
('Cable Alternating Bench Chest Fly',3,'Bring arm back to center, alternate sides while maintaining controlled movement.'),
('Cable Alternating Bench Press',1,'Lie on bench, hold handles beside chest, elbows bent.'),
('Cable Alternating Bench Press',2,'Press one handle upward until arm extends, opposite arm remains stationary.'),
('Cable Alternating Bench Press',3,'Lower slowly, alternate arms while keeping shoulders stable.'),
('Cable Alternating Decline Bench Chest Fly',1,'Lay on bench with cables above shoulder level.'),
('Cable Alternating Decline Bench Chest Fly',2,'Start with both arms extended out.'),
('Cable Alternating Decline Bench Chest Fly',3,'Bring one arm forward and downward, while keeping the other arm in the same position.'),
('Cable Alternating Decline Bench Chest Fly',4,'Alternate arms until you complete the allotted amount of reps.'),
('Cable Archer Row',1,'Place the cable at shoulder height.'),
('Cable Archer Row',2,'On the same side as the working arm, step back and rotate outwards.'),
('Cable Archer Row',3,'Pull your elbow back while flaring your elbow out.'),
('Cable Bar Calve Raise',1,'Use a straight bar or ez bar attachment with the cable set all the way to the bottom.'),
('Cable Bar Calve Raise',2,'Walk a few steps back.'),
('Cable Bar Calve Raise',3,'Pull your heels straight up until you feel a contraction in your calves and then back to original position.'),
('Cable Bar Curl',1,'Use a bar attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Bar Curl',2,'Face the cable machine.'),
('Cable Bar Curl',3,'Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support. Face your palm forward. Flex at the elbow and extend.'),
('Cable Bar Face Pull',1,'Facing the pulley, pull the weight towards you while keeping your arms parallel to the ground.'),
('Cable Bar Face Pull',2,'Pull your hands back to both sides of your head and hold the position.'),
('Cable Bar Face Pull',3,'Slowly return weight to starting position. Repeat.'),
('Cable Bar Kneeling Crunch',1,'Use a bar attachment and set the cable all the way to the top.'),
('Cable Bar Kneeling Crunch',2,'Walk a few steps forward and fall to a kneeling position.'),
('Cable Bar Kneeling Crunch',3,'Push your hips back and flex your abs, then push hips forward until in the starting position.'),
('Cable Bar Reverse Grip Curl',1,'Use a bar attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Bar Reverse Grip Curl',2,'Face the cable machine.'),
('Cable Bar Reverse Grip Curl',3,'Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support. Face your palm down. Flex at the elbow and extend.'),
('Cable Bar Rolling Pushdown',1,'Stand facing cable holding bar with palms down, elbows bent, and shoulders flexed.'),
('Cable Bar Rolling Pushdown',2,'First extend your shoulders (like performing a pullover), then extend the elbows.'),
('Cable Bar Romanian Deadlift',1,'Start with a straight bar or ez bar attachment set to the bottom of the machine. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back'),
('Cable Bar Romanian Deadlift',2,'Push your butt back to initiate the movement and then push your butt forward until you\'re back in a standing position.'),
('Cable Bar Romanian Deadlift',3,'To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back on any exercise.'),
('Cable Bar Skullcrusher',1,'Use a bar attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the top of the machine.'),
('Cable Bar Skullcrusher',2,'Face away from the machine with your elbows up and the attachment just behind your head.'),
('Cable Bar Skullcrusher',3,'Extend at the elbows until you feel a contraction in your triceps and then flex at the elbow back to the starting position.'),
('Cable Bar Staggered Romanian Deadlift',1,'Start with a straight bar attachment set to the bottom of the machine. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back.'),
('Cable Bar Staggered Romanian Deadlift',2,'Stand with a staggered stance. Push your butt back to initiate the movement and then push your butt forward until you\'re back in a standing position.'),
('Cable Bar Staggered Romanian Deadlift',3,'To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back on any exercise.'),
('Cable Bar Standing Crunch',1,'Use a bar attachment and set the cable all the way to the top.'),
('Cable Bar Standing Crunch',2,'Face away from the cable tower and walk a few steps forward.'),
('Cable Bar Standing Crunch',3,'Push your hips back, and flex your abs.'),
('Cable Bar Standing Crunch',4,'Return to the starting standing position and repeat.'),
('Cable Bayesian Curl',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Bayesian Curl',2,'Face away from the cable machine.'),
('Cable Bayesian Curl',3,'Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support. Face your palm forward. Flex at the elbow and extend.'),
('Cable Behind The Back Lateral Raise',1,'Place the cable all the way at the bottom and stand with the cable crossing behind your body.'),
('Cable Behind The Back Lateral Raise',2,'While keeping your elbow mostly extended, lift your arm until it\'s parallel with the floor.'),
('Cable Belt Calf Raise',1,'Put on a dip belt and attach the cable carabiner to the chain/strap.'),
('Cable Belt Calf Raise',2,'Take a few steps back and stand tall. Raise up onto the balls of your feet and hold for a 1 count.'),
('Cable Belt Split Squat',1,'Put on a dip belt and attach the strap/ chain to the cable\'s carabiner.'),
('Cable Belt Split Squat',2,'Take a few steps back and take a split stance.'),
('Cable Belt Split Squat',3,'Lower into a split squat, letting the weight pull you forward. As you squat back to the starting position push yourself backwards against the resistance.'),
('Cable Belt Squat',1,'Put on a dip belt. Attach the strap/chain to the cable\'s carabiner.'),
('Cable Belt Squat',2,'Take a few steps back. Begin to squat by flexing at the knees and hips.'),
('Cable Belt Squat',3,'Let the weight pull you forward as you squat. Then push your toes through the front of your shoes as you squat back to the start position.'),
('Cable Bench Straight Leg Kickback',1,'Use an ankle attachment. Bring a bench over to the cables. The cable should be set to hip height.'),
('Cable Bench Straight Leg Kickback',2,'Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.'),
('Cable Bench Straight Leg Kickback',3,'Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.'),
('Cable Bent Over Bar Pullover',1,'You can use any attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the top of the machine.'),
('Cable Bent Over Bar Pullover',2,'Grab your attachment and walk a few steps back. Push your butt back to where you are leaning forward somewhat.'),
('Cable Bent Over Bar Pullover',3,'Initiate the movement with your shoulders and not your elbows. Imagine trying to pull the attachment through your thighs at the bottom.'),
('Cable Bent Over Single Arm Overhead Tricep Extension',1,'Face away from cable, hinge at hips, and grasp handle behind head.'),
('Cable Bent Over Single Arm Overhead Tricep Extension',2,'Keep upper arm still and extend elbow until arm is straight.'),
('Cable Bent Over Single Arm Overhead Tricep Extension',3,'Squeeze tricep at the top, then slowly return to starting position.'),
('Cable Braced Single Arm Chest Fly',1,'Stand sideways to cable, hinge forward, and hold handle at shoulder height.'),
('Cable Braced Single Arm Chest Fly',2,'Brace free hand against support, then bring working arm across chest in an arc.'),
('Cable Braced Single Arm Chest Fly',3,'Squeeze chest at the end, then slowly return to starting position.'),
('Cable Braced Single Arm Chest Press',1,'Stand sideways to cable, hinge forward, and grab something for stability.'),
('Cable Braced Single Arm Chest Press',2,'Press across the body going just short of extending your elbow.'),
('Cable Braced Single Arm Internally Rotated Chest Fly',1,'Stand sideways to cable, hinge forward, and hold handle at shoulder height with an internally rotated shoulder.'),
('Cable Braced Single Arm Internally Rotated Chest Fly',2,'Brace free hand against support, then bring working arm across chest in an arc.'),
('Cable Braced Single Arm Internally Rotated Chest Fly',3,'Squeeze chest at the end, then slowly return to starting position.'),
('Cable Braced Wrist Curl',1,'Stand facing cable, brace forearm on support with palm up holding handle.'),
('Cable Braced Wrist Curl',2,'Lower wrist slowly to feel stretch in forearm flexors.'),
('Cable Braced Wrist Curl',3,'Curl wrist upward, squeezing forearm at the top.'),
('Cable Braced Wrist Extension',1,'Stand facing cable, brace forearm on support with palm down holding handle.'),
('Cable Braced Wrist Extension',2,'Lower wrist slowly to feel stretch in top of forearm.'),
('Cable Braced Wrist Extension',3,'Extend wrist upward, contracting forearm extensors fully.'),
('Cable Calve Raise',1,'Use a straight bar or ez bar attachment with the cable set all the way to the bottom.'),
('Cable Calve Raise',2,'Walk a few steps back.'),
('Cable Calve Raise',3,'Pull your heels straight up until you feel a contraction in your calves and then back to original position.'),
('Cable Chest Press',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cables should be set to shoulder height.'),
('Cable Chest Press',2,'Bring both of the handles to your chest and make sure you are in the center of the cable crossover.'),
('Cable Chest Press',3,'Walk a few steps forward. Then press the weight forward.'),
('Cable Chest Press',4,'From there, you should flex and extend at both the shoulders and elbows simultaneously.'),
('Cable Cross Pushdown',1,'Either use two handles or no attachment at all. Both sides of the cable crossover should be set to the top.'),
('Cable Cross Pushdown',2,'Stand in the center of the machine holding each Cable in the opposing hand. Your upper arm should be at a 45 degree angle with your torso.'),
('Cable Cross Pushdown',3,'Extend your elbows until you feel a contraction and then return to the starting position'),
('Cable Decline Bench Chest Fly',1,'Bring a bench over to the cables, set the cables above shoulder height.'),
('Cable Decline Bench Chest Fly',2,'Bring both of the handles to your chest and make sure you are in the center of the cable crossover.'),
('Cable Decline Bench Chest Fly',3,'Press the weight forward. From there, your shoulders should horizontally abduct and adduct while your elbows stay in a fixed position.'),
('Cable Decline Bench Press',1,'Use a handle attachment. Bring a bench over to the cables. The cables should be set above height.'),
('Cable Decline Bench Press',2,'Bring both of the handles to your chest and make sure you are in the center of the cable crossover.'),
('Cable Decline Bench Press',3,'From there, you should flex and extend at both the shoulders and elbows simultaneously.'),
('Cable Decline Press Around',1,'Set cables slightly above shoulder height and step forward into staggered stance.'),
('Cable Decline Press Around',2,'Press arm forward and downward in an arc, finishing slightly across your torso.'),
('Cable Elevated Deadlift',1,'Start with handles set to the bottom of the machine. Grab a box, stand on top of the box, squat the weight up into a standing position.'),
('Cable Elevated Deadlift',2,'Push your butt back to initiate the movement and then push your butt forward until you\'re back in a standing position.'),
('Cable Elevated Deadlift',3,'To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back on any exercise.'),
