('Cable Half Kneeling High To Low Wood Chopper',2,'Face sideways, then rotate your torso with your arms extended against the resistance.'),
('Cable Half Kneeling High To Low Wood Chopper',3,'After completing your given number of reps, face the opposite direction and repeat.'),
('Cable Half Kneeling Low To High Wood Chopper',1,'Set the cable at a low position. Take a half kneeling position. Use a handle attachment.'),
('Cable Half Kneeling Low To High Wood Chopper',2,'Face sideways, then rotate your torso with your arms extended against the resistance.'),
('Cable Half Kneeling Low To High Wood Chopper',3,'After completing your given number of reps, face the opposite direction and repeat.'),
('Cable Half Kneeling Wood Chopper',1,'Set the cable at nipple level. Take a half kneeling position. Use a handle attachment.'),
('Cable Half Kneeling Wood Chopper',2,'Face sideways, then rotate your torso with your arms extended against the resistance.'),
('Cable Half Kneeling Wood Chopper',3,'After completing your given number of reps, face the opposite direction and repeat.'),
('Cable Hammer Bayesian Curl',1,'Stand facing away from the cables and grab two handle attachments.'),
('Cable Hammer Bayesian Curl',2,'Take a neutral grip, flex your elbows, and extend.'),
('Cable Hamstring Curl',1,'Use an ankle attachment with the cable set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Hamstring Curl',2,'Stand upright or try bending slightly forward.'),
('Cable Hamstring Curl',3,'Flex at the knee and pull your ankle straight back.'),
('Cable High Bayesian Curl',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set to about elbow height.'),
('Cable High Bayesian Curl',2,'Face away from the cable machine.'),
('Cable High Bayesian Curl',3,'Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support. Face your palm forward. Flex at the elbow and extend.'),
('Cable High Internally Rotated Reverse Fly',1,'Use a handle attachment or no attachment at all. The cable should be set to the top.'),
('Cable High Internally Rotated Reverse Fly',2,'Walk a few steps away with the cable coming from the opposing side of the working arms. Internally rotate the shoulders.'),
('Cable High Internally Rotated Reverse Fly',3,'From there, your shoulders should horizontally abduct and adduct, while your elbows stay in a fixed position.'),
('Cable High Reverse Fly',1,'Use a handle attachment or no attachment at all. The cable should be set to the top.'),
('Cable High Reverse Fly',2,'Walk a few steps away with the cable coming from the opposing side of the working arm.'),
('Cable High Reverse Fly',3,'From there, your shoulders should horizontally abduct and adduct, while your elbows stay in a fixed position.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Hammer Bayesian Curl',1,'Stand facing away from high cable, hold handle with palm facing inward.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Hammer Bayesian Curl',2,'Step forward to create tension and let arm extend fully behind you.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Hammer Bayesian Curl',3,'Curl handle toward shoulder, keeping palm neutral, then lower slowly.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Hammer Rolling Curl',1,'Set cable at about elbow level. Stand facing away from the cables and grab handle attachment.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Hammer Rolling Curl',2,'Take a neutral grip, flex your elbows, as you curl hinge forward.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Hammer Rolling Curl',3,'As you extend your elbow, also extend your hips until you are back in a standing position.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Rear Delt Fly',1,'Use a handle attachment or no attachment at all. The cable should be set to the top.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Rear Delt Fly',2,'Walk a few steps away with the cable coming from the opposing side of the working arm.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Rear Delt Fly',3,'From there, your shoulders should horizontally abduct and adduct, while your elbows stay in a fixed position.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Reverse Bayesian Curl',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set at elbow level.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Reverse Bayesian Curl',2,'Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Reverse Bayesian Curl',3,'Face your palm downwards, and curl.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Reverse Rolling Curl',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set at elbow level.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Reverse Rolling Curl',2,'Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Reverse Rolling Curl',3,'Face your palm downwards, as you curl hinge forward.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Reverse Rolling Curl',4,'As you extend your elbow, also extend your hips until you are back in a standing position.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Rolling Curl',1,'Set cable at about elbow level. Stand facing away from the cables and grab handle attachment.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Rolling Curl',2,'Take an underhand grip, flex your elbows, as you curl hinge forward.'),
('Cable High Single Arm Rolling Curl',3,'As you extend your elbow, also extend your hips until you are back in a standing position.'),
('Cable Incline Bench Straight Leg Kickback',1,'Use an ankle attachment. Bring a bench over to the cables. Put the bench at incline level. The cable should be set to shoulder height.'),
('Cable Incline Bench Straight Leg Kickback',2,'Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.'),
('Cable Incline Bench Straight Leg Kickback',3,'Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.'),
('Cable Incline Fly Around',1,'Set cables slightly above shoulder height and step forward into staggered stance.'),
('Cable Incline Fly Around',2,'Fly arm forward and upward in an arc, finishing slightly across your torso.'),
('Cable Incline Press Around',1,'Set cables slightly below shoulder height and step forward into staggered stance.'),
('Cable Incline Press Around',2,'Press arm forward and upward in an arc, finishing slightly across your torso.'),
('Cable Internal Rotation',1,'Stand tall, hold the cable handle with a neutral grip, your elbow should be at a 90 degree angle.'),
('Cable Internal Rotation',2,'Rotate your shoulder by bringing your forearm across your body.'),
('Cable Kayak Row',1,'Use a bar attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the top of the machine.'),
('Cable Kayak Row',2,'Grab your attachment and walk a few steps back. Push your butt back to where you are leaning forward somewhat.'),
('Cable Kayak Row',3,'Initiate the movement with your shoulders and not your elbows. Bring one arm to your side.'),
('Cable Kayak Row',4,'You can either alternate sides or do one side at a time.'),
('Cable Kneeling High To Low Wood Chopper',1,'Kneel sideways to cable and grasp handle with both hands overhead.'),
('Cable Kneeling High To Low Wood Chopper',2,'Rotate torso and pull handle diagonally down toward opposite hip.'),
('Cable Kneeling High To Low Wood Chopper',3,'Control the return, keeping core braced and hips stable.'),
('Cable Kneeling Low To High Wood Chopper',1,'Kneel sideways to cable and grasp handle near hip level with both hands.'),
('Cable Kneeling Low To High Wood Chopper',2,'Rotate torso and pull handle diagonally upward across body toward opposite shoulder.'),
('Cable Kneeling Low To High Wood Chopper',3,'Control the return, keeping core braced and hips stable.'),
('Cable Kneeling Oblique Crunch',1,'Kneel sideways to cable and hold rope behind head, elbows pointed out.'),
('Cable Kneeling Oblique Crunch',2,'Crunch torso toward hip on cable side, keeping hips stable.'),
('Cable Kneeling Oblique Crunch',3,'Slowly return to upright, maintaining constant tension on obliques.'),
('Cable Kneeling Pallof Press',1,'Kneel sideways to cable and hold handle at chest, elbows tucked.'),
('Cable Kneeling Pallof Press',2,'Brace core and press handle straight forward without rotating torso.'),
('Cable Kneeling Pallof Press',3,'Hold briefly, then return handle to chest under full control.'),
('Cable Kneeling Pallof Press To Wood Chopper',1,'Kneel sideways to cable and press handle straight forward, keeping torso stable.'),
('Cable Kneeling Pallof Press To Wood Chopper',2,'Rotate torso and pull handle diagonally across body into a wood chopper motion.'),
('Cable Kneeling Pallof Press To Wood Chopper',3,'Return to center and bring handle back to chest under control.'),
('Cable Kneeling Wood Chopper',1,'Kneel sideways to cable and grip handle with both hands in front of chest.'),
('Cable Kneeling Wood Chopper',2,'Rotate torso and pull handle diagonally across body in a smooth arc.'),
('Cable Kneeling Wood Chopper',3,'Control the return, keeping core braced and hips stable.'),
('Cable Lat Prayer',1,'You can use any attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the top of the machine.'),
('Cable Lat Prayer',2,'Grab your attachment and walk a few steps back. Push your butt back to where you are leaning forward. Your ears should be between your arms.'),
('Cable Lat Prayer',3,'Initiate the movement with your shoulders and not your elbows. As you flex at the shoulder joint push your hips forward until your hips meet the attachment.'),
('Cable Leaning Single Arm Skullover',1,'Stand in front of cable stack facing away to and lean torso slightly forward, holding handle overhead.'),
('Cable Leaning Single Arm Skullover',2,'Break at the elbow until your forearm touch your bicep, then flex at the shoulder joint bringing your upper arm to the side of your head.'),
('Cable Leaning Single Arm Skullover',3,'Bring your elbow back forward, then extend your elbows.'),
('Cable Low Single Arm Lateral Raise',1,'Use a handle attachment with the cable set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Low Single Arm Lateral Raise',2,'You should vertically abduct at the shoulder raising your arm straight out to the side.'),
('Cable Low Single Arm Lateral Raise',3,'Raise until your arm is parallel with the ground and then back to the starting position.'),
('Cable Oblique Pushdown',1,'Set the cable just over your head. Use a handle attachment.'),
('Cable Oblique Pushdown',2,'Face sideways, push the handle down until your elbow is extended. Flex your obliques until you feel a contraction.'),
('Cable Oblique Pushdown',3,'After completing your given number of reps, face the opposite direction and repeat.'),
('Cable Overhead Press',1,'Use a handle attachment with the cable set to the bottom of the machine. Stand upright making sure to maintain a flat back. Your starting position will have your palms facing forward.'),
('Cable Overhead Press',2,'Use both your elbows and shoulders to press the weight directly overhead.'),
('Cable Overhead Tricep Press',1,'You can use any attachment. The cable should be even with your mid-back. Face away from the machine.'),
('Cable Overhead Tricep Press',2,'Point your elbows straight forward. Press the weight straight toward the ceiling.'),
('Cable Overhead Tricep Press',3,'As you return to the start, push your elbows forward. Try to touch your biceps to your forearms at the bottom of each rep.'),
('Cable Pallof Press',1,'Use a handle attachment, set the cable at nipple level, walk a few steps away, and face sideways.'),
('Cable Pallof Press',2,'Start with both hands on the handle and your fists against your chest.'),
('Cable Pallof Press',3,'Press the handle forward until your elbows are fully extended, then pull the handle back to your chest.'),
('Cable Pallof Press Rotation',1,'Use a handle attachment, set the cable at nipple level, walk a few steps away, and face sideways.'),
('Cable Pallof Press Rotation',2,'Start with both hands on the handle and your fists against your chest.'),
('Cable Pallof Press Rotation',3,'Press the handle forward until your elbows are fully extended, then rotate away from the cable stack.'),
('Cable Pallof Press Rotation',4,'Then pull the handle back to your chest.'),
('Cable Pec Fly',1,'Set the cable pin at shoulder height or just above.'),
('Cable Pec Fly',2,'Bring both of the handles to your chest and make sure you are in the center of the cable crossover.'),
('Cable Pec Fly',3,'Walk a few steps forward. Then press the weight forward. From there, your shoulders should horizontally abduct and adduct while your elbows stay in a fixed position.'),
('Cable Pull Around',1,'Place cable pin all the way at the top or nearly at the top of the cable stack.'),
('Cable Pull Around',2,'Face sideways and take a half kneeling position.'),
('Cable Pull Around',3,'Grab the handle and reach across the body, begin the pull.'),
('Cable Pull Around',4,'As you pull, imagine you are trying to put your elbow into your pocket.'),
('Cable Pull In',1,'Use a handle attachment set all the way to the top of the cable crossover machine.'),
('Cable Pull In',2,'Walk a few steps away from the cable machine. Face your body sideways.'),
('Cable Pull In',3,'Face your palm up toward the ceiling. Then pull your elbow in toward your rib cage.'),
('Cable Pull Through',1,'This exercise works best with a rope attachment but can be done with anything. The attachment should be set to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Pull Through',2,'Face away from the cable machine, straddle the cable itself, and grab the attachment. Walk a few steps away.'),
('Cable Pull Through',3,'Break at the hips while maintaining a flat back and mostly extended knees.'),
('Cable Pull Through',4,'Push hips forward until you are back in a standing position.'),
('Cable Reverse Bayesian Curl',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Reverse Bayesian Curl',2,'Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.'),
('Cable Reverse Bayesian Curl',3,'Face your palm downwards. Flex at the elbow and extend.'),
('Cable Rope Face Pulls',1,'Facing the pulley, pull the weight towards you while keeping your arms parallel to the ground.'),
('Cable Rope Face Pulls',2,'Pull your hands back to both sides of your head and hold the position.'),
('Cable Rope Face Pulls',3,'Slowly return weight to starting position. Repeat.'),
('Cable Rope Front Raise',1,'Face away from the cables. Use a rope attachment.'),
('Cable Rope Front Raise',2,'With your elbows extended raise your fists straight up to the ceiling until they are at eye level.'),
('Cable Rope Hammer Curl',1,'Use a rope attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Rope Hammer Curl',2,'Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.'),
('Cable Rope Hammer Curl',3,'Use a neutral grip thumb facing up pinky-facing down). Flex at the elbow and extend.'),
('Cable Rope Kneeling Crunch',1,'Use a rope attachment and set the cable all the way to the top.'),
('Cable Rope Kneeling Crunch',2,'Walk a few steps forward then fall into a kneeling position.'),
('Cable Rope Kneeling Crunch',3,'Push your hips back and flex your abs, then push hips forward until in the starting position.'),
('Cable Rope Kneeling Face Pull',1,'Start with the cables at the top. Use a rope attachment. Fall to a half kneeling position.'),
('Cable Rope Kneeling Face Pull',2,'Pull the metal piece in the middle of the rope to the bridge of your nose.'),
('Cable Rope Kneeling Oblique Crunch',1,'Use a rope attachment and set the cable all the way to the top.'),
('Cable Rope Kneeling Oblique Crunch',2,'Walk a few steps forward then fall into a kneeling position.'),
('Cable Rope Kneeling Oblique Crunch',3,'Push your hips back and flex your abs, then push hips forward until in the starting position.'),
('Cable Rope Lat Prayer',1,'Use a rope attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the top of the machine.'),
('Cable Rope Lat Prayer',2,'Grab your attachment and walk a few steps back. Push your butt back to where you are leaning forward. Your ears should be between your arms.'),
('Cable Rope Lat Prayer',3,'Initiate the movement with your shoulders and not your elbows. As you flex at the shoulder joint push your hips forward until your hips meet the attachment.'),
('Cable Rope Mid Lateral Raise',1,'Place the cable at the same height as your fist when your arms are at your side and stand with the cable crossing your body.'),
('Cable Rope Mid Lateral Raise',2,'While keeping your elbow mostly extended, lift your arm until it\'s parallel with the floor.'),
('Cable Rope Overhead Tricep Extension',1,'You can use any attachment. The cable should be all the way to the bottom of the machine. Face away from the machine.'),
('Cable Rope Overhead Tricep Extension',2,'Point your elbows straight up toward the ceiling.'),
('Cable Rope Overhead Tricep Extension',3,'From there, extend your elbows until your fists are pointed straight toward the ceiling.'),
('Cable Rope Pullover',1,'Use a rope attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the top of the machine.'),
('Cable Rope Pullover',2,'Grab your attachment and walk a few steps back. Push your butt back to where you are leaning forward somewhat.'),
('Cable Rope Pullover',3,'Initiate the movement with your shoulders and not your elbows. Imagine trying to pull the attachment through your thighs at the bottom.'),
('Cable Rope Pushdown',1,'The cable should be set all the way at the top of the machine.'),
('Cable Rope Pushdown',2,'Make sure to keep your upper arm glued at your side. Extend your elbows until you feel your triceps contract.'),
('Cable Rope Rolling Pushdown',1,'Stand facing cable holding rope, elbows bent, and shoulders flexed.'),
('Cable Rope Rolling Pushdown',2,'First extend your shoulders (like performing a pullover), then extend the elbows.'),
('Cable Rope Single Arm Low Lateral Raise',1,'Use a rope attachment with the cable set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Rope Single Arm Low Lateral Raise',2,'You should vertically abduct at the shoulder raising your arms straight out to the side.'),
('Cable Rope Single Arm Low Lateral Raise',3,'Raise until your arms are parallel with the ground and then back to the starting position.'),
('Cable Rope Skullcrusher',1,'Use a rope attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the top of the machine.'),
('Cable Rope Skullcrusher',2,'Face away from the machine with your elbows up and the attachment just behind your head.'),
('Cable Rope Skullcrusher',3,'Extend at the elbows until you feel a contraction in your triceps and then flex at the elbow back to the starting position.'),
('Cable Rope Standing Crunch',1,'Stand facing cable, hold rope behind head with elbows tucked in.'),
('Cable Rope Standing Crunch',2,'Brace core and curl torso downward toward hips without pulling with arms.'),
('Cable Rope Standing Crunch',3,'Return slowly to standing tall, keeping constant tension on abs.'),
('Cable Rope Upright Row',1,'Use a rope attachment with the cable set to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Rope Upright Row',2,'Pull your elbows straight up toward the ceiling until the attachment is just below your chin then extend until your elbows are fully extended.'),
('Cable Row Bar Kneeling Crunch',1,'Use a double handle attachment and set the cable all the way to the top.'),
('Cable Row Bar Kneeling Crunch',2,'Walk a few steps forward then fall into a kneeling position.'),
('Cable Row Bar Kneeling Crunch',3,'Push your hips back and flex your abs, then push hips forward until in the starting position.'),
('Cable Row Bar Standing Row',1,'Place the cable at shoulder height. Use a row bar.'),
('Cable Row Bar Standing Row',2,'Pull the handles back using your arms. Push out your chest.'),
('Cable Row Bar Standing Row',3,'Pull the handles towards your body until your hands are beside your abdomen.'),
('Cable Seated Bar Face Pull',1,'Sit facing cable machine and grasp bar with shoulder-width overhand grip.'),
('Cable Seated Bar Face Pull',2,'Pull bar toward upper face while driving elbows outward and back.'),
('Cable Seated Bar Face Pull',3,'Squeeze rear delts at the end, then return bar slowly with control.'),
('Cable Seated Bayesian Curl',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Seated Bayesian Curl',2,'Sit on a bench facing away from the cable machine.'),
('Cable Seated Bayesian Curl',3,'Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support. Face your palm forward. Flex at the elbow and extend.'),
('Cable Seated Bayesian Reverse Curl',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Seated Bayesian Reverse Curl',2,'Face away from the cable machine and sit on the bench. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.'),
('Cable Seated Bayesian Reverse Curl',3,'Face your palm downwards. Flex at the elbow and extend.'),
('Cable Seated Leg Curl',1,'Bring a bench over to the cable stack, put the cable at head height (when seated). Use an ankle attachment.'),
('Cable Seated Leg Curl',2,'Sit on the bench.'),
('Cable Seated Leg Curl',3,'Flex at the knee and pull your ankle straight back.'),
('Cable Seated Leg Extension',1,'Use an ankle/wrist attachment. Pull the cable under the bench and attach it at your ankle.'),
('Cable Seated Leg Extension',2,'Extend at the knee against the cable.'),
('Cable Seated Rope Face Pull',1,'Sit facing cable and hold rope with palms facing each other, arms extended.'),
('Cable Seated Rope Face Pull',2,'Pull rope toward upper face while flaring elbows outward.'),
('Cable Seated Rope Face Pull',3,'Squeeze rear delts and mid-traps, then slowly return to start.'),
('Cable Seated Single Arm Face Pull',1,'Sit facing cable and hold handle with arm extended at shoulder height.'),
('Cable Seated Single Arm Face Pull',2,'Pull handle toward upper face while driving elbow outward and back.'),
('Cable Seated Single Arm Face Pull',3,'Squeeze rear delt, then return slowly, maintaining control.'),
('Cable Side Bend',1,'Set the cable at the bottom of the stack. Use a handle attachment.'),
('Cable Side Bend',2,'Face sideways, grab the handle, lean away from the cable.'),
('Cable Side Bend',3,'After completing your given number of reps, face the opposite direction and repeat.'),
('Cable Silverback Shrug',1,'Use a bar attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the bottom.'),
('Cable Silverback Shrug',2,'Stand up with the attachment in hand, walk a couple of steps back make sure you are standing upright and not leaning backwards.'),
('Cable Silverback Shrug',3,'Retract your shoulder blades and then protract to return to the starting position.'),
('Cable Single Arm 30 Degree Shrug',1,'Use a handle attachment. With the cable attachment set all the way to the bottom.'),
('Cable Single Arm 30 Degree Shrug',2,'Grab one handle and make sure you are centered in the machine. Let your arm hang freely.'),
('Cable Single Arm 30 Degree Shrug',3,'Pull your shoulder blade up and in towards your ears. Let your shoulder blade depress back to the starting position.'),
('Cable Single Arm Bayesian Curl',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Single Arm Bayesian Curl',2,'Face away from the cable machine.'),
('Cable Single Arm Bayesian Curl',3,'Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support. Face your palm forward. Flex at the elbow and extend.'),
('Cable Single Arm Face Pull',1,'Stand facing cable and hold handle at shoulder height with arm extended.'),
('Cable Single Arm Face Pull',2,'Pull handle toward upper face while driving elbow outward and back.'),
('Cable Single Arm Face Pull',3,'Squeeze rear delt at the end, then return slowly with control.'),
('Cable Single Arm Hammer Curl',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Single Arm Hammer Curl',2,'Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.'),
('Cable Single Arm Hammer Curl',3,'Use a neutral grip thumb facing up pinky-facing down). Flex at the elbow and extend.'),
('Cable Single Arm Internally Rotated High Reverse Fly',1,'Use a handle attachment or no attachment at all. The cable should be set to the top.'),
('Cable Single Arm Internally Rotated High Reverse Fly',2,'Walk a few steps away with the cable coming from the opposing side of the working arms. Internally rotate the shoulders.'),
('Cable Single Arm Internally Rotated High Reverse Fly',3,'From there, your shoulder should horizontally abduct and adduct, while your elbows stay in a fixed position.'),
('Cable Single Arm Lat Prayer',1,'Use handle attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the top of the machine.'),
('Cable Single Arm Lat Prayer',2,'Grab your attachment and walk a few steps back. Push your butt back to where you are leaning forward. Your ear should be even with your arms.'),
('Cable Single Arm Lat Prayer',3,'Initiate the movement with your shoulder and not your elbow. As you flex at the shoulder joint push your hips forward until your hips meet the attachment.'),
