('Cable Single Arm Neutral Grip Row',2,'Pull the handle back using your arms. Push out your chest.'),
('Cable Single Arm Neutral Grip Row',3,'Pull the handle towards your body until your hands are beside your abdomen.'),
('Cable Single Arm Overhead Tricep Extension',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set to your mid-back. Face away from the machine.'),
('Cable Single Arm Overhead Tricep Extension',2,'Point your elbows straight up toward the ceiling.'),
('Cable Single Arm Overhead Tricep Extension',3,'From there, extend your elbows until your fists are pointed straight toward the ceiling.'),
('Cable Single Arm Pushdown',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way at the top of the machine.'),
('Cable Single Arm Pushdown',2,'Make sure to keep your upper arm glued at your side. Extend your elbow until you feel your tricep contract.'),
('Cable Single Arm Rear Delt Row',1,'Use a handle attachment, grab with an overhand grip and take a position with the cable crossing your body.'),
('Cable Single Arm Rear Delt Row',2,'Pull your elbows back while flaring your elbows outward.'),
('Cable Single Arm Reverse Curl',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Single Arm Reverse Curl',2,'Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.'),
('Cable Single Arm Reverse Curl',3,'Face your palm downwards. Flex at the elbow and extend.'),
('Cable Single Arm Rolling Pushdown',1,'Stand facing cable holding handle with palm down, elbow bent, and shoulder flexed.'),
('Cable Single Arm Rolling Pushdown',2,'First extend your shoulder (like performing a pullover), then extend the elbow.'),
('Cable Single Arm Underhand Grip Row',1,'Place the cable at shoulder height. Use a handle attachment. Face your palm upward.'),
('Cable Single Arm Underhand Grip Row',2,'Pull the handle back using your arms. Push out your chest.'),
('Cable Single Arm Underhand Grip Row',3,'Pull the handle towards your body until your hands are beside your abdomen.'),
('Cable Single Leg Deadlift',1,'Start with a straight bar or easy bar attachment. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back.'),
('Cable Single Leg Deadlift',2,'Push your butt back to initiate the movement while lifting one of your legs. Then push your butt forward until you\'re back in a standing position.'),
('Cable Single Leg Deadlift',3,'Compete your given amount of reps, then switch to opposite leg.'),
('Cable Single Leg Deadlift',4,'To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back.'),
('Cable Single Leg Laying Leg Curl',1,'Bring a bench over to the cable stack, put the cable all the way at the bottom. Use an ankle attachment.'),
('Cable Single Leg Laying Leg Curl',2,'Lay on the bench.'),
('Cable Single Leg Laying Leg Curl',3,'Flex at the knee and pull your ankle straight back.'),
('Cable Split Squat',1,'You can use a straight or EZ bar on this exercise. Cable should be set all to the bottom.'),
('Cable Split Squat',2,'Grab the attachment and walk back a few steps. Take a split stance. One leg in front and one behind.'),
('Cable Split Squat',3,'Break at the knees and hips to initiate the split squat. Make sure your back knee touches the floor.'),
('Cable Split Squat',4,'Squat back up into a standing position.'),
('Cable Standing Crunch',1,'Use a double handle attachment and set the cable all the way to the top.'),
('Cable Standing Crunch',2,'Face away from the cable tower and walk a few steps forward.'),
('Cable Standing Crunch',3,'Push your hips back, and flex your abs.'),
('Cable Standing Crunch',4,'Return to the starting standing position and repeat.'),
('Cable Standing Glute Kickback',1,'Use an ankle attachment. The cable should be set to the bottom of the crossover machine.'),
('Cable Standing Glute Kickback',2,'Break at the knee, push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.'),
('Cable Standing Glute Kickback',3,'Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.'),
('Cable Standing High To Low Wood Chopper',1,'Stand sideways to cable and grasp handle with both hands overhead.'),
('Cable Standing High To Low Wood Chopper',2,'Rotate torso and pull handle diagonally down toward opposite hip.'),
('Cable Standing High To Low Wood Chopper',3,'Control the return, keeping core braced and hips stable.'),
('Cable Standing Hip Abduction',1,'Use an ankle attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the bottom.'),
('Cable Standing Hip Abduction',2,'Face sideways with the ankle attachment on your outside leg. Walk a few steps away.'),
('Cable Standing Hip Abduction',3,'Abduct at the hips and raise your leg out to the side.'),
('Cable Standing Hip Abduction',4,'Return to the starting position and stop just short of your foot touching back to the ground (to keep tension on the muscle).'),
('Cable Standing Leg Extension',1,'Stand upright facing away from the cable crossover with the cable set to the height of your hips. Use an ankle/wrist attachment.'),
('Cable Standing Leg Extension',2,'Extend at the knee against the cable.'),
('Cable Standing Low To High Wood Chopper',1,'Stand sideways to cable and grasp handle near hip level with both hands.'),
('Cable Standing Low To High Wood Chopper',2,'Rotate torso and pull handle diagonally upward toward opposite shoulder.'),
('Cable Standing Low To High Wood Chopper',3,'Control the return, keeping core braced and hips stable.'),
('Cable Standing Mid Kickback',1,'Use an ankle attachment. The cable should be set halfway up the crossover machine.'),
('Cable Standing Mid Kickback',2,'Start with a bent knee position. Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.'),
('Cable Standing Mid Kickback',3,'Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.'),
