('Cable Standing Single Arm Chest Fly',2,'Bring arm across chest in a smooth arc without rotating your torso.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Chest Fly',3,'Squeeze chest at end range, then return slowly to starting position.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Chest Press',1,'Stand sideways to cable and hold handle at chest height with elbow bent.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Chest Press',2,'Brace core and press handle straight forward without rotating torso.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Chest Press',3,'Squeeze chest at extension, then return handle slowly to starting position.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Cross Rear Delt Row',1,'Stand sideways to cable and hold handle across your body at opposite side.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Cross Rear Delt Row',2,'Pull handle outward and back, leading with elbow and keeping arm slightly bent.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Cross Rear Delt Row',3,'Squeeze rear delt at the end, then return slowly with control.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Incline Chest Fly',1,'Stand sideways to cable with handle set low, arm slightly bent.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Incline Chest Fly',2,'Bring arm upward and across chest in an arc without rotating torso.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Incline Chest Fly',3,'Squeeze upper chest at the top, then return slowly to starting position.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Incline Chest Press',1,'Stand sideways to cable with handle set low, holding it at chest height.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Incline Chest Press',2,'Press handle upward and forward at a slight diagonal, keeping torso stable.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Incline Chest Press',3,'Squeeze chest at the top, then return slowly to starting position.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Internally Rotated Chest Fly',1,'Stand sideways to cable and hold handle at shoulder height, arm slightly bent.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Internally Rotated Chest Fly',2,'Rotate palm inward and bring arm across chest in a sweeping arc.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Internally Rotated Chest Fly',3,'Squeeze chest at end range, then return slowly while maintaining internal rotation.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Internally Rotated Incline Chest Fly',1,'Stand sideways to cable with handle set low, palm rotated inward before lifting.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Internally Rotated Incline Chest Fly',2,'Bring arm upward and across chest in an arc, keeping elbow slightly bent.'),
('Cable Standing Single Arm Internally Rotated Incline Chest Fly',3,'Squeeze upper chest at the top, then return slowly while maintaining internal rotation.'),
('Cable Standing Straight Leg Glute Kickback',1,'Use an ankle attachment. The cable should be set to the bottom of the crossover machine.'),
('Cable Standing Straight Leg Glute Kickback',2,'Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.'),
('Cable Standing Straight Leg Glute Kickback',3,'Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.'),
('Cable Standing Straight Leg Mid Kickback',1,'Use an ankle attachment. The cable should be set to halfway up the crossover machine.'),
('Cable Standing Straight Leg Mid Kickback',2,'Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.'),
('Cable Standing Straight Leg Mid Kickback',3,'Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.'),
('Cable Straight Arm Pull In',1,'Use a handle attachment set all the way to the top of the cable crossover machine.'),
('Cable Straight Arm Pull In',2,'Walk a few steps away from the cable machine. Face your body sideways.'),
('Cable Straight Arm Pull In',3,'Face your palm forward. Then pull your elbow in toward your rib cage.'),
('Cable Supinating Row',1,'Place the cable at shoulder height.'),
('Cable Supinating Row',2,'Start with an overhand grip. As you pull your elbow back, rotate your palm until it faces upward.'),
('Cable Twisting Curl',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Twisting Curl',2,'Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.'),
('Cable Twisting Curl',3,'Start with a neutral grip. Flex at the elbow. While flexing twist your palm. When you hit the top of the movement your palm should be facing upward.'),
('Cable Upright Row',1,'Use a handle attachment with the cable set to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Upright Row',2,'Pull your elbows straight up toward the ceiling until the attachment is just below your chin then extend until your elbows are fully extended.'),
('Cable Wood Chopper',1,'Set the cable at about nipple level. Use a handle attachment.'),
('Cable Wood Chopper',2,'Face sideways, then rotate your torso with your arms extended against the resistance.'),
('Cable Wood Chopper',3,'After completing your given number of reps, face the opposite direction and repeat.'),
('Cable Wrist Curl',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Wrist Curl',2,'Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.'),
('Cable Wrist Curl',3,'Start with your elbow at a 90° angle with your palm facing up. Flex and extend at the wrist.'),
('Cable Wrist Extension',1,'Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.'),
('Cable Wrist Extension',2,'Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.'),
('Cable Wrist Extension',3,'Start with your elbow at a 90 degree angle with your palm facing down. Flex and extend at the wrist.'),
('Cable Zercher Good Morning',1,'Begin by standing with your feet about hip-width apart and holding the bar in the crook of your elbows, with your palms facing towards your body.'),
('Cable Zercher Good Morning',2,'Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and lower your torso forward until it is nearly parallel to the ground.'),
('Cable Zercher Good Morning',3,'Push through your heels to extend your hips and raise your body back to the starting position.'),
('Cable Zercher Squat',1,'Start with a straight bar or easy bar attachment .'),
('Cable Zercher Squat',2,'Place the bar in your elbows, squat straight up and then walk back a few steps.'),
('Cable Zercher Squat',3,'Break at your knees and hips to initiate the squat. Make sure you maintain a flat back.'),
('Cable Zercher Squat',4,'Squat all the way back to a standing position.'),
('Calf Raises',1,'Balance on the balls of your feet on the platform or plates, leaning forward to use the wall to assist with balance.'),
('Calf Raises',2,'Lower the heels of your feet towards the ground and pause, then push through the balls of your feet like you are standing tip toe, pausing at the apex of the motion.'),
('Calf Raises',3,'Repeat as necessary.'),
('Calves Stretch Variation One',1,'Place the ball of your foot against the wall with your heel on the ground. Place your hands on the wall in front of your shoulders.'),
('Calves Stretch Variation One',2,'Keeping your knee straight, slowly lean towards the wall, pause for a few seconds when you feel the stretch extending through your calf muscle.'),
('Calves Stretch Variation One',3,'Return to the starting position, and repeat the stretch with your other leg.'),
('Calves Stretch Variation Three',1,'Balance the balls of your feet on the platform, leaning forward to use the wall to assist with balance. Engage your calves so that your feet are flat before beginning the stretch.'),
('Calves Stretch Variation Three',2,'Lower the heels of your feet towards the ground and pause, then push through the balls of your feet like you are standing tip toe, pausing at the apex of the stretch.'),
('Calves Stretch Variation Three',3,'Repeat as necessary.'),
('Calves Stretch Variation Two',1,'With both feet flat on the ground, place one leg in front of your shoulder, your other leg should mirror this position behind your other shoulder. In the starting position both of your knees should be straight.'),
('Calves Stretch Variation Two',2,'Place the palms of your hands against the wall at shoulder height in front of you, lean towards the wall and bend your front leg at the knee while keeping your back leg straight.'),
('Calves Stretch Variation Two',3,'Pause at the apex of the stretch and return to the starting position. Switch the position of your legs and repeat.'),
('Cardio Assault Bike',1,'Adjust seat and handlebar height for comfort and proper posture on the assault bike.'),
('Cardio Assault Bike',2,'Start pedaling with even, controlled motion, maintaining your desired resistance level.'),
('Cardio Assault Bike',3,'Monitor heart rate and intensity; increase or decrease resistance for an effective cardio workout.'),
('Cardio Assault Bike Arms Only',1,'Adjust seat and handlebar height for comfort and proper posture on the assault bike.'),
('Cardio Assault Bike Arms Only',2,'Start pedaling with even, controlled motion, maintaining your desired resistance level. Then keep the motion going with only your arms.'),
('Cardio Band Hammer Curl Jacks',1,'Stand with a band looped under both feet and the band grasped in both hands.'),
('Cardio Band Hammer Curl Jacks',2,'Do a light hop and bring your feet outward while simultaneously flexing the elbows.'),
('Cardio Band Hammer Curl Jacks',3,'Bring both feet back together and extend the elbows.'),
('Cardio Band Press Jacks',1,'Stand with the band looped under both feet and the other end of the band in both hands in an overhead press position.'),
('Cardio Band Press Jacks',2,'Do a light hop and bring both feet outward while pressing the band overhead.'),
('Cardio Band Reverse Fly Jacks',1,'Grab the band with a double overhand grip. Bring both feet outward while performing a little hop.'),
('Cardio Band Reverse Fly Jacks',2,'As you hop, pull the band apart.'),
('Cardio Band Seal Jacks',1,'Loop a band around your back. Start with both arms extended at your side.'),
('Cardio Band Seal Jacks',2,'As you perform the jack. Bring both arms together and make a little clap.'),
('Cardio Box Quick Feet',1,'Stay light on your toes and tap both feet to the ground in quick succession.'),
('Cardio Box Quick Feet',2,'Move in a square pattern.'),
('Cardio Criss Cross Jacks',1,'Perform a jumping jack while crossing the feet.'),
('Cardio Diamond Hop',1,'With both feet, leap forward then back, then to the left, then to the right.'),
('Cardio Diamond Hop',2,'Repeat.'),
('Cardio Figure Eight Sprint',1,'Perform s sprint in a figure eight pattern.'),
('Cardio Figure Eight Sprint',2,'Make sure to stay low.'),
('Cardio Forward Scissor',1,'Do a light hop and split your stance.'),
('Cardio Forward Scissor',2,'Land lightly on your toes, and then bring the opposing leg forward.'),
('Cardio In And Out Forward',1,'Bring one leg forward and then the other.'),
('Cardio In And Out Forward',2,'Bring the original leg backwards and then the other.'),
('Cardio In And Outs',1,'Start with both feet together.'),
('Cardio In And Outs',2,'Do a slight hop and bring your feet outwards, then back inwards.'),
('Cardio In In Out Out Shuffle',1,'Start with your feet side by side.'),
('Cardio In In Out Out Shuffle',2,'Bring one foot laterally, then the other.'),
('Cardio In In Out Out Shuffle',3,'Return the first foot to its starting position, then the other.'),
('Cardio Jumping Jacks',1,'Stand with feet together, arms at your sides, ready to jump.'),
('Cardio Jumping Jacks',2,'Jump while spreading legs and raising arms overhead.'),
('Cardio Jumping Jacks',3,'Return to starting position with legs together and arms at your sides. Repeat.'),
('Cardio Karaoke',1,'Stand upright, feet together, facing forward, ready to move laterally.'),
('Cardio Karaoke',2,'Move right foot behind left, then step left foot to the side.'),
('Cardio Karaoke',3,'Alternate crossing and stepping, increase speed, maintain rhythm and balance.'),
('Cardio Knee Taps',1,'Stand straight, feet hip-width apart, engage core.'),
('Cardio Knee Taps',2,'Lift knees alternately, tap with same side hand.'),
('Cardio Knee Taps',3,'Continue rhythmically, maintain posture, increase speed as able.'),
('Cardio Lateral Quick Feet',1,'Start with a shoulder width stance.'),
('Cardio Lateral Quick Feet',2,'Quickly tap your feet while moving laterally.'),
('Cardio Lateral Shuffle',1,'Start with a wide stance.'),
('Cardio Lateral Shuffle',2,'Shuffle sideways for a specified distance while maintaining a quarter squat position.'),
('Cardio Long Jump',1,'Stand feet shoulder-width, knees slightly bent, arms behind you, eyes forward.'),
('Cardio Long Jump',2,'Swing arms backward, squat deeply, loading legs for explosive power.'),
('Cardio Long Jump',3,'Swing arms, explode forward, extend legs mid-air, land softly on both feet.'),
('Cardio Long Jump Shuffle Back',1,'Stand feet shoulder-width, knees slightly bent, arms behind you, eyes forward.'),
('Cardio Long Jump Shuffle Back',2,'Swing arms backward, squat deeply, loading legs for explosive power.'),
('Cardio Long Jump Shuffle Back',3,'Swing arms, explode forward, extend legs mid-air, land softly on both feet.'),
('Cardio Long Jump Shuffle Back',4,'Shuffle back to the starting position.'),
('Cardio Quick Feet',1,'Quickly tap each foot to the ground.'),
('Cardio Row Erg Rower',1,'Sit on seat, feet strapped in, grip handle with arms extended.'),
('Cardio Row Erg Rower',2,'Push with legs, lean back slightly, pull handle to lower ribs.'),
('Cardio Row Erg Rower',3,'Extend arms, lean forward from hips, bend knees to return to start.'),
('Cardio Row Erg Rower Arms Only',1,'Make sure your feet are strapped in tightly.'),
('Cardio Row Erg Rower Arms Only',2,'Without bending your legs, pull the handle to your ribcage.'),
('Cardio Row Erg Rower Arms Only',3,'Fully extend your elbows before initiating the next rep.'),
('Cardio Row Erg Rower Four Stroke Sprint Start',1,'Sit on seat, feet strapped in, grip handle with arms extended.'),
('Cardio Row Erg Rower Four Stroke Sprint Start',2,'Push with legs, lean back slightly. Do four small pulls with increasing distance on each rep.'),
('Cardio Row Erg Rower Four Stroke Sprint Start',3,'Extend arms, lean forward from hips, bend knees to return to start.'),
('Cardio Row Erg Rower Legs Only',1,'Strap your feet in tightly.'),
('Cardio Row Erg Rower Legs Only',2,'Keep your arms extended while flexing and extending at the hips and knees.'),
('Cardio Seal Jacks',1,'Stand with feet together, arms in front at chest level, palms touching.'),
('Cardio Seal Jacks',2,'Spread legs wide, simultaneously swing arms out to sides, palms facing forward.'),
('Cardio Seal Jacks',3,'Jump back to starting position, bringing arms together again quickly. Repeat rhythmically.'),
('Cardio Shuttle Sprint',1,'Set up two cones at a specified distance.'),
('Cardio Shuttle Sprint',2,'Stay low and sprint quickly to the second cone.'),
('Cardio Shuttle Sprint',3,'Hinge forward and tap the cone, then turn and sprint to the original cone.'),
('Cardio Shuttle Sprint',4,'Repeat for the desired time or reps.'),
('Cardio Single Leg Forward Hop',1,'Pick up one leg off the ground.'),
('Cardio Single Leg Forward Hop',2,'Hop forward and backward quickly while staying on your toes.'),
('Cardio Single Leg Lateral Hop',1,'Pick up one leg off the ground.'),
('Cardio Single Leg Lateral Hop',2,'Hop laterally quickly while staying on your toes.'),
('Cardio Skater',1,'Stand, balance on right foot, left foot behind, slightly bent knees.'),
('Cardio Skater',2,'Jump to left, landing on left foot, right foot behind, swinging arms.'),
('Cardio Skater',3,'Continue leaping side-to-side, maintaining balance and speed, like a speed skater.'),
('Cardio Skater To Single Leg Burpee',1,'Leap sideways, land on right foot, left leg behind to the side.'),
('Cardio Skater To Single Leg Burpee',2,'Drop into a single-leg burpee, right leg only, hands to ground.'),
('Cardio Skater To Single Leg Burpee',3,'Return to standing on right, leap sideways to left, repeat with left leg.'),
('Cardio Ski Erg',1,'Leap sideways, land on right foot, left leg behind to the side.'),
('Cardio Ski Erg',2,'Drop into a single-leg burpee, right leg only, hands to ground.'),
('Cardio Ski Erg',3,'Return to standing on right, leap sideways to left, repeat with left leg.'),
('Cardio Sprint In Place',1,'Stand tall, feet hip-width apart, knees slightly bent, ready to move.'),
('Cardio Sprint In Place',2,'Quickly drive knees up towards chest, alternating legs, pumping arms in rhythm.'),
('Cardio Sprint In Place',3,'Gradually speed up, maintaining high knees and arm movement, breathe steadily.'),
('Cardio Step Out Jacks',1,'Stand tall, feet together, arms by sides, ready to move.'),
('Cardio Step Out Jacks',2,'Step right foot out, simultaneously raise arms above head.'),
('Cardio Step Out Jacks',3,'Step right foot in, lower arms, repeat left, maintain rhythm.'),
('Cardio Three Step Heismans',1,'Start with a shoulder width stance.'),
('Cardio Three Step Heismans',2,'Stay on your toes, step right, tap your left toe to the ground, plant your right foot and raise your left leg.'),
('Cardio Three Step Heismans',3,'Then repeat in the opposite direction.'),
('Cat Pose',1,'Begin on your hands and knees with your wrists directly under your shoulders and your knees directly under your hips.'),
('Cat Pose',2,'Inhale and arch your back, lifting your tailbone and head towards the ceiling, while lowering your belly towards the floor.'),
('Cat Pose',3,'Exhale and round your spine, tucking your chin towards your chest, and bringing your tailbone towards your knees.'),
('Cat Pose',4,'Repeat these movements, flowing smoothly between the two poses, for several breaths.'),
('Cervical Extension Band',1,'While seated on a bench, place a ribbon/flat band behind your head. Straighten out your back while still holding onto the ends of the band'),
('Cervical Extension Band',2,'Gently extend the arms till the band starts applying force onto the neck muscles. Maintain the arm position.'),
('Cervical Extension Band',3,'Allow the chin to slide forward, before pulling the head back. The neck in the \"back\" position should be straight and elongated.'),
('Cervical Extension Banded Hold',1,'While seated on a bench, place a ribbon/flat band behind your head.'),
('Cervical Extension Banded Hold',2,'Straighten out your back while still holding onto the ends of the band.'),
('Cervical Extension Banded Hold',3,'Gently extend the arms till the band starts applying force onto the neck muscles.'),
('Cervical Extension Banded Hold',4,'Hold the arm position and resist the band with the strength of your neck muscles.'),
('Cervical Extension Eccentric Band',1,'While seated on a bench, place a ribbon/flat band behind your head.'),
('Cervical Extension Eccentric Band',2,'Straighten out your back while still holding onto the ends of the band.'),
('Cervical Extension Eccentric Band',3,'Gently extend the arms till the band starts applying force onto the neck muscles then bend your arms so that the band resistance is reduced but not eliminated.'),
('Cervical Extension Eccentric Band',4,'Do not allow any movement in your neck.'),
('Cervical Extension Hold',1,'While seated on a bench, straighten your back, pull the shoulders back and allow the head to slightly tilt forward, without rounding the back.'),
('Cervical Extension Hold',2,'Lock your fingers and place the palms on the back-top of your head.'),
('Cervical Extension Hold',3,'Engage the neck muscles by straightening the neck and then rest the weight of your arms on the head.'),
('Cervical Extension Hold',4,'Resist the forward-downward force of your arms with your neck muscles.'),
('Chair Pose',1,'Stand straight with your feet hip-width apart and arms at your sides.'),
('Chair Pose',2,'Inhale and raise your arms straight up over your head.'),
('Chair Pose',3,'Exhale and bend your knees, lowering your hips as if you were sitting in a chair.'),
('Chair Pose',4,'Hold the pose for a few breaths, then inhale and stand up straight.'),
('Chest Stretch Variation Four',1,'Raise your arms to shoulder height, fully extended in front of you.'),
('Chest Stretch Variation Four',2,'Slowly bring your arms behind your back still at shoulder height.'),
('Chest Stretch Variation Four',3,'Pause for a few seconds and then return to starting position.'),
('Chest Stretch Variation One',1,'Using a raised wall, place your arm at a 90 degree angle against it.'),
('Chest Stretch Variation One',2,'With a staggered stance, lean into the wall extending your chest.'),
('Chest Stretch Variation One',3,'Pause for a few seconds and then return to starting position and repeat on opposite side.'),
('Chest Stretch Variation Three',1,'Place your arms behind your back and clasp your hands together.'),
('Chest Stretch Variation Three',2,'Slowly extend your elbows until they are locked then lift them away from you.'),
('Chest Stretch Variation Three',3,'Pause in this position for a few seconds and then return them to starting position.'),
('Chest Stretch Variation Two',1,'Lay on your side with one hand just in front of you.'),
('Chest Stretch Variation Two',2,'With a slight bend in your arm, rotate your arm around your body as slowly as possible.'),
('Chest Stretch Variation Two',3,'Return to the starting position and then repeat on the other side.'),
('Child Pose Arms Extended',1,'Begin in a tabletop position with your hands and knees on the ground.'),
('Child Pose Arms Extended',2,'Sit back onto your heels and extend your arms out in front of you.'),
('Child Pose Arms Extended',3,'Rest your forehead on the ground.'),
('Child Pose Arms Extended',4,'Hold for a few breaths and then release.'),
('Child Pose Arms Extended Left Right',1,'Begin in a tabletop position with your hands and knees on the ground.'),
('Child Pose Arms Extended Left Right',2,'Sit back onto your heels and extend your arms out in front of you to one side.'),
('Child Pose Arms Extended Left Right',3,'Rest your forehead on the ground.'),
('Child Pose Arms Extended Left Right',4,'Hold for a few breaths and then repeat on the other side.'),
('Child Pose Arms On Side',1,'Begin in a tabletop position with your hands and knees on the ground.'),
('Child Pose Arms On Side',2,'Sit back onto your heels and place your arms at your sides with your palms facing up.'),
('Child Pose Arms On Side',3,'Rest your forehead on the ground.'),
('Child Pose Arms On Side',4,'Hold for a few breaths and then release.'),
('Child Pose Elbows On Block',1,'Place two blocks on the floor, shoulder-width apart.'),
('Child Pose Elbows On Block',2,'Kneel in front of the blocks, and lower your torso down so that your elbows are resting on the blocks, and your forehead is resting on the floor.'),
('Child Pose Elbows On Block',3,'Relax your arms, shoulders, and neck, and breathe deeply.'),
('Child Pose Elbows On Block',4,'Hold for a few breaths, then release.'),
('Chin Ups',1,'Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)'),
('Chin Ups',2,'With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.'),
('Chin Ups',3,'Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.'),
('Cobra Pose',1,'Start prone, hands under shoulders.'),
('Cobra Pose',2,'Inhale, lift chest, arch back.'),
('Cobra Pose',3,'Elongate neck, gaze up. Breathe, hold. Release, exhale.'),
('Control Front Plank Position',1,'Place hands on the shoulder rests on feet on the footbar.'),
('Control Front Plank Position',2,'Engage core, glutes tight, body forming a straight line.'),
('Control Front Plank Position',3,'Press arms forward, protract shoulders slightly, keep neck neutral.'),
('Control Front Plank Position',4,'Hold position with steady breathing and full-body tension.'),
('Corpse Pose',1,'Lie down on your back with your legs straight and arms at your sides.'),
('Corpse Pose',2,'Close your eyes and take deep breaths in through your nose and out through your mouth.'),
('Corpse Pose',3,'Allow your body to completely relax and let go of any tension.'),
('Corpse Pose',4,'Hold for several minutes and then slowly come back up to a seated position.'),
('Crescent Moon Pose',1,'Begin in Runner\'s Lunge pose with your right foot forward.'),
('Crescent Moon Pose',2,'Slowly lift your torso up and bring your arms overhead, palms facing each other.'),
('Crescent Moon Pose',3,'Make sure your right knee is directly above your ankle, and your left leg is straight behind you.'),
('Crescent Moon Pose',4,'Hold for a few breaths before repeating on the other side.'),
('Crescent Moon Pose Quad Stretch',1,'Begin in Crescent Moon Pose with your right foot forward and a block nearby.'),
('Crescent Moon Pose Quad Stretch',2,'Place the block at the highest height under your left hand.'),
('Crescent Moon Pose Quad Stretch',3,'Reach your left arm behind you and take hold of your left foot or ankle.'),
('Crescent Moon Pose Quad Stretch',4,'Gently pull your foot towards your buttocks while pressing your left hand into the block to deepen the stretch in your left quad. Hold for a few breaths before releasing and repeating on the other side.'),
('Crescent Moon Pose Quad Stretch With Block',1,'Begin in Crescent Moon Pose with your right foot forward and a block nearby.'),
('Crescent Moon Pose Quad Stretch With Block',2,'Place the block at the highest height under your left hand.'),
('Crescent Moon Pose Quad Stretch With Block',3,'Reach your left arm behind you and take hold of your left foot or ankle.'),
('Crescent Moon Pose Quad Stretch With Block',4,'Gently pull your foot towards your buttocks while pressing your left hand into the block to deepen the stretch in your left quad. Hold for a few breaths before releasing and repeating on the other side.'),
('Criss Cross Bow Tie Pose',1,'Stand with your feet hip-width apart and your arms at your sides.'),
('Criss Cross Bow Tie Pose',2,'Cross your right arm over your left arm, bringing your palms together in front of your chest.'),
('Criss Cross Bow Tie Pose',3,'Lower your arms down so that your palms face down towards the ground, and your right elbow is resting on top of your left elbow.'),
('Criss Cross Bow Tie Pose',4,'Hold for a few breaths, then switch sides.'),
('Crow Pose',1,'Begin in a squatting position with your feet together and your knees apart.'),
('Crow Pose',2,'Place your hands on the floor in front of you, shoulder-width apart. Keep your arms straight and engage your core.'),
('Crow Pose',3,'Slowly shift your weight forward and lift your feet off the ground, coming onto your tiptoes.'),
('Crow Pose',4,'Bend your elbows and lean your weight onto your hands, shifting your knees towards your upper arms.'),
('Crow Pose',5,'Gently lift one foot off the ground, and then the other, balancing on your hands. Hold the pose for a few breaths before releasing back to the ground.'),
('Crunches',1,'Lay flat on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the ground, about a foot from your lower back.'),
('Crunches',2,'Place your fingertips on your temples with your palms facing out.'),
('Crunches',3,'Draw your belly into the base of your spine to engage the muscles, then raise your head and shoulders off the floor. Return to starting position and repeat.'),
('Curve Treadmill',1,'Get the treadmill up to a comfortable speed where you are doing a walk.'),
('Dead Hang',1,'Grip a pull-up bar with palms facing forward.'),
('Dead Hang',2,'Hang with arms fully extended.'),
('Dead Hang',3,'Hold for recommended amount of time, keeping your core engaged.'),
('Decline Push Up',1,'Use a bench to elevate your feet.'),
('Decline Push Up',2,'Put your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width.'),
('Decline Push Up',3,'Slowly lower your body until your chest almost touches the ground'),
('Decline Push Up',4,'Raise your body until you almost lock your elbows.'),
('Depth Jump',1,'Stand on top of a box. Step off of the box and land on the floor.'),
('Depth Jump',2,'Land as softly as possible. Squat as you land to minimise impact on your joints.'),
('Depth Jump',3,'Go straight into another hop after you\'ve landed. This will help you learn to absorb impact.'),
('Diamond Push Ups',1,'Position your index fingers and thumbs so they are touching, forming a diamond shape'),
('Diamond Push Ups',2,'Use a standard push up position'),
('Diamond Push Ups',3,'Lower your chest towards your hands, keep your elbows close to your body'),
('Diamond Push Ups',4,'Stop just before your chest touches the floor, then push back up to the starting position.'),
('Dorsal Flexion Hold',1,'From the standing position, raise your toes and balance on your heels for the given duration.'),
('Dorsal Flexion Hold',2,'Maintain a good upper body form.'),
('Double Pigeon Pose',1,'Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you.'),
('Double Pigeon Pose',2,'Place a block under your left knee, then bend your right knee and stack it on top of your left ankle.'),
('Double Pigeon Pose',3,'Flex both feet and gently press your knees towards the ground, feeling a stretch in your hips.'),
('Double Pigeon Pose',4,'Hold the pose for a few breaths, then switch sides and repeat.'),
('Downward Dog',1,'Begin on your hands and knees with your hands shoulder-width apart and your knees hip-width apart.'),
('Downward Dog',2,'Spread your fingers wide and press down into your palms, making sure that your fingers are evenly spaced and facing forward.'),
('Downward Dog',3,'Tuck your toes under and lift your knees off the ground, straightening your legs as much as possible.'),
('Downward Dog',4,'Press your hips up and back, bringing your body into an inverted \"V\" shape.'),
('Downward Dog',5,'Keep your arms straight and your shoulder blades spread apart, and try to press your heels down towards the ground.'),
('Downward Dog',6,'Hold the pose for several breaths, then release and return to your starting position.'),
('Downward Dog Toe To Heel',1,'Begin in a downward-facing dog position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your feet hip-width apart.'),
('Downward Dog Toe To Heel',2,'Lift your right foot off the mat and place your right toes on top of your left heel.'),
('Downward Dog Toe To Heel',3,'Press your palms and fingers firmly into the mat and lift your hips up towards the ceiling, deepening the stretch in your hamstrings and calves.'),
('Downward Dog Toe To Heel',4,'Hold the pose for a few breaths, and then release by slowly walking your hands back out to a downward-facing dog position.'),
('Downward Dog With Fingers Facing Feet',1,'Begin in the same starting position as the previous exercise, with your hands and knees on the ground.'),
('Downward Dog With Fingers Facing Feet',2,'Spread your fingers wide and turn your hands so that your fingers are facing towards your feet.'),
('Downward Dog With Fingers Facing Feet',3,'Tuck your toes under and lift your knees off the ground, straightening your legs as much as possible.'),
('Downward Dog With Fingers Facing Feet',4,'Press your hips up and back, bringing your body into an inverted \"V\" shape.'),
('Downward Dog With Fingers Facing Feet',5,'Keep your arms straight and your shoulder blades spread apart, and try to press your heels down towards the ground.'),
('Downward Dog With Fingers Facing Feet',6,'Hold the pose for several breaths, then release and return to your starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Arnold Press',1,'Start in a standing position'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Forward Lunge',1,'Stand tall, holding dumbbells by your sides, feet hip-width apart.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Forward Lunge',2,'Step forward with one leg, lowering until both knees form 90° angles.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Forward Lunge',3,'Push through front foot, return to start, and switch legs.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Lateral Lunge',1,'Hold one dumbbell with one or both hands, feet hip-width apart.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Lateral Lunge',2,'Step out to one side, bending the knee.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Lateral Lunge',3,'Push off, return to center, then switch sides.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Overhead Press',1,'Start with two dumbbells just above your shoulders.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Overhead Press',2,'Press one dumbbell to the ceiling while keeping the other in place.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Overhead Press',3,'Let the first dumbbell return to its starting position before pressing the other dumbbell.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Pendlay Row',1,'The dumbbells should be set on the ground. Hinge forward while keeping a flat back.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Pendlay Row',2,'Pull one elbow back toward the ceiling and then return the dumbbell to the ground softly.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Pendlay Row',3,'Then pull with the other arm.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Rear Delt Fly',1,'With dumbbells in either hand, bend your knees with your feet slightly bowed out. Arch your back above your knees, and start with the weights touching in front of your chest.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Rear Delt Fly',2,'With bent elbows, raise your arms up to shoulder level, pausing at the at the end of the motion.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Rear Delt Fly',3,'Slowly lower your arms back to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Reverse Lunge',1,'Hold two dumbbells by your side.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Reverse Lunge',2,'Take a big step backwards with your left leg, lowering your body until your left thigh is parallel to the ground and your right knee is bent at a 90-degree angle.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Reverse Lunge',3,'Push back up and switch legs, alternating each rep.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Single Arm Press',1,'Start in a bench press position with two dumbbells.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Single Arm Press',2,'Break at one of your elbows first while keeping the other elbow extended.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Single Arm Press',3,'Your working arm should reach your side before pressing back to the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Single Arm Press',4,'Then alternate to the other arm.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Single Arm Thruster',1,'Hold two dumbbells at shoulder height, palms facing inward.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Single Arm Thruster',2,'Squat down, then drive upward, pressing one dumbbell overhead.'),
('Dumbbell Alternating Single Arm Thruster',3,'Lower dumbbell as you descend again, alternating arms each rep.'),
('Dumbbell Arnold Press',1,'Stand with both palms facing you.'),
('Dumbbell Arnold Press',2,'Begin to press the dumbbells to the ceiling while rotating your palms.'),
('Dumbbell Arnold Press',3,'When you reach elbow extension, your palms should be facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Assisted Bulgarian Split Squat',1,'Grab a stick of some sort or hold onto something stable (rack, bench).'),
('Dumbbell Assisted Bulgarian Split Squat',2,'Grab a box that is knee height or slightly lower.'),
('Dumbbell Assisted Bulgarian Split Squat',3,'Hold the stick in your right arm, dumbbell in the other and put your right leg on the box.'),
('Dumbbell Assisted Bulgarian Split Squat',4,'Begin your squat by breaking at the knees. Get your knee close to the floor or all the way to the floor. Make sure to keep your chest tall.'),
('Dumbbell Bayesian Lateral Raise',1,'Lay on an incline bench and let your arms freely.'),
('Dumbbell Bayesian Lateral Raise',2,'Lateral raise your arms straight out to the side until your arms are about parallel with the ground.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Flat Curl',1,'Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips pushed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Flat Curl',2,'Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Hammer Flat Curl',1,'Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips pushed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Hammer Flat Curl',2,'Take a neutral grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Hammer Incline Curl',1,'Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Hammer Incline Curl',2,'Take a neutral grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Incline Curl',1,'Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Incline Curl',2,'Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Reverse Flat Curl',1,'Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips pushed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Reverse Flat Curl',2,'Take an overhand grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Reverse Incline Curl',1,'Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Reverse Incline Curl',2,'Take an overhand grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Reverse Incline Curl',3,'Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Reverse Incline Curl',4,'Take an overhand grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Rolling Curl',1,'Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips pushed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Rolling Curl',2,'Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Single Arm Overhead Tricep Extension',1,'Lay sideways on an incline bench and press the elbow of the working arm into the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Single Arm Overhead Tricep Extension',2,'Use your free arm to pull your upper body into the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Braced Single Arm Overhead Tricep Extension',3,'Break at the elbow until your elbow is fully flexed, then extend your elbow until the dumbbell is pointed at the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Press',1,'Start by lying flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Press',2,'Hold the dumbbells at chest level with your palms facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Press',3,'Engage your core and press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Wrist Curl',1,'Grip the dumbbell with your palm facing upwards with your forearm rested against the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Wrist Curl',2,'Slowly curl your wrist upwards in a semicircular motion.'),
('Dumbbell Bench Wrist Curl',3,'Return to starting position and repeat.'),
('Dumbbell Bent Arm Lateral Raise',1,'Stand tall with a 90 degree bend at your elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Bent Arm Lateral Raise',2,'Lateral raise your arms straight out to the side until your arms are about parallel with the ground.'),
('Dumbbell Box Squat',1,'Stand in front of a box or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart with a dumbbell in a goblet position.'),
('Dumbbell Box Squat',2,'Lower your body into a squat position, sitting back onto the box and pausing for a moment before standing back up.'),
('Dumbbell Box Squat',3,'Push through your heels to return to the standing position.'),
('Dumbbell Bulgarian Split Squat',1,'Find a box or bench that is roughly knee height or a few inches lower. (The lower the box is the lower the mobility requirement).'),
('Dumbbell Bulgarian Split Squat',2,'You can either place your toes or the top of your foot on the box. Point your front foot forward or slightly turned outwards and break at the knees and hips simultaneously.'),
('Dumbbell Bulgarian Split Squat',3,'Aim to get your front leg to hit parallel depth (hamstring parallel with the ground) or lower.'),
('Dumbbell Bulgarian Split Squat',4,'The further forward your front foot is, the longer the Range of Motion is at your hips. The further back your front foot is, the longer the ROM at your knees.'),
('Dumbbell Calf Raise',1,'Stand tall with your feet on the ground. You can put the the balls of your feet on top of a plate to extend the range of motion.'),
('Dumbbell Calf Raise',2,'Imagine you have a string attached to your heels and pull your heels up toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Chest Fly',1,'Lay on a bench with two dumbbells extended in front of you.'),
('Dumbbell Chest Fly',2,'You should have a slight bend in your elbows and maintain that bend. Your shoulder joint should do all the movement.'),
('Dumbbell Chest Fly',3,'Bring the dumbbells out to your side. Stop the dumbbells before going behind your body.'),
('Dumbbell Chest Fly',4,'Bring the dumbbells back together at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Clean And Press',1,'Hold dumbbells at sides, hinge slightly, and explosively pull to shoulders.'),
('Dumbbell Clean And Press',2,'Catch dumbbells at shoulder height with knees slightly bent.'),
('Dumbbell Clean And Press',3,'Press overhead until arms extend, then lower under control.'),
('Dumbbell Concentration Curl',1,'Sit on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor and your back straight.'),
('Dumbbell Concentration Curl',2,'Lean forward and place your elbow on the inside of your leg.'),
('Dumbbell Concentration Curl',3,'Curl the dumbbell while keeping your elbow against your leg. Make sure to fully extend your elbow on each rep.'),
('Dumbbell Cross Body Romanian Deadlift',1,'Stand with a shoulder width stance holding one dumbbell. Push your butt back while leaving your knees MOSTLY extended.'),
('Dumbbell Cross Body Romanian Deadlift',2,'Reach toward the opposing leg. You should feel a stretch in your hamstrings. When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward to complete the rep.'),
('Dumbbell Cross Body Romanian Deadlift',3,'Do not push your hips all the way forward. This will hyperextend your spine. Just go to a normal standing position.'),
('Dumbbell Crunch',1,'Start by lying flat on your back with your feet flat on the floor and your knees bent.'),
('Dumbbell Crunch',2,'Hold a dumbbell over your clavicle.'),
('Dumbbell Crunch',3,'Engage your core muscles and lift your torso off the floor until your shoulders are a few inches off the ground.'),
('Dumbbell Crunch',4,'Lower yourself back down to the starting position, but avoid resting completely on the floor between reps.'),
('Dumbbell Cuban Press',1,'Perform an upright row until elbows are bent at 90 degrees and arms parallel to the ground.'),
('Dumbbell Cuban Press',2,'Rotate your shoulders, raising the dumbbells overhead. Then press overhead.'),
('Dumbbell Curl',1,'Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand at arm\'s length.'),
('Dumbbell Curl',2,'Raise one dumbbell and twist your forearm until it is vertical and your palm faces the shoulder.'),
('Dumbbell Curl',3,'Lower to original position and repeat with opposite arm'),
('Dumbbell Curtsy Deficit Lunge',1,'Stand on a platform, dumbbells in both hands, feet hip-width apart.'),
('Dumbbell Curtsy Deficit Lunge',2,'Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Curtsy Deficit Lunge',3,'Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Alternating Single Arm Press',1,'Lay on a decline bench with both arms extended in front of you.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Alternating Single Arm Press',2,'Break at one of your arms first bringing that arm to your side while keeping the other arm extended.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Alternating Single Arm Press',3,'Press the dumbbell back to the ceiling. Fully extend that arm before initiating on the other side.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Bench Press',1,'Lay on a decline bench with both arms extended in front of you.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Bench Press',2,'Break at the elbows and bring your upper arms to your side.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Bench Press',3,'Once your upper arms have reached your side, press the dumbbells back to the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Chest Fly',1,'Lay flat on a decline bench press with the dumbbells pointed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Chest Fly',2,'Maintain a slight bend in your elbows. Bring the dumbbells out to the side, stopping the dumbbells before they pass your torso.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Chest Fly',3,'Bring the dumbbells together to finish the rep.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Guillotine Bench Press',1,'Lie on the decline bench, grasp a pair of dumbbells and hold them at shoulder level with your palms facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Guillotine Bench Press',2,'Slowly lower the dumbbells to your chest, keeping your elbows flared out. As you lower the dumbbells, exhale deeply.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Guillotine Bench Press',3,'Once your elbows reach your chest, pause for a moment and then press them back up to the starting position'),
('Dumbbell Decline Neutral Bench Press',1,'Lie on the decline bench, grasp a pair of dumbbells and hold them at shoulder level with your palms facing each other. Keep your elbows bent and close to your body.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Neutral Bench Press',2,'Slowly lower the dumbbells to your chest, keeping your elbows bent and close to your body.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Neutral Bench Press',3,'Once the dumbbells reach your chest, pause for a moment and then press them back up to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Neutral Bench Press',4,'This variation is much easier on the shoulder joints.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Single Arm Bench Press',1,'Start by laying on a decline bench with two dumbbells.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Single Arm Bench Press',2,'Position the dumbbell above your chest with your elbow bent and shoulder level.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Single Arm Bench Press',3,'Slowly lower the dumbbell towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body and your core engaged while the other dumbbell remains pointed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Single Arm Bench Press',4,'Once the dumbbell reaches your side, pause for a moment and then press the weight back up to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Single Arm Bench Press',5,'Repeat for the desired number of repetitions before switching to your other arm.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Skullcrusher',1,'Start by lying on a decline bench with a dumbbell in each hand.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Skullcrusher',2,'Hold the dumbbells above your chest with your arms extended and your palms facing each other. This is the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Skullcrusher',3,'Slowly lower the dumbbells towards your forehead by bending your elbows. Keep your upper arms stationary and only move your forearms.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Skullcrusher',4,'Once the dumbbells are close to your forehead, reverse the motion by extending your elbows and returning to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Squeeze Press',1,'Lay flat on a decline bench with two dumbbells pressed to one another.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Squeeze Press',2,'Break at the elbows and keep your elbows tucked as you bring the dumbbells to your chest.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Squeeze Press',3,'Continue to press the dumbbells into one another throughout the rep.'),
('Dumbbell Decline Squeeze Press',4,'Once the dumbbells reach your chest, press back toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Deficit Reverse Lunge',1,'Stand on a platform, dumbbells in both hands, feet hip-width apart.'),
('Dumbbell Deficit Reverse Lunge',2,'Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Deficit Reverse Lunge',3,'Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.'),
('Dumbbell Drag Curl',1,'Hold dumbbells at sides with palms forward and elbows tight to body.'),
('Dumbbell Drag Curl',2,'Curl dumbbells by dragging them along torso, moving elbows behind you.'),
('Dumbbell Drag Curl',3,'Squeeze biceps at top, then lower slowly to start position.'),
('Dumbbell Elbow Side Plank',1,'Take an elbow side plank position. Place a dumbbell on your hip.'),
('Dumbbell Elbow Side Plank',2,'Raise your hip up into position for the allotted amount of time.'),
('Dumbbell Elevated Pushup',1,'Start by placing two dumbbells on the floor, about shoulder-width apart.'),
('Dumbbell Elevated Pushup',2,'Position yourself in a plank position with your hands on top of the dumbbells, keeping your arms straight.'),
('Dumbbell Elevated Pushup',3,'Keep your feet together, with your toes resting on the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Elevated Pushup',4,'Engage your core and lower your body towards the floor by bending your arms, until your chest nearly touches the dumbbells.'),
('Dumbbell Elevated Pushup',5,'Push your body back up to the starting position, straightening your arms and engaging your chest, triceps and shoulders.'),
('Dumbbell External Rotation',1,'Hold a dumbbell in one hand, elbow bent at 90 degrees while resting on your inner thigh/ knee.'),
('Dumbbell External Rotation',2,'Rotate your arm outward, keeping your elbow stable.'),
('Dumbbell Farmer Walk',1,'Grab a dumbbell in each hand, arms straight down.'),
('Dumbbell Farmer Walk',2,'Walk forward with a straight posture.'),
('Dumbbell Feet Down Russian Twist',1,'Sit with feet on floor, lean back slightly, holding dumbbell at chest.'),
('Dumbbell Feet Down Russian Twist',2,'Rotate torso and move dumbbell toward one side without letting feet lift.'),
('Dumbbell Feet Down Russian Twist',3,'Twist to opposite side, keeping core tight and movement controlled.'),
('Dumbbell Flat Preacher Curl',1,'Start with a with a dumbbell in one hand and your tricep resting on flat bench.'),
('Dumbbell Flat Preacher Curl',2,'From this starting position, curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary on the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Floor Fly',1,'Lie on your back holding dumbbells above chest with slight elbow bend.'),
('Dumbbell Floor Fly',2,'Lower arms out wide until elbows lightly touch the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Floor Fly',3,'Bring dumbbells back together over chest, squeezing pecs at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Floor Press',1,'Bring your elbows to the floor, rest for a second to remove all the momentum from the rep, then press to a lockout.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Curtsy Deficit Lunge',1,'Stand on a platform, dumbbells in front rack, feet hip-width apart.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Curtsy Deficit Lunge',2,'Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Curtsy Deficit Lunge',3,'Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Deficit Reverse Lunge',1,'Stand on a platform, dumbbells in front rack position, feet hip-width apart.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Deficit Reverse Lunge',2,'Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Deficit Reverse Lunge',3,'Push through front foot, return to start'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Pause Squat',1,'Place two dumbbells on your shoulders and make sure you force your elbows upward.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Pause Squat',2,'Push your hips back and break at the knees.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Pause Squat',3,'When you reach parallel (hamstrings parallel with the ground) pause for 1-3 seconds. Then push through your heels back to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Squat',1,'Place two dumbbells on your shoulders and push your elbows upward.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Squat',2,'Push your hips back and break at the knees.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Squat',3,'Hit parallel depth and then drive through your heels back to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Stability Ball Wall Squat',1,'Place a stability ball against a wall at about hip height.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Stability Ball Wall Squat',2,'Hold two dumbbells in front rack position.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Stability Ball Wall Squat',3,'Break at the hips and knees until you hit parallel or just below, then squat back up.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Step Up',1,'Stand in front of a step or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold two dumbbells at your shoulders with an overhand grip.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Step Up',2,'Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing off your foot to raise your body up onto the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Step Up',3,'Bring your left foot up onto the bench and stand up straight, keeping the barbell at your shoulders.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Step Up',4,'Step back down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, to return to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Step Up Knee Drive',1,'Hold dumbbells in front rack position and place one foot on platform.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Step Up Knee Drive',2,'Drive through front heel to step up, keeping chest tall and core braced.'),
('Dumbbell Front Rack Step Up Knee Drive',3,'Lift trailing knee high at the top, then step down slowly with control.'),
('Dumbbell Front Raise',1,'Grab two dumbbells while standing upright with the dumbbells at your side.'),
('Dumbbell Front Raise',2,'Raise the two dumbbells with your elbows being fully extended until the dumbbells are eye level.'),
('Dumbbell Front Raise',3,'Lower the weights in a controlled manner to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Dumbbell Full Front Raise',1,'Stand tall with an overhand grip on the dumbbell. Raise your arms until your fists are pointed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Full Front Raise',2,'Return to the start under control. This exercise is prone to using momentum when you begin to fatigue.'),
('Dumbbell Full Lateral Raise',1,'Stand up straight with dumbbells at either side, palms facing your hips.'),
('Dumbbell Full Lateral Raise',2,'Raise your arms on either side with a slight bend in your elbow until they are over head. Pause at the top of the motion.'),
('Dumbbell Full Lateral Raise',3,'Slowly return your arms down to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Glute Bridge',1,'Lay flat on the ground with both feet planted. Make sure you keep your heels glued to the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Glute Bridge',2,'Place the dumbbell on your hips. Push your hips toward the ceiling until you feel your glutes contract.'),
('Dumbbell Glute Bridge',3,'Then return to the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Alternating Curtsy Lunge',1,'Hold a dumbbell at your chest, feet hip-width apart.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Alternating Curtsy Lunge',2,'Step one leg diagonally back into a lunge.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Alternating Curtsy Lunge',3,'Alternate legs, keeping your chest up and core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Bulgarian Split Squat',1,'Holding the dumbbell in a goblet squat place your foot on a bench or box.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Bulgarian Split Squat',2,'Break at the hips and knees. Try to go to the point where your hamstring is parallel with the ground. Or until your back knee taps the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Bulgarian Split Squat',3,'Make sure to keep your back flat and your elbows directly under your fists.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Curtsy Deficit Lunge',1,'Stand on a platform, dumbbell in goblet squat position, feet hip-width apart.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Curtsy Deficit Lunge',2,'Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Curtsy Deficit Lunge',3,'Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Curtsy Deficit Lunge',4,'Stand on a platform, dumbbell in goblet squat position, feet hip-width apart.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Curtsy Deficit Lunge',5,'Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Curtsy Deficit Lunge',6,'Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Deficit Reverse Lunge',1,'Stand on a platform, dumbbell in a goblet position, feet hip-width apart.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Deficit Reverse Lunge',2,'Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Deficit Reverse Lunge',3,'Push through front foot, return to start.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Good Morning',1,'Hold the dumbbell in a goblet position. With your elbows directly under your fists.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Good Morning',2,'Push your hips back while leaving your knees MOSTLY extended. You should feel a stretch in your hamstrings.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Good Morning',3,'When you feel the stretch push your hips forward until you\'re back in a standing position.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Lateral Lunge',1,'Engage your core by drawing your belly button towards your spine. This will help to stabilize your body. Hold a dumbbell in a goblet position.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Lateral Lunge',2,'Take a large step to the side with your right foot, planting it firmly on the ground.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Lateral Lunge',3,'As you step, bend your right knee and lower your hips until your right thigh is parallel to the ground. Your left leg should remain straight.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Lateral Lunge',4,'Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Repeat on the opposite side by stepping out with your left foot.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Pulse Squat',1,'Hold a dumbbell in goblet position.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Pulse Squat',2,'Squat down to parallel depth and then halfway back up.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Pulse Squat',3,'Stay in this short range of motion for the duration of the set.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Side Step Up',1,'Begin by standing beside a sturdy box or bench that is about knee-height, holding a dumbbell with a goblet grip.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Side Step Up',2,'Place your right foot on the box and push through the heel to lift your body up and onto the box.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Side Step Up',3,'Step back down with your right foot.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Squat',1,'Hold the weight tucked into your upper chest area, keeping your elbows in. Your feet should be slightly wider than shoulder width.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Squat',2,'Sink down into the squat, keeping your elbows inside the track of your knees.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Squat',3,'Push through your heels while keeping your chest up and return to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Step Up',1,'Begin by standing in front of a sturdy box or bench that is about knee-height, holding a dumbbell with a goblet grip.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Step Up',2,'Place your right foot on the box and push through the heel to lift your body up and onto the box.'),
('Dumbbell Goblet Step Up',3,'Step back down with your right foot.'),
('Dumbbell Guillotine Bench Press',1,'Lie on the flat bench, grasp a pair of dumbbells and hold them at shoulder level with your palms facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Guillotine Bench Press',2,'Slowly lower the dumbbells to your chest, keeping your elbows flared out. As you lower the dumbbells, exhale deeply.'),
('Dumbbell Guillotine Bench Press',3,'Once your elbows reach your chest, pause for a moment and then press them back up to the starting position'),
('Dumbbell Guillotine Incline Bench Press',1,'Lie on the incline bench, grasp a pair of dumbbells and hold them at shoulder level with your palms facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Guillotine Incline Bench Press',2,'Slowly lower the dumbbells to your chest, keeping your elbows flared out. As you lower the dumbbells, exhale deeply.'),
('Dumbbell Guillotine Incline Bench Press',3,'Once your elbows reach your chest, pause for a moment and then press them back up to the starting position'),
('Dumbbell Half Kneeling Goblet Romanian Deadlift',1,'Place one knee on a bench and hold a dumbbell in a goblet position.'),
('Dumbbell Half Kneeling Goblet Romanian Deadlift',2,'Push your hips back while leaving your knee mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.'),
('Dumbbell Half Kneeling Goblet Romanian Deadlift',3,'When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you\'re back in a standing position.'),
('Dumbbell Half Kneeling Overhead Press',1,'Take a half kneeling position while holding two dumbbells.'),
('Dumbbell Half Kneeling Overhead Press',2,'Drive the dumbbells upwards.'),
('Dumbbell Half Kneeling Romanian Deadlift',1,'Place one knee on a bench and hold a dumbbell.'),
('Dumbbell Half Kneeling Romanian Deadlift',2,'Push your hips back while leaving your knee mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.'),
('Dumbbell Half Kneeling Romanian Deadlift',3,'When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you\'re back in a standing position.'),
('Dumbbell Half Kneeling Single Arm Overhead Press',1,'Take a half kneeling position while holding one dumbbell.'),
('Dumbbell Half Kneeling Single Arm Overhead Press',2,'Drive the dumbbell upwards.'),
('Dumbbell Half Kneeling Wood Chopper',1,'Take a half kneeling position. Start with the dumbbell by your knee on the side of the kneeling leg.'),
('Dumbbell Half Kneeling Wood Chopper',2,'Rotate at the upper spine, holding the dumbbell away from your body with nearly extended elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Hammer Curl',1,'Hold the dumbbells with a neutral grip (thumbs facing the ceiling).'),
('Dumbbell Hammer Curl',2,'Slowly lift the dumbbell up to chest height'),
('Dumbbell Hammer Curl',3,'Return to starting position and repeat.'),
('Dumbbell Hand Side Plank',1,'Start by lying on your side with your feet stacked on top of each other and a dumbbell on your hip.'),
('Dumbbell Hand Side Plank',2,'Place your bottom hand on the ground beneath your shoulder and engage your core to raise your hips off the ground.'),
('Dumbbell Hand Side Plank',3,'From this starting position, hold the side plank position for the desired amount of time, making sure to keep your body straight and your hips level.'),
('Dumbbell Hang Clean And Press',1,'Hold dumbbells at thighs with slight knee bend and flat back.'),
('Dumbbell Hang Clean And Press',2,'Pull dumbbells to shoulders explosively, catching them in partial squat.'),
('Dumbbell Hang Clean And Press',3,'Stand tall and press overhead until arms are fully extended.'),
('Dumbbell Head On Bench Rear Delt Fly',1,'With dumbbells in either hand, bend your knees with your feet slightly bowed out. Arch your back above your knees, place your head on the top of an incline bench, and start with the weights touching in front of your chest.'),
('Dumbbell Head On Bench Rear Delt Fly',2,'With bent elbows, raise your arms up to shoulder level, pausing at the at the end of the motion.'),
('Dumbbell Head On Bench Rear Delt Fly',3,'Slowly lower your arms back to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Heels Up Goblet Squat',1,'Take a half kneeling stance. The dumbbell should start over your knee that is up.'),
('Dumbbell Heels Up Goblet Squat',2,'Rotate at the spine and point the dumbbell to the opposing side.'),
('Dumbbell Heels Up Narrow Goblet Squat',1,'Stand with your feet on a plate. Your feet should be very close to one another, but not touching.'),
('Dumbbell Heels Up Narrow Goblet Squat',2,'Begin your squat by pushing your hips back and breaking at the knees. Try to keep your chest tall while squatting.'),
('Dumbbell High Incline Bench Press',1,'Position the bench between 45 and 60 degrees.'),
('Dumbbell High Incline Bench Press',2,'Lay flat on the bench with your feet on the ground.'),
('Dumbbell High Incline Bench Press',3,'Lower the bar to your mid chest'),
('Dumbbell High Incline Bench Press',4,'Raise the dumbbells (slowly and controlled) until you\'ve locked your elbows.'),
('Dumbbell High Incline Skullover',1,'Set bench to high incline and hold dumbbells above chest.'),
('Dumbbell High Incline Skullover',2,'Flex elbows first, then flex the shoulders until a stretch is felt in your triceps.'),
('Dumbbell High Incline Skullover',3,'Bring your elbows back up until they are pointed at the ceiling, then extend your elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Hip Thrust',1,'Place your shoulder blades against a box or bench that won\'t move.'),
('Dumbbell Hip Thrust',2,'Both your feet should be planted and your heels should not come off the floor. Point your toes forward.'),
('Dumbbell Hip Thrust',3,'Break at the hips. Seek the longest range of motion possible. Focus on the top end of the movement. Push your hips as high as possible on each rep.'),
('Dumbbell Hollow Hold',1,'Lay flat on the ground with a dumbbell overhead.'),
('Dumbbell Hollow Hold',2,'Pull your upper back and legs off the ground. Make a banana shape with your body.'),
('Dumbbell Hollow Hold',3,'The dumbbell should be held in your hands and your ears should be between your biceps.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Bench Press',1,'Lay flat on the incline bench with your feet on the ground. Raise the dumbbells until you have straight arms.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Bench Press',2,'Lower the dumbbells to your mid chest'),
('Dumbbell Incline Bench Press',3,'Raise the dumbbells until you\'ve locked your elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Chest Fly',1,'Lay on an incline bench with two dumbbells extended in front of you.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Chest Fly',2,'You should have a slight bend in your elbows and maintain that bend. Your shoulder joint should do all the movement.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Chest Fly',3,'Bring the dumbbells out to your side. Stop the dumbbells before going behind your body.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Chest Fly',4,'Bring the dumbbells back together at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Chest Flys',1,'Lay flat on the bench and place your feet on the ground.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Chest Flys',2,'Begin the exercise with the dumbbells held together above your chest, elbows slightly bent.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Chest Flys',3,'Simultaneously lower the weights to either side.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Chest Flys',4,'Pause when the weights are parallel to the bench, then raise your arms to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Curl',1,'Hold the dumbbells with an underhand grip. Seated on an incline bench.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Curl',2,'Slowly lift the dumbbell up to chest height'),
('Dumbbell Incline Curl',3,'Return to starting position and repeat.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Front Raise',1,'Grab two dumbbells while sitting on an incline bench upright with the dumbbells at your side.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Front Raise',2,'Raise the two dumbbells with your elbows being fully extended until the dumbbells are eye level.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Front Raise',3,'Lower the weights in a controlled manner to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Hammer Curl',1,'Hold the dumbbells with a neutral grip (thumbs facing the ceiling). Seated on an incline bench.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Hammer Curl',2,'Slowly lift the dumbbell up to chest height'),
('Dumbbell Incline Hammer Curl',3,'Return to starting position and repeat.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Reverse Curl',1,'Lay on an incline bench.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Reverse Curl',2,'Grab the dumbbells with a pronated (overhand) grip. You can do this exercise thumbless if it\'s more comfortable on your wrists.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Reverse Curl',3,'Flex at the elbows until your biceps touch your forearms. Try not to let your elbows flair outward.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Skullcrusher',1,'Set bench to incline and hold dumbbells above chest with palms facing in.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Skullcrusher',2,'Bend elbows to lower dumbbells toward forehead under control.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Skullcrusher',3,'Extend arms fully, squeezing triceps at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Skullover',1,'Lay flat on an incline bench with two dumbbells pointed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Skullover',2,'Break at the elbows until your forearms touch your biceps, then flex at the shoulder joint bringing your upper arms to the sides of your head.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Skullover',3,'Bring your elbows back up until they are pointed at the ceiling, then extend your elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Twisting Curl',1,'Sit on incline bench holding dumbbells at sides, palms facing inward.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Twisting Curl',2,'Curl one dumbbell while twisting palm toward shoulder.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Twisting Curl',3,'Lower slowly, then repeat with opposite arm.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Zottman Curl',1,'Lay on an incline bench with your palms facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Zottman Curl',2,'Flex at the elbows until your forearms touch your biceps.'),
('Dumbbell Incline Zottman Curl',3,'When you hit the top of the movement, rotate your palms and then lower the dumbbells slowly.'),
('Dumbbell Internal Rotation',1,'Lay flat on the ground with your elbow on the floor and dumbbell pointed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Internal Rotation',2,'Lower the dumbbell until your knuckles get close to the ground. Then back to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Chest Fly',1,'Lay on a bench with two dumbbells extended in front of you in an overhand grip.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Chest Fly',2,'You should have a slight bend in your elbows and maintain that bend. Your shoulder joint should do all the movement.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Chest Fly',3,'Bring the dumbbells out to your side. Stop the dumbbells before going behind your body.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Chest Fly',4,'Bring the dumbbells back together at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Floor Fly',1,'Lie on your back holding dumbbells above chest with palms turned downward.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Floor Fly',2,'Lower arms out wide while maintaining internal rotation and slight elbow bend.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Floor Fly',3,'Bring dumbbells back together over chest, squeezing pecs at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Incline Chest Fly',1,'Lay on an incline bench with two dumbbells extended in front of you.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Incline Chest Fly',2,'You should have a slight bend in your elbows and maintain that bend. Your shoulder joint should do all the movement. You should have an overhand grip.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Incline Chest Fly',3,'Bring the dumbbells out to your side. Stop the dumbbells before going behind your body.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Incline Chest Fly',4,'Bring the dumbbells back together at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Rear Delt Fly',1,'Sit with hinged over position, dumbbells in hands, arms slightly bent, internally rotate shoulders.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Rear Delt Fly',2,'Raise dumbbells out to sides, squeeze rear delts.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Rear Delt Fly',3,'Lower weights, repeat for reps.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Single Arm Floor Fly',1,'Lie on your back holding one dumbbell above chest with palm turned downward.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Single Arm Floor Fly',2,'Lower arm out wide while keeping internal rotation and slight elbow bend.'),
('Dumbbell Internally Rotated Single Arm Floor Fly',3,'Bring dumbbell back over chest, squeezing pec at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Kickstand Squat',1,'Stand with feet hip-width apart, one foot slightly behind. Hold dumbbell in a goblet position.'),
('Dumbbell Kickstand Squat',2,'Lower into a squat, keeping weight on front heel.'),
('Dumbbell Kickstand Squat',3,'Return to standing, engaging glutes and core.'),
('Dumbbell Knee Lawnmower Row',1,'Stand with feet staggered and one hand on your knee. Hold a dumbbell in the opposing hand.'),
('Dumbbell Knee Lawnmower Row',2,'Hinge forward at the hips, keeping the back flat, and eyes facing forward. The weight should hang directly below the shoulders.'),
('Dumbbell Knee Lawnmower Row',3,'Start with an overhand grip, as you pull rotate the dumbbell. When your upper arm reaches your side your palm should be facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Kneeling Single Arm Row',1,'Place one hand and one knee on a bench. Make sure you keep a flat back.'),
('Dumbbell Kneeling Single Arm Row',2,'Pull the dumbbell toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Kneeling Single Arm Row',3,'Make sure to avoid any jerking or rotating.'),
('Dumbbell Kneeling Wood Chopper',1,'Start in a kneeling position with your shoulder blades pulled back.'),
('Dumbbell Kneeling Wood Chopper',2,'The dumbbell should begin by one of your hips.'),
('Dumbbell Kneeling Wood Chopper',3,'Rotate at the spine and bring the dumbbell from your hip, 180 degrees around your body. The dumbbell should land at eye level.'),
('Dumbbell Larsen Press',1,'Lie on bench with feet off floor, holding dumbbells above chest.'),
('Dumbbell Larsen Press',2,'Lower dumbbells toward chest while keeping legs elevated and torso stable.'),
('Dumbbell Larsen Press',3,'Press upward, squeezing chest at the top without arching lower back.'),
('Dumbbell Lateral Raise',1,'Stand up straight with dumbbells at either side, palms facing your hips.'),
('Dumbbell Lateral Raise',2,'Raise your arms on either side with a slight bend in your elbow until they are parallel with the floor. Pause at the top of the motion.'),
('Dumbbell Lateral Raise',3,'Slowly return your arms down to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Laying 30 Degree Shrug',1,'Lay sideways on a bench letting your arm hang freely.'),
('Dumbbell Laying 30 Degree Shrug',2,'Pull your shoulder blade and joint toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Curl',1,'Hold the dumbbells with an underhand grip. Seated on a bench.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Curl',2,'Start with the dumbbells pointed toward the ceiling, then lower the dumbbells toward your sides.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Curl',3,'Fully extend your elbows, but don\'t let your upper arm fall behind your torso.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Incline Lateral Raise',1,'Lay on your side on an incline bench. Brace yourself by holding onto the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Incline Lateral Raise',2,'While keeping your elbow mostly extended, raise the dumbbell to the side.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Incline Lateral Raise',3,'The end of the range of motion is when the dumbbell is pointed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Incline Lateral Raise',4,'Make sure you don\'t flex and extend your elbow.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Incline Row',1,'Lay on an incline bench that is between 30-45 degrees high.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Incline Row',2,'Let your arms hang freely. Pull your elbows straight back toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Reverse Fly',1,'With dumbbells in either hand, lay on an incline bench that\'s at about 15-30 degrees.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Reverse Fly',2,'With bent elbows, raise your arms up to shoulder level, pausing at the at the end of the motion.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Reverse Fly',3,'Slowly lower your arms back to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Reverse Fly Internally Rotated',1,'With dumbbells in either hand and an overhand grip, lay on an incline bench that is roughly 15 - 30 degrees high.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Reverse Fly Internally Rotated',2,'With bent elbows, raise your arms up to shoulder level, pausing at the at the end of the motion.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Reverse Fly Internally Rotated',3,'Slowly lower your arms back to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Silverback Shrug',1,'Lay on an incline bench with your arms hanging freely.'),
('Dumbbell Laying Silverback Shrug',2,'Pull your shoulder blades back toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Leg Curl',1,'Lay flat on a bench with a dumbbell between your feet.'),
('Dumbbell Leg Curl',2,'Flex your knees and raise the dumbbell until the soles of your shoes are pointed at the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Leg Extension',1,'Place a dumbbell between your feet. Lean back slightly and hold on to the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Leg Extension',2,'Extend your knees until you feel your quads contract hard.'),
('Dumbbell Long Lever Russian Twist',1,'Start by sitting on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. Hold a dumbbell in both hands with your arms extended straight in front of you.'),
('Dumbbell Long Lever Russian Twist',2,'Twist your torso to the right, bringing the dumbbell towards the ground, then return to the center. Repeat on the left side, twisting to the left and bringing the dumbbell towards the ground.'),
('Dumbbell Long Lever Russian Twist',3,'Continue this twisting motion, alternating sides, for the desired number of repetitions. Keep your core engaged and avoid swinging your arms to generate momentum.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Alternating Overhead Press',1,'Start with two dumbbells near your shoulders with a neutral grip.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Alternating Overhead Press',2,'Press one of the dumbbells toward the ceiling while keeping the other in position.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Alternating Overhead Press',3,'Let the first dumbbell return to its starting position before pressing the other.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Bench Press',1,'Lie on a flat bench, grasp a pair of dumbbells and hold them at shoulder level with your palms facing each other. Keep your elbows bent and close to your body.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Bench Press',2,'Slowly lower the dumbbells to your chest, keeping your elbows bent and close to your body.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Bench Press',3,'Once the dumbbells reach your chest, pause for a moment and then press them back up to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Bench Press',4,'This variation is much easier on the shoulder joints.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral High Incline Bench Press',1,'Set bench to high incline and hold dumbbells with neutral grip at shoulders.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral High Incline Bench Press',2,'Press dumbbells upward until arms extend without locking elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral High Incline Bench Press',3,'Lower slowly to shoulder level and repeat.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Incline Bench Press',1,'Lie on an incline bench, grasp a pair of dumbbells and hold them at shoulder level with your palms facing each other. Keep your elbows bent and close to your body.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Incline Bench Press',2,'Slowly lower the dumbbells to your chest, keeping your elbows bent and close to your body.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Incline Bench Press',3,'Once the dumbbells reach your chest, pause for a moment and then press them back up to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Incline Bench Press',4,'This variation is much easier on the shoulder joints.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Overhead Press',1,'Start with both dumbbells near your shoulders in a neutral grip.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Overhead Press',2,'Press the dumbbells toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Overhead Press',3,'Make sure you don\'t arch your back as you fatigue.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Seated Overhead Press',1,'Sit on an upright bench , grasp a pair of dumbbells and hold them at shoulder level with your palms facing each other. Keep your elbows bent and close to your body.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Seated Overhead Press',2,'Slowly lower the dumbbells to your shoulder joint, keeping your elbows bent and close to your body.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Seated Overhead Press',3,'Once the dumbbells reach your chest, pause for a moment and then press them back up to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Neutral Seated Overhead Press',4,'This variation is much easier on the shoulder joints.'),
('Dumbbell Offset Squat',1,'Hold a dumbbell over one shoulder.'),
('Dumbbell Offset Squat',2,'Initiate the squat by pushing your hips back.'),
('Dumbbell Offset Squat',3,'Avoid doing any twisting. Try to keep your shoulders even.'),
('Dumbbell Overhead Press',1,'Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.'),
('Dumbbell Overhead Press',2,'Bring the dumbbells to your shoulders, with your palms facing forward and your elbows bent.'),
('Dumbbell Overhead Press',3,'From this starting position, extend your arms upwards so that the dumbbells are overhead.'),
('Dumbbell Overhead Press',4,'Make sure to keep your core engaged and your back straight throughout the movement.'),
('Dumbbell Overhead Side Bend',1,'Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell overhead.'),
('Dumbbell Overhead Side Bend',2,'From this starting position, bend to the side as far as you can while keeping your feet planted and your core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Overhead Squat',1,'Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and hold two dumbbells overhead with both hands, using an overhand grip.'),
('Dumbbell Overhead Squat',2,'Begin the squat by bending at the hips and knees, keeping your core tight and the dumbbells balanced overhead.'),
('Dumbbell Overhead Squat',3,'Lower your body as far as you can while keeping the dumbbells overhead, then push back up to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Overhead Squat',4,'Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, making sure to keep your back straight, chest lifted, and the dumbbells stable overhead throughout the entire movement.'),
('Dumbbell Overhead Tricep Extension',1,'Hold a dumbbell overhead.'),
('Dumbbell Overhead Tricep Extension',2,'Flex at the elbows until the dumbbell is behind your head.'),
('Dumbbell Overhead Tricep Extension',3,'Then extend your elbows until the dumbbell is back in the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Pendlay Row',1,'The dumbbells should be placed on the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Pendlay Row',2,'Hinge forward with a flat back and grab the dumbbells.'),
('Dumbbell Pendlay Row',3,'Pull both dumbbells back and your elbows toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Pendlay Row',4,'Return the dumbbells back to the floor softly on each rep.'),
('Dumbbell Plank Pullthrough',1,'Get into a plank position. Either from your knees or toes.'),
('Dumbbell Plank Pullthrough',2,'Start with the DB by your right hand. Reach with your left and pull the dumbbell to your left arm. Then repeat with the right.'),
('Dumbbell Preacher Curl',1,'Sit at preacher bench, hold dumbbells in each hand with arm extended, palm facing up.'),
('Dumbbell Preacher Curl',2,'Curl dumbbells towards shoulder, keeping upper arm stationary and elbows in.'),
('Dumbbell Preacher Curl',3,'Lower dumbbell slowly back to start.'),
('Dumbbell Pullover',1,'Grab a dumbbell and hold with both hands. Point your dumbbell at the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Pullover',2,'Flex at the shoulder joint while keeping your elbows mostly extended.'),
('Dumbbell Pullover',3,'Flex until you feel a stretch in your lats then bring the dumbbell back to the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Pullover Eccentrics',1,'Lie on a bench holding a dumbbell over your shoulder, straight arm.'),
('Dumbbell Pullover Eccentrics',2,'Slowly lower your arm towards the ground (overhead position).'),
('Dumbbell Pullover Eccentrics',3,'Pause in the stretched position.'),
('Dumbbell Pullover Eccentrics',4,'Bend your elbow to return to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Push Press',1,'Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.'),
('Dumbbell Push Press',2,'From this starting position, dip your knees slightly and then quickly extend them as you press the dumbbells upwards.'),
('Dumbbell Push Press',3,'Make sure to keep your core engaged and your back straight throughout the movement.'),
('Dumbbell Push Press',4,'Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.'),
('Dumbbell Quad Stomp',1,'Place your front foot on a low box and take a split stance. Put all of your weight on your front foot.'),
('Dumbbell Quad Stomp',2,'Break at the knees and lower yourself until your calves touch your hamstrings.'),
('Dumbbell Quad Stomp',3,'Push yourself back to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Rear Delt Fly',1,'With dumbbells in either hand, bend your knees with your feet slightly bowed out. Arch your back above your knees, and start with the weights touching in front of your chest.'),
('Dumbbell Rear Delt Fly',2,'With bent elbows, raise your arms up to shoulder level, pausing at the at the end of the motion.'),
('Dumbbell Rear Delt Fly',3,'Slowly lower your arms back to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Rear Delt Row',1,'Hinge forward at the hips while maintaining a flat back. Try to get your torso as close to parallel with the ground as your mobility will allow for.'),
('Dumbbell Rear Delt Row',2,'Let your arms hang in front of you. Pull your elbows back towards the ceiling while flaring your elbows outward.'),
('Dumbbell Renegade Row',1,'Start by getting into a plank position with a dumbbell in each hand. Your feet should be shoulder-width apart and your hands should be placed on the dumbbells, with your palms facing each other.'),
('Dumbbell Renegade Row',2,'From this starting position, row one dumbbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body and your core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Renegade Row',3,'Slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position, and repeat on the other side.'),
('Dumbbell Renegade Row',4,'Make sure to keep your body straight and your hips level throughout the movement.'),
('Dumbbell Reverse Curl',1,'Grab the dumbbells with a pronated (overhand) grip. You can do this exercise thumbless if it\'s more comfortable on your wrists.'),
('Dumbbell Reverse Curl',2,'Flex at the elbows until your biceps touch your forearms. Try not to let your elbows flair outward.'),
('Dumbbell Reverse Grip Bench Press',1,'Lay flat on the bench with your feet on the ground. With straight arms unrack the bar with a reverse grip.'),
('Dumbbell Reverse Grip Bench Press',2,'Lower the dumbbells to your lower chest.'),
('Dumbbell Reverse Grip Bench Press',3,'Raise the bar until you\'ve locked your elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Rolling Tricep Extension',1,'Lay flat on a bench with two dumbbells pointed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Rolling Tricep Extension',2,'Break at the elbows until your forearms touch your biceps, then flex at the shoulder joint bringing your upper arms to the sides of your head.'),
('Dumbbell Rolling Tricep Extension',3,'Bring your elbows back up until they are pointed at the ceiling, then extend your elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Romanian Deadlift',1,'Stand with a shoulder width stance. Push your butt back while leaving your knees MOSTLY extended.'),
('Dumbbell Romanian Deadlift',2,'You should feel a stretch in your hamstrings. When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward to complete the rep.'),
('Dumbbell Romanian Deadlift',3,'Do not push your hips all the way forward. This will hyperextend your spine. Just go to a normal standing position.'),
('Dumbbell Row Bilateral',1,'Grab both dumbbells and hinge forward at the hips. Make sure you keep a flat back.'),
('Dumbbell Row Bilateral',2,'The closer your torso is to parallel with the ground the longer the range of motion will be at your shoulder. The better the results you\'ll get from the exercise.'),
('Dumbbell Row Bilateral',3,'Let your arms hang freely, and then pull your elbow joint straight back toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Row Unilateral',1,'Brace your off arm against something stable (bench, box). Stagger your stance so your leg on the side of your working arm is back.'),
('Dumbbell Row Unilateral',2,'Try to get your torso to parallel with the ground. That will extend your range of motion.'),
('Dumbbell Row Unilateral',3,'Let your arm hang freely and then pull your elbow back. Imagine you\'ve got a tennis ball in your armpit and squeeze it each rep.'),
('Dumbbell Russian Twist',1,'Sit on the floor and flex your knees and hips to a 90 degree angle.'),
('Dumbbell Russian Twist',2,'Your feet should be hovering off the ground. (If that\'s too hard start with heels on the floor)'),
('Dumbbell Russian Twist',3,'Rotate your upper spine to engage your obliques.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Arnold Press',1,'Begin seated on an upright bench with your palms facing you.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Arnold Press',2,'Begin pressing toward the ceiling. As you press, rotate your palms.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Arnold Press',3,'As you extend your elbows fully your palms should be facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Calf Raise',1,'Start by sitting on a bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and a dumbbell in each hand placed on each leg.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Calf Raise',2,'From this starting position, raise your heels as high as you can by pushing up through your toes.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Calf Raise',3,'Slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Curl',1,'Sit tall holding dumbbells at your sides with palms facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Curl',2,'Curl both dumbbells toward your shoulders, keeping elbows tight to torso.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Curl',3,'Squeeze biceps, then lower slowly to full extension.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Full Lateral Raise',1,'Sit tall holding dumbbells at sides with slight bend in elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Full Lateral Raise',2,'Raise arms outward until arms go overhead.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Full Lateral Raise',3,'Lower under control, maintaining constant tension on delts.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Hammer Curl',1,'Sit tall holding dumbbells at your sides with palms facing inward.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Hammer Curl',2,'Curl dumbbells toward shoulders while maintaining neutral grip throughout.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Hammer Curl',3,'Squeeze biceps, then lower slowly to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Overhead Press',1,'Sit on a bench with back support. Raise the dumbbells to shoulder height with your palms forward.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Overhead Press',2,'Raise the dumbbells upwards and pause at the contracted position.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Overhead Press',3,'Lower the weights back to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Overhead Tricep Extension',1,'Sit on the bench and hold a dumbbell with both hands. Raise the dumbbell overhead at arms length, holding the weight up with the palms of your hands.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Overhead Tricep Extension',2,'Keep your elbows in while you lower the weight behind your head, your upper arms stationary.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Overhead Tricep Extension',3,'Raise the weight back to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Rear Delt Fly',1,'With dumbbells in either hand, bend your knees with your feet slightly bowed out. Arch your back above your knees, and start with the weights touching in front of your chest.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Rear Delt Fly',2,'With bent elbows, raise your arms up to shoulder level, pausing at the at the end of the motion.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Rear Delt Fly',3,'Slowly lower your arms back to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Rear Delt Row',1,'Sit on a bench. Put your chest in your lap. Try to get your torso as close to parallel with the ground as your mobility will allow for.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Rear Delt Row',2,'Let your arms hang in front of you. Pull your elbows back towards the ceiling while flaring your elbows outward.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Reverse Curl',1,'Sit tall holding dumbbells at your sides with palms facing downward.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Reverse Curl',2,'Curl dumbbells toward your shoulders, keeping wrists stable and elbows tucked.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Reverse Curl',3,'Lower slowly to full extension, maintaining control throughout.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Shrug',1,'Sit on a bench with dumbbells in both hands, palms facing your body, back straight.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Shrug',2,'Elevate your shoulders and hold the contracted position at the apex of the motion.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Shrug',3,'Slowly lower your shoulders back to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Arnold Press',1,'Start by sitting on an incline bench and holding a dumbbell in one hand.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Arnold Press',2,'Bring the dumbbell to your shoulder, with your palm facing you and your elbow bent.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Arnold Press',3,'From this starting position, extend your arm upwards so that the dumbbell is directly above your head.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Arnold Press',4,'As you extend your arm, rotate your palm to face away from your body.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Curl',1,'Sit tall holding dumbbell at your sides with palm facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Curl',2,'Curl the dumbbell toward your shoulder, keeping elbow tight to torso.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Curl',3,'Squeeze bicep, then lower slowly to full extension.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Curl',4,'Sit tall holding dumbbell at your sides with palm facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Curl',5,'Curl the dumbbell toward your shoulder, keeping elbow tight to torso.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Curl',6,'Squeeze bicep, then lower slowly to full extension.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Full Lateral Raise',1,'Sit tall holding one dumbbell at your side with slight bend in elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Full Lateral Raise',2,'Raise arm outward until arms go overhead.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Full Lateral Raise',3,'Lower under control, maintaining constant tension on delts.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Hammer Curl',1,'Sit tall holding one dumbbell at your side with palm facing inward.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Hammer Curl',2,'Curl dumbbell toward shoulder while keeping elbow tight to your torso.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Hammer Curl',3,'Squeeze bicep, then lower slowly to full extension.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Lateral Raise',1,'Sit tall with one dumbbell at your side, palm facing inward.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Lateral Raise',2,'Lift arm outward until shoulder height, keeping elbow slightly bent.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Lateral Raise',3,'Lower smoothly and repeat, keeping torso still.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Reverse Curl',1,'Sit tall holding one dumbbell at your side with palm facing downward.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Reverse Curl',2,'Curl dumbbell toward shoulder, keeping wrist stable and elbow tucked.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Reverse Curl',3,'Lower slowly to full extension while maintaining control.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Zottman Curl',1,'Sit tall holding dumbbell at your side with palm facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Zottman Curl',2,'Curl dumbbell up, then rotate palm downward at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Single Arm Zottman Curl',3,'Lower slowly with palm down, controlling the entire descent.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Y Press',1,'Sit on an upright bench , grasp a pair of dumbbells and hold them at shoulder level with your palms facing each other. Keep your elbows bent and close to your body.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Y Press',2,'Press the dumbbells outward into a y shape.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Zottman Curl',1,'Sit tall holding dumbbells at sides with palms facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Zottman Curl',2,'Curl dumbbells up, then rotate palms downward at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Seated Zottman Curl',3,'Lower slowly with palms down, controlling the entire descent.'),
('Dumbbell Service Exercise',1,'Stand up straight and hold a dumbbell in one arm. Perform a bicep curl across your body'),
('Dumbbell Service Exercise',2,'Bring the dumbbell to your shoulder and rotate palm and elbow out.'),
('Dumbbell Service Exercise',3,'Point the elbow towards the ceiling while the dumbbell remains just over the shoulder.'),
('Dumbbell Service Exercise',4,'Extend your elbow to raise the dumbbell over your head. Start lowering your arm to your side as you turn the palm to face down'),
('Dumbbell Shoulder Extension',1,'Start by hinging over with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.'),
('Dumbbell Shoulder Extension',2,'Bring the dumbbells to your sides, with your palms facing forward and your elbows slightly bent.'),
('Dumbbell Shoulder Extension',3,'Make sure to keep your core engaged and your back straight throughout the movement.'),
('Dumbbell Shoulder External Rotation',1,'Sit on a bench with one foot on the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Shoulder External Rotation',2,'Place the elbow on the inside of your elbow and use it for leverage.'),
('Dumbbell Shoulder External Rotation',3,'Point your fist toward the wall andthen toward the ceiling. Rotating a total of 90 degrees.'),
('Dumbbell Shrug',1,'Stand tall with two dumbbells. Pull your shoulder blades up. Give a one second squeeze at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Side Bend',1,'Stand with feet hip-width apart and place your right hand on the right hip.'),
('Dumbbell Side Bend',2,'Hold a dumbbell with the left hand. Bend at the hips to the side.'),
('Dumbbell Side Bend',3,'Make sure you don\'t start to lean forward to try and force a longer range of motion.'),
('Dumbbell Side Plank Up Down',1,'Start by lying on your side with your feet stacked on top of each other and a dumbbell on your hip.'),
('Dumbbell Side Plank Up Down',2,'Place your bottom elbow on the ground beneath your shoulder and engage your core to raise your hips off the ground.'),
('Dumbbell Side Plank Up Down',3,'Your hips will do all the moving. Think, \"hips up, hips down.\"'),
('Dumbbell Side Step Up',1,'Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart, with a dumbbell in your hands. Your feet should be slightly pointed outward, and your shoulders should be down and relaxed.'),
('Dumbbell Side Step Up',2,'Place a step or box beside you, and step up onto it with one foot. Your other foot should remain on the ground.'),
('Dumbbell Side Step Up',3,'Push off your grounded foot, raising your body up onto the step.'),
('Dumbbell Side Step Up',4,'Step back down with the same foot, returning to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Silverback Shrug',1,'Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding dumbbells with both hands in front just past shoulder width.'),
('Dumbbell Silverback Shrug',2,'Bend forward at the hips with a slight bend in your knees, keeping your back straight.'),
('Dumbbell Silverback Shrug',3,'Engage your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to touch them together.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Arnold Press',1,'Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in one hand.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Arnold Press',2,'Bring the dumbbell to your shoulder, with your palm facing you and your elbow bent.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Arnold Press',3,'From this starting position, extend your arm upwards so that the dumbbell is directly above your head.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Arnold Press',4,'As you extend your arm, rotate your palm to face away from your body.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Flat Curl',1,'Lay off the side of a bench with the back of your working arm pressed into the side of the bench. Keep your hips all the way up.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Flat Curl',2,'Fully extend your elbow and feel a stretch through your bicep, then curl.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Flat Curl',3,'Stop before the dumbbell is pointed at the ceiling to keep tension on your biceps.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Hammer Flat Curl',1,'Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips pushed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Hammer Flat Curl',2,'Use a hammer grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Hammer Incline Curl',1,'Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips down.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Hammer Incline Curl',2,'Take a neutral grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Incline Curl',1,'Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Incline Curl',2,'Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Reverse Flat Curl',1,'Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips pushed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Reverse Flat Curl',2,'Use an overhand grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Reverse Incline Curl',1,'Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Reverse Incline Curl',2,'Take an overhand grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Wrist Curl',1,'Drape one arm over a bench while holding a dumbbell. Point your palm toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Wrist Curl',2,'Extend and curl your wrist against resistance.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Chest Press',1,'Lie on bench holding one dumbbell above chest with arm extended.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Chest Press',2,'Lower dumbbell toward chest while keeping torso stable and level.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Chest Press',3,'Press upward, squeezing chest at the top without twisting.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Clean And Press',1,'Hold dumbbell between legs, hinge slightly, and pull explosively to shoulder.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Clean And Press',2,'Catch dumbbell at shoulder height with knees slightly bent.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Clean And Press',3,'Press overhead until arm fully extends, then lower under control.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Floor Fly',1,'Lie on your back holding one dumbbell above chest with slight elbow bend.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Floor Fly',2,'Lower arm out wide until elbow lightly touches the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Floor Fly',3,'Bring dumbbell back over chest, squeezing pec at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up',1,'Stand in front of a step or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold one dumbbell on your shoulder with an overhand grip.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up',2,'Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing off your foot to raise your body up onto the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up',3,'Bring your left foot up onto the bench and stand up straight, keeping the barbell at your shoulders.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up',4,'Step back down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, to return to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up Knee Drive',1,'Hold one dumbbell in front rack position and place opposite foot on platform.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up Knee Drive',2,'Drive through front heel to step up while keeping chest tall and core tight.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up Knee Drive',3,'Lift trailing knee high at the top, then step down slowly with control.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Hammer Curl',1,'Stand or sit tall holding dumbbell at your side with palm facing inward.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Hammer Curl',2,'Curl dumbbell toward shoulder while keeping elbow tight to torso.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Hammer Curl',3,'Squeeze bicep, then lower slowly to full extension under control.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Hang Clean And Press',1,'Hold dumbbell in one hand at thigh level with slight knee bend.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Hang Clean And Press',2,'Pull dumbbell upward explosively to shoulder, catching it smoothly.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Hang Clean And Press',3,'Press overhead, fully extending arm, then return to start position.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm High Incline Chest Press',1,'Sit on high incline bench holding dumbbell at shoulder with arm bent.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm High Incline Chest Press',2,'Press dumbbell upward and slightly inward until arm fully extends.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm High Incline Chest Press',3,'Lower slowly to starting position, keeping torso stable and controlled.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Chest Press',1,'Lay flat on the bench with your feet on the ground. With straight arms unrack the bar.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Chest Press',2,'Lower the bar to your mid chest'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Chest Press',3,'Raise the bar until you\'ve locked your elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Curl',1,'Hold a dumbbell with an underhand grip. Seated on an incline bench.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Curl',2,'Slowly lift the dumbbell up to chest height'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Curl',3,'Return to starting position and repeat.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Hammer Curl',1,'Sit on incline bench holding one dumbbell with a neutral grip with arm hanging straight down.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Hammer Curl',2,'Curl dumbbell toward shoulder without moving upper arm.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Hammer Curl',3,'Squeeze bicep, then lower slowly to full stretch.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Reverse Curl',1,'Lay on an incline bench.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Reverse Curl',2,'Grab a dumbbell with a pronated (overhand) grip. You can do this exercise thumbless if it\'s more comfortable on your wrists.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Reverse Curl',3,'Flex at the elbows until your bicep touches your forearm. Try not to let your elbow flair outward.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Skullcrusher',1,'Set bench to incline and hold dumbbell above chest with palmsfacing in.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Skullcrusher',2,'Bend elbow to lower dumbbell toward forehead under control.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Skullcrusher',3,'Extend arm fully, squeezing tricep at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Twisting Curl',1,'Sit on incline bench holding dumbbell at side, palm facing inward.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Incline Twisting Curl',2,'Curl dumbbell while twisting palm toward shoulder.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Larsen Press',1,'Lie on bench with feet off floor, holding one dumbbell above chest.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Larsen Press',2,'Lower dumbbell toward chest while keeping core tight and legs raised.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Larsen Press',3,'Press upward, squeezing chest at the top without twisting torso.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Neutral Overhead Press',1,'Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in one hand.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Neutral Overhead Press',2,'Bring the dumbbell to your shoulder, with your palm facing your body and your elbow bent.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Neutral Overhead Press',3,'From this starting position, press the dumbbell upwards so that it is directly above your shoulder.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Press',1,'Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in one hand.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Press',2,'Bring the dumbbell to your shoulder, with your palm facing forward and your elbow bent.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Press',3,'From this starting position, extend your arm upwards so that the dumbbell is overhead.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Press',4,'Make sure to keep your core engaged and your back straight throughout the movement.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Tricep Extension',1,'Stand tall with a single dumbbell extended overhead.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Tricep Extension',2,'Flex at the elbow letting the dumbbell travel behind your body.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Tricep Extension',3,'Try not to let your elbow flare outward.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Pendlay Row',1,'Stand with feet hip-width, hinge forward until torso is nearly parallel to floor.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Pendlay Row',2,'Grab dumbbell from floor with straight arm, keeping back flat and core braced.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Pendlay Row',3,'Pull elbow straight up to ribs, then lower dumbbell fully back to the floor each rep.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Preacher Curl',1,'Start with a with a dumbbell in one hand and your elbow resting on the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Preacher Curl',2,'From this starting position, curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary on the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Press',1,'Start by laying on a bench with two dumbbells.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Press',2,'Position the dumbbell above your chest with your elbow bent and shoulder level.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Press',3,'Slowly lower the dumbbell towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body and your core engaged while the other dumbbell remains pointed toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Press',4,'Once the dumbbell reaches your side, pause for a moment and then press the weight back up to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Press',5,'Repeat for the desired number of repetitions before switching to your other arm.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Pullover',1,'Lie on bench holding one dumbbell above chest with slight elbow bend.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Pullover',2,'Lower dumbbell in an arc behind head until you feel a deep stretch.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Pullover',3,'Pull dumbbell back over chest using lats and triceps, keeping movement controlled.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Push Press',1,'Hold dumbbell at shoulder height, feet shoulder-width apart.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Push Press',2,'Dip slightly at knees, then drive upward, pressing dumbbell overhead.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Push Press',3,'Lock out arm briefly, then lower dumbbell under control.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Rear Delt Row',1,'Hinge at hips with back flat, holding dumbbell under shoulder with arm extended.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Rear Delt Row',2,'Pull elbow out and back at a wide angle, targeting rear delt.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Rear Delt Row',3,'Squeeze at the top, then lower slowly to full stretch.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Row',1,'Start by standing in front of a flat bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in one hand.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Row',2,'Place your other hand on the bench for support, and bend at the waist so that your chest is parallel to the ground.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Row',3,'From this starting position, row the dumbbell up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blade together as you do so.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Row',4,'Make sure to keep your elbow close to your body and your core engaged throughout the movement.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Row Knee',1,'Start by placing your elbow on one knee.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Row Knee',2,'Hold a dumbbell in your other hand, with your palm facing inwards towards your body.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Row Knee',3,'From this starting position, row the dumbbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body and your core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Seated Hammer Curl',1,'Sit tall holding one dumbbell at your side with palm facing inward.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Seated Hammer Curl',2,'Curl dumbbell toward shoulder while keeping elbow tight to your torso.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Seated Hammer Curl',3,'Squeeze bicep, then lower slowly to full extension under control.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Seated Overhead Tricep Extension',1,'Sit tall holding dumbbell overhead with one hand, arm fully extended.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Seated Overhead Tricep Extension',2,'Lower dumbbell behind head by bending elbow slowly.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Seated Overhead Tricep Extension',3,'Extend arm back up, squeezing triceps at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Shoulder Extension',1,'Hold dumbbells at your sides with straight arms and palms neutral.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Shoulder Extension',2,'Move arm backward until you feel lats and rear delts engage.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Shoulder Extension',3,'Lower slowly to starting position under full control.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Skullcrusher',1,'Lie on flat bench holding one dumbbell above shoulder, palm facing in.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Skullcrusher',2,'Bend elbow to lower dumbbell beside head without moving upper arm.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Skullcrusher',3,'Extend arm fully, contracting triceps at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Spider Curl',1,'Lay on an incline or preacher curl bench.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Spider Curl',2,'Let your arms hang freely off the edge of the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Spider Curl',3,'Fully flex your elbow and fully extend your elbow on each rep.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Step Up',1,'Stand in front of a step or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold one dumbbell on your side with a neutral grip.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Step Up',2,'Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing off your foot to raise your body up onto the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Step Up',3,'Bring your left foot up onto the bench and stand up straight, keeping the barbell at your shoulders.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Step Up',4,'Step back down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, to return to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Step Up Knee Drive',1,'Hold one dumbbell at your side and place opposite foot firmly on platform.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Step Up Knee Drive',2,'Drive through front heel to step up, keeping torso tall and core tight.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Step Up Knee Drive',3,'Lift trailing knee high at the top, then step down slowly with control.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Thruster',1,'Hold dumbbell at shoulder height with feet shoulder-width apart.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Thruster',2,'Squat down, then drive upward, pressing dumbbell overhead in one motion.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Thruster',3,'Lower dumbbell as you descend into next rep smoothly.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Tricep Guilotine Press',1,'Lie on bench holding dumbbell above upper chest with palm facing in.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Tricep Guilotine Press',2,'Lower dumbbell toward neck or upper chest by bending elbow forward.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Tricep Guilotine Press',3,'Extend arm fully, squeezing triceps at the top while keeping shoulder stable.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Upright Row',1,'Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand with an overhand grip.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Upright Row',2,'Keep your back straight and chest lifted, engage your core to maintain balance.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Upright Row',3,'Begin the movement by lifting the dumbbell straight up towards your chin, keeping your elbow close to your body and the weight in line with your shoulder.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Upright Row',4,'Continue to lift the weight until it reaches the chin or neck level, keeping the elbow high and close to the body.'),
('Dumbbell Single Arm Upright Row',5,'Lower the weight back down to the starting position with control.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Calf Raise',1,'Standing straight with a dumbbell in one hand, lift the same foot as the side without the dumbbell off the floor. Hold onto something for balance.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Calf Raise',2,'Raise your heel upwards while keeping your knees stationary.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Calf Raise',3,'Pause when your heels are fully extended and then slowly return to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Heels Elevated Hip Thrust',1,'Start by lying on a bench with your foot on a plate or low box and a dumbbell on your hips.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Heels Elevated Hip Thrust',2,'Lift one leg off the ground and engage your glutes to raise your hips up towards the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Heels Elevated Hip Thrust',3,'From this starting position, slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Single Arm Deadlift',1,'Start by standing on one leg with a dumbbell in one hand.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Single Arm Deadlift',2,'Slowly bend at the hips and lower the dumbbell towards the ground while extending your free leg behind you.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Single Arm Deadlift',3,'Keep your core engaged and your back straight as you lower the weight.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Single Arm Deadlift',4,'Once the dumbbell is close to the ground, push through your heel to return to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Stiff Leg Deadlift',1,'Start by standing on one leg with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding two dumbbells.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Stiff Leg Deadlift',2,'From this starting position, hinge at the hips to lower the dumbbell towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Stiff Leg Deadlift',3,'Once you feel a stretch in your hamstring, slowly return to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Single Leg Stiff Leg Deadlift',4,'Make sure to keep your standing leg slightly bent and avoid rounding your back as you lower the dumbbell.'),
('Dumbbell Situp',1,'Lay flat on the ground with your spine neutral. Extend you arms so your fists are pointed at the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Situp',2,'Sit-up by flexing your abs. Continue to reach for the ceiling for the entire rep.'),
('Dumbbell Six Way Lateral Raise',1,'Perform a front raise, then bring dumbbells out to your side, then raise the dumbbells over head.'),
('Dumbbell Skullcrusher',1,'Lay flat on the floor or a bench with your fists extended to the ceiling and a neutral grip.'),
('Dumbbell Skullcrusher',2,'Break at the elbows until your fists are by your temples. Then extend your elbows and flex your triceps at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Somersault Squat',1,'Start in a deep squat holding a dumbbell between your thighs.'),
('Dumbbell Somersault Squat',2,'Extend your knees until mostly extended without extending the hips.'),
('Dumbbell Spider Curl',1,'Start by placing your forearms on a flat bench and holding a dumbbell in each hand.'),
('Dumbbell Spider Curl',2,'From this starting position, curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body and your core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Spider Curl',3,'Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.'),
('Dumbbell Spinal Jefferson Curl',1,'Stand tall holding dumbbells in front of thighs with straight arms.'),
('Dumbbell Spinal Jefferson Curl',2,'Slowly roll down through spine, reaching dumbbells toward feet.'),
('Dumbbell Spinal Jefferson Curl',3,'Reverse motion, rolling back up one vertebra at a time.'),
('Dumbbell Squeeze Press',1,'Lay flat on a bench with two dumbbells pressed to one another.'),
('Dumbbell Squeeze Press',2,'Break at the elbows and keep your elbows tucked as you bring the dumbbells to your chest.'),
('Dumbbell Squeeze Press',3,'Continue to press the dumbbells into one another throughout the rep.'),
('Dumbbell Squeeze Press',4,'Once the dumbbells reach your chest, press back toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Stability Ball Wall Squat',1,'Place a stability ball against a wall at about hip height.'),
('Dumbbell Stability Ball Wall Squat',2,'Hold two dumbbells in each hand.'),
('Dumbbell Stability Ball Wall Squat',3,'Break at the hips and knees until you hit parallel or just below, then squat back up.'),
('Dumbbell Staggered Deadlift',1,'Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.'),
('Dumbbell Staggered Deadlift',2,'Place one foot slightly behind the other, with the heel of your back foot elevated on a step or weight plate.'),
('Dumbbell Staggered Deadlift',3,'From this starting position, bend at the hips and knees to lower the dumbbells towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.'),
('Dumbbell Staggered Deadlift',4,'Once the dumbbells are below your knees, drive through your heels to stand back up to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Staggered Waiters Bow',1,'Set up a bar at mid way up your quad. Place the working leg against the bar.'),
('Dumbbell Staggered Waiters Bow',2,'Place one foot behind. You should only be on your toes on that back foot. Your front foot should be planted flat the entire time.'),
('Dumbbell Staggered Waiters Bow',3,'Bend your back knee and push your hips back. Look for a stretch in your front hamstring.'),
('Dumbbell Staggered Waiters Bow',4,'When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward again until you\'re back in a standing position.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Bayesian Lateral Raise',1,'Stand tall on lean slightly forward.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Bayesian Lateral Raise',2,'Lateral raise your arms straight out to the side until your arms are about parallel with the ground.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Curl',1,'Stand tall holding one dumbbell at your side, palm facing forward.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Curl',2,'Curl dumbbell toward shoulder, keeping elbow close to your torso.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Curl',3,'Squeeze bicep, then lower slowly to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Hammer Curl',1,'Hold dumbbell at side with palm facing inward, elbow tight to body.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Hammer Curl',2,'Curl dumbbell upward while maintaining neutral grip throughout.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Hammer Curl',3,'Lower under control, keeping tension on biceps and forearm.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Reverse Curl',1,'Hold dumbbell with palm facing down and arm straight by your side.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Reverse Curl',2,'Curl dumbbell toward shoulder, leading with back of hand.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Reverse Curl',3,'Lower slowly to starting position, keeping wrist stable.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Twisting Curl',1,'Hold dumbbell with palm facing inward and arm extended fully.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Twisting Curl',2,'Curl upward while rotating palm to face shoulder at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Twisting Curl',3,'Squeeze bicep, then lower dumbbell, rotating back to start.'),
('Dumbbell Step Up',1,'Stand in front of a step or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold two dumbbells on your side with a neutral grip.'),
('Dumbbell Step Up',2,'Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing off your foot to raise your body up onto the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Step Up',3,'Bring your left foot up onto the bench and stand up straight, keeping the barbell at your shoulders.'),
('Dumbbell Step Up',4,'Step back down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, to return to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Step Up Knee Drive',1,'Hold dumbbells at your sides and place one foot firmly on platform.'),
('Dumbbell Step Up Knee Drive',2,'Drive through front heel to step up, keeping torso tall and balanced.'),
('Dumbbell Step Up Knee Drive',3,'Lift trailing knee high at the top, then step down slowly with control.'),
('Dumbbell Suitcase Crunch',1,'Lay flat on the ground with a dumbbell. Point the soles of your shoes at the ceiling as well as the dumbbell.'),
('Dumbbell Suitcase Crunch',2,'Reach for your feet with the dumbbell before bringing your spine back to the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Sumo Squat',1,'Start by standing with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.'),
('Dumbbell Sumo Squat',2,'Place the dumbbells on the ground between your feet.'),
('Dumbbell Sumo Squat',3,'From this starting position, bend your knees and lower your body down into a squat.'),
('Dumbbell Sumo Squat',4,'Make sure to keep your core engaged and your back straight throughout the movement.'),
('Dumbbell Superman',1,'Lay flat on the ground on your stomach with your arms extended overhead. Hold a dumbbell with a neutral grip.'),
('Dumbbell Superman',2,'Lift your legs and chest off the ground simultaneously and hold for a 1 count at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Superman',3,'Relax your lower back and lower your legs and chest back to the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Superman Hold',1,'Lie face down on a mat.'),
('Dumbbell Superman Hold',2,'Hold dumbbells out in front'),
('Dumbbell Superman Hold',3,'Lift arms and legs simultaneously, squeezing lower back.'),
('Dumbbell Supinated Row',1,'Grab both dumbbells and hinge forward at the hips. Make sure you keep a flat back.'),
('Dumbbell Supinated Row',2,'The closer your torso is to parallel with the ground the longer the range of motion will be at your shoulder. The better the results you\'ll get from the exercise.'),
('Dumbbell Supinated Row',3,'Let your arms hang freely, maintain an underhand grip, and then pull your elbow joint straight back toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Swing',1,'Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in both hands.'),
('Dumbbell Swing',2,'Bend your knees slightly and hinge at the hips to swing the dumbbell between your legs.'),
('Dumbbell Swing',3,'From this starting position, explosively extend your hips and swing the dumbbell up to chest height.'),
('Dumbbell Swing',4,'Allow the momentum of the swing to carry the dumbbell back down between your legs, and then repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.'),
('Dumbbell Swing Lunge',1,'Stand with your feet shoulder-width. Dumbbells at your side.'),
('Dumbbell Swing Lunge',2,'Step forward with your right foot and bend both knees to lower your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground.'),
('Dumbbell Swing Lunge',3,'Push off your right foot to return to the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Swing Lunge',4,'Step back with the same leg until the back knee taps the floor.'),
('Dumbbell Tate Press',1,'Lay flat on a bench with two dumbbells extended toward the ceiling.'),
('Dumbbell Tate Press',2,'Maintain an overhand grip. Flex at the elbows.'),
('Dumbbell Tate Press',3,'The dumbbells will land on your upper chest/clavicle.'),
('Dumbbell Tate Press',4,'Extend your elbows bringing the dumbbells back into their starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Tate Press',5,'*Named after Dave Tate*'),
('Dumbbell Thruster',1,'Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.'),
('Dumbbell Thruster',2,'Bring the dumbbells to your shoulders, with your palms facing inward and your elbows bent.'),
('Dumbbell Thruster',3,'From this starting position, dip your knees slightly and then quickly extend them as you press the dumbbells upwards.'),
('Dumbbell Thruster',4,'As you press the dumbbells upwards, also push your hips forward to help generate additional power.'),
('Dumbbell Thruster',5,'Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.'),
('Dumbbell Tricep Guillotine Press',1,'Lay flat on a bench.'),
('Dumbbell Tricep Guillotine Press',2,'Push your elbows forward until your biceps touch your forearms. Then extend your elbows until back at the starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Tricep Kickback',1,'Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in one hand.'),
('Dumbbell Tricep Kickback',2,'Bend at the waist and place your opposite hand on your knee for support.'),
('Dumbbell Tricep Kickback',3,'From this starting position, extend your arm backwards so that the dumbbell is behind your body.'),
('Dumbbell Tricep Kickback',4,'Make sure to keep your elbow close to your body and your core engaged throughout the movement.'),
('Dumbbell Twisting Curl',1,'Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.'),
('Dumbbell Twisting Curl',2,'Bring the dumbbells to your sides, with your palms facing inward and your elbows bent.'),
('Dumbbell Twisting Curl',3,'From this starting position, curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders while rotating your wrists so that your palms face your shoulders at the top of the movement.'),
('Dumbbell Upright Row',1,'Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding 2 dumbbells in each hand.'),
('Dumbbell Upright Row',2,'Keep your back straight and chest lifted, engage your core to maintain balance.'),
('Dumbbell Upright Row',3,'Begin the movement by lifting the dumbbells straight up towards your chin, keeping your elbow close to your body and the weight in line with your shoulder.'),
('Dumbbell Upright Row',4,'Continue to lift the weight until it reaches the chin or neck level, keeping the elbow high and close to the body.'),
('Dumbbell Waiters Bow',1,'Place a barbell at about midway up your thigh. Press your quads into the barbell.'),
('Dumbbell Waiters Bow',2,'Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.'),
('Dumbbell Waiters Bow',3,'When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you\'re back in a standing position.'),
('Dumbbell Weighted Chin Ups',1,'Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you). Use a dip belt and the let the weight hang between your legs.'),
('Dumbbell Weighted Chin Ups',2,'With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.'),
('Dumbbell Weighted Chin Ups',3,'Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.'),
('Dumbbell Weighted Dip',1,'Use a dip belt to attach a dumbbell to yourself. Grip bars with arms straight, shoulders above hands. Keep legs straight or bent.'),
('Dumbbell Weighted Dip',2,'Lower slowly until elbows are at 90 degrees.'),
('Dumbbell Weighted Dip',3,'Push back up to start position, extending arms fully.'),
('Dumbbell Weighted Pull Ups',1,'Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, arms and shoulders fully extended.'),
('Dumbbell Weighted Pull Ups',2,'Pull your body up until your chin is above the bar.'),
('Dumbbell Weighted Pull Ups',3,'Lower your body back to starting position.'),
('Dumbbell Wood Chopper',1,'Stand with a shoulder width stance. Begin with the dumbbell near one of your quads.'),
('Dumbbell Wood Chopper',2,'Rotate at your upper spine to engage the obliques.'),
('Dumbbell Wood Chopper',3,'You can pivot your back foot to keep from generating too much torque at the knee.'),
('Dumbbell Wrist Curl',1,'Grip the dumbbell with your palm facing upwards with your forearm rested against the bench.'),
('Dumbbell Wrist Curl',2,'Slowly curl your wrist upwards in a semicircular motion.'),
('Dumbbell Wrist Curl',3,'Return to starting position and repeat.'),
('Dumbbell Wrist Extension',1,'Grab two dumbbells with an overhand grip and lay your forearms across your knees.'),
('Dumbbell Wrist Extension',2,'Let your wrists flex fully, then extend your wrists.'),
('Dumbbell Wrist Supinations Pronations',1,'Sit by a bench or table and lean your arm on it.'),
('Dumbbell Wrist Supinations Pronations',2,'Hold a dumbbell/weight/lever on one end.'),
('Dumbbell Wrist Supinations Pronations',3,'Rotate the wrist so the palm faces down and up in succession.'),
('Dumbbell Y Press',1,'Stand tall, grasp a pair of dumbbells and hold them at shoulder level with your palms facing each other. Keep your elbows bent and close to your body.'),
('Dumbbell Y Press',2,'Press the dumbbells outward into a y shape.'),
('Dumbbell Zottman Curl',1,'Hold dumbbells at sides, palms facing forward, elbows tight to body.'),
('Dumbbell Zottman Curl',2,'Curl both dumbbells up, then rotate palms downward at the top.'),
('Dumbbell Zottman Curl',3,'Lower slowly with palms facing the floor, controlling the descent.'),
('Eagle Arms Chin Into Chest',1,'Sit cross-legged on the floor and bring your arms out to the sides at shoulder height.'),
('Eagle Arms Chin Into Chest',2,'Cross your right arm over your left, bending both elbows so that your forearms are parallel to the floor.'),
('Eagle Arms Chin Into Chest',3,'Lift your elbows towards the ceiling and bring your hands together, then drop your chin towards your chest.'),
('Eagle Arms Chin Into Chest',4,'Hold for a few breaths, then release your arms and repeat on the other side.'),
('Easy Pose Neck Stretch',1,'Begin by sitting cross-legged on the floor.'),
('Easy Pose Neck Stretch',2,'Slowly drop your chin towards your chest, feeling a stretch in the back of your neck.'),
('Easy Pose Neck Stretch',3,'Inhale and lift your head up, then exhale and drop your right ear towards your right shoulder.'),
('Easy Pose Neck Stretch',4,'Hold for a few breaths, then switch sides and repeat the stretch.'),
('Eccentric Dragonflag',1,'Perform a reverse crunch and then kick your legs up toward the ceiling.'),
('Eccentric Dragonflag',2,'With your hips and knees extended, lower yourself slowly back to the start position.'),
('Elbow Plank Mountain Climber',1,'Begin in an elbow plank position with your core engaged.'),
('Elbow Plank Mountain Climber',2,'Bring your right knee towards your right elbow.'),
('Elbow Plank Mountain Climber',3,'Return to plank, then switch legs quickly. Repeat.'),
('Elbow Side Plank',1,'Press your elbow into the floor.'),
('Elbow Side Plank',2,'Pick your hips up off the ground and maintain this position for the allotted amount of time.'),
('Elbow Side Plank',3,'Make sure you don\'t let your chest fall forward or backward.'),
('Elevated Pike Press',1,'Use a bench or an object to elevate your feet.'),
('Elevated Pike Press',2,'Lower your head towards the floor by bending your elbows'),
('Elevated Pike Press',3,'Push through your hands and return to the starting pike position.'),
('Elevated Pike Press',4,'Repeat'),
('Elevated Pike Shoulder Shrug',1,'Use a bench or an object like a chair to elevate your feet.'),
('Elevated Pike Shoulder Shrug',2,'Slowly lower your body (scapula) while keeping your elbows locked (this is key)'),
('Elevated Pike Shoulder Shrug',3,'Slowly raise your body back to the start position.'),
('Elliptical',1,'Step onto the pedals, grip the handles, and start moving your feet in a natural stride.'),
('Elliptical',2,'Adjust resistance and incline for desired intensity while maintaining a steady, controlled motion.'),
('Elliptical',3,'Keep your posture upright, engage your core, and maintain a consistent pace for an effective workout.'),
('Eversions',1,'Sit on a step or low box, preferably with a back support. Extend both legs and wrap the band around the balls of the working foot'),
('Eversions',2,'Pass the band around the other foot as shown in the video. Hold the end of the band with the opposite arm of the working foot'),
('Eversions',3,'The ankle should be at 90° and turned inwards (inversion) before you start the movement. Turn the ankle out, without moving the rest of the leg.'),
('Extended side Angle Pose With Block',1,'Begin in a lunge position with your right foot forward and your left foot back.'),
('Extended side Angle Pose With Block',2,'Place a block on the outside of your right foot and place your right hand on top of it.'),
('Extended side Angle Pose With Block',3,'Look down towards your right foot as you reach your left arm towards the front of the room, feeling a stretch in your side body. Hold for a few breaths and then switch sides.'),
('extended-side-angle-pose',1,'Begin in a lunge position with your right foot forward and your left foot back.'),
('extended-side-angle-pose',2,'Place your right hand on a block or the ground on the outside of your right foot.'),
('extended-side-angle-pose',3,'Reach your left arm overhead and then round your spine, bringing your left hand to your right ear.'),
('extended-side-angle-pose',4,'Look down towards your right foot as you reach your left arm towards the front of the room, feeling a stretch in your side body. Hold for a few breaths and then switch sides.'),
('Ez Bar Close Grip Curl',1,'Stand upright, hold EZ bar with narrow underhand grip, elbows pinned to sides.'),
('Ez Bar Close Grip Curl',2,'Curl bar upward by flexing elbows, keep shoulders still throughout movement.'),
('Ez Bar Close Grip Curl',3,'Squeeze biceps at top, pause briefly for maximum contraction.'),
('Ez Bar Close Grip Curl',4,'Lower bar slowly under control until arms fully extended.'),
('Ez Bar Cuban Press',1,'Hold EZ bar with overhand grip, elbows bent, bar at upper abdomen.'),
('Ez Bar Cuban Press',2,'Raise elbows to shoulder height while externally rotating forearms upward.'),
('Ez Bar Cuban Press',3,'Press bar overhead once forearms are vertical and aligned.'),
('Ez Bar Cuban Press',4,'Reverse motion slowly back to starting position.'),
('Ez Bar Curl',1,'Stand tall, hold EZ bar with shoulder-width underhand grip.'),
('Ez Bar Curl',2,'Curl bar upward, keeping elbows tucked and torso stable.'),
('Ez Bar Curl',3,'Pause and squeeze biceps at the top.'),
('Ez Bar Curl',4,'Lower slowly until arms fully extended.'),
('Ez Bar Drag Curl',1,'Grab an EZ bar with an underhand grip.'),
('Ez Bar Drag Curl',2,'Pull your elbows straight back and let the bar drag against your upper body (or very close to it).'),
('Ez Bar Front Raise',1,'Stand tall with an overhand grip on the barbell. Raise your arms until your fists are around eye level.'),
('Ez Bar Front Raise',2,'Return to the start under control. This exercise is prone to using momentum when you begin to fatigue.'),
('Ez Bar Overhead Press',1,'Take a roughly shoulder width grip. There should be a straight line from your elbow to fist (vertical forearms).'),
('Ez Bar Overhead Press',2,'Pull your chin back and press the weight toward the ceiling by extending at the elbow joint and flexing at the shoulder joint.'),
('Ez Bar Overhead Press',3,'Press until your elbows are extended and push your head forward slightly.'),
('Ez Bar Overhead Press',4,'Return to the start position with control. Pulling your chin back to allow the bar to pass your face safely.'),
('Ez Bar Overhead Tricep Extension',1,'Be careful getting the bar into place overhead. Push your elbows forward while keeping your elbows tucked in.'),
('Ez Bar Overhead Tricep Extension',2,'Look for what feels like a stretch in your triceps. Extend your elbows until your fists are pointed at the ceiling.'),
('EZ Bar Preacher Curl',1,'Position yourself on preacher bench; grasp EZ bar with underhand grip, elbows extended.'),
('EZ Bar Preacher Curl',2,'Slowly curl bar towards shoulders; keep upper arms stationary, focus on biceps.'),
('EZ Bar Preacher Curl',3,'Lower bar back to starting position; maintain control, repeat for reps.'),
('Ez Bar Reverse Curl',1,'Take a double overhand grip that\'s about shoulder width. Flex your elbows while keeping your elbows tucked in. Try not to let them flare out.'),
('Ez Bar Reverse Curl',2,'Curl until your forearm presses into your bicep. Then fully extend your elbows at the bottom of each rep.'),
('EZ Bar Reverse Preacher Curl',1,'Sit on preacher bench, grip EZ bar overhand at shoulder width, elbows resting on pad.'),
('EZ Bar Reverse Preacher Curl',2,'Curl bar towards chin, keep elbows stable.'),
('EZ Bar Reverse Preacher Curl',3,'Lower bar slowly to starting position, maintaining control throughout.'),
('Ez Bar Reverse Spider Curl',1,'Lay on an incline bench and hold the EZ bar with your elbows extended.'),
('Ez Bar Reverse Spider Curl',2,'From this starting position, curl the bar up towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body and your core engaged.'),
('Ez Bar Reverse Spider Curl',3,'Slowly lower the bar back down to the starting position, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.'),
('Ez Bar Romanian Deadlift',1,'Take a shoulder width, double overhand or mixed grip.'),
('Ez Bar Romanian Deadlift',2,'Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.'),
('Ez Bar Romanian Deadlift',3,'When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you\'re back in a standing position.'),
('Ez Bar Shrug',1,'Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart, with a barbell in front of you.'),
('Ez Bar Shrug',2,'Bend down and grab the bar with an overhand grip, your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back straight and your shoulders down as you grip the bar.'),
('Ez Bar Shrug',3,'Stand up straight, lifting the bar off the ground and pulling it toward your hips. Keep your elbows close to your body and your shoulders down as you do this.'),
('Ez Bar Shrug',4,'Once the bar is at your hips, raise your shoulders as high as you can, holding the position for a moment.'),
('Ez Bar Spider Curl',1,'Lay on an incline bench and hold an incline bench with your elbows extended.'),
('Ez Bar Spider Curl',2,'From this starting position, curl the bat up towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body and your core engaged.'),
('Ez Bar Spider Curl',3,'Slowly lower the bar back down to the starting position, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.'),
('Ez Bar Upright Row',1,'Take a double overhand roughly shoulder width grip.'),
('Ez Bar Upright Row',2,'Pull your elbows straight up the ceiling. Aim to get the bar to chin level or slightly higher.'),
('Ez Bar Zercher Squat',1,'Begin by standing with your feet about hip-width apart and holding the bar in the crook of your arms, near your belly. Your palms should be facing towards your body.'),
('Ez Bar Zercher Squat',2,'Sit back and lower your body down until your thighs are parallel to the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.'),
('Ez Bar Zercher Squat',3,'Push through your heels to extend your hips and stand back up to the starting position.'),
('Feet Pulling Straps Hamstring Curls Prone On The Long Box',1,'Lie prone on long box, hips supported, straps around feet.'),
('Feet Pulling Straps Hamstring Curls Prone On The Long Box',2,'Start with legs extended, core engaged, pelvis neutral.'),
('Feet Pulling Straps Hamstring Curls Prone On The Long Box',3,'Bend knees, curling heels toward glutes using hamstrings.'),
('Feet Pulling Straps Hamstring Curls Prone On The Long Box',4,'Extend legs slowly, maintaining control and constant strap tension.'),
('Foam Roller Angel',1,'Place a long tube or foam roller on the ground.'),
('Foam Roller Angel',2,'Sit on the very edge of the roller and lie on it, aligning it with your spine.'),
('Foam Roller Angel',3,'Knees are bent and placed on the ground, which provides stability and a neutral lower back'),
('Foam Roller Angel',4,'Bring you arms overhead by keeping them parallel to the ground throughout the whole movement, before bringing them back to the starting position.'),
('Footwork Heels On The Bar',1,'Lie supine, heels on bar hip-width, toes lifted slightly.'),
('Footwork Heels On The Bar',2,'Press bar away, fully extending legs without locking knees.'),
('Footwork Heels On The Bar',3,'Maintain neutral pelvis, ribs down, and steady core engagement.'),
('Footwork Heels On The Bar',4,'Bend knees to return with control, keeping heels connected.'),
('Footwork High Half Toe',1,'Lie supine, balls of feet on bar, heels lifted high.'),
('Footwork High Half Toe',2,'Press bar away, extending legs while maintaining lifted heels.'),
('Footwork High Half Toe',3,'Keep pelvis neutral, ribs down, and core engaged.'),
('Footwork High Half Toe',4,'Bend knees to return smoothly, maintaining ankle stability and control.'),
('Footwork Lower And Lift',1,'Lie supine, balls of feet on bar, heels lifted.'),
('Footwork Lower And Lift',2,'Press bar away, fully extending legs with control.'),
('Footwork Lower And Lift',3,'Lower heels under bar, then lift heels as high as possible.'),
('Footwork Lower And Lift',4,'Bend knees to return, maintaining steady tension and ankle control.'),
('Forearm Plank',1,'Place forearms on the ground with your elbows bent at a 90° angle aligned beneath your shoulders, with your arms parallel at shoulder-width.'),
('Forearm Plank',2,'Your feet should be together, with only your toes touching the floor.'),
('Forearm Plank',3,'Lift your belly off the floor and form a straight line from your heels to the crown of your head and hold.'),
