('Glute Ham Raise',1,'Position yourself on a glute ham raise machine or find a suitable substitute like a stability ball or bench.'),
('Glute Ham Raise',2,'Adjust the equipment to fit your body by setting the footplate at an appropriate height and making sure your feet are securely anchored.'),
('Glute Ham Raise',3,'Begin the movement by slowly lowering your upper body towards the ground while keeping your torso and legs aligned.'),
('Glute Ham Raise',4,'Once you reach the lowest point where your body is parallel to the ground or as far as you can comfortably go, pause briefly.'),
('Glute Ham Raise',5,'Engage your glutes and hamstrings again as you push yourself back up to the starting position, using the strength of your posterior chain muscles.'),
('Gluteator',1,'Sit on the seat upright with your knees placed on the pads and your feet on the foot pads.'),
