('Hand Side Plank Reach Through',2,'Reach your top arm under your body.'),
('Hand Side Plank Reach Through',3,'Return to the plank position.'),
('Hanging Knee Raises',1,'Grab the bar and hang, your body still and your legs straight.'),
('Hanging Knee Raises',2,'Slowly draw your knees up to your chest'),
('Hanging Knee Raises',3,'Once you have raised your knees as high as possible, lower your legs and repeat. Duration of these movements should be slow so that you do not utilize momentum, enabling you to get the most out of the exercise.'),
('Hanging Knee Raises',4,'Duration of these movements should be slow so that you do not utilize momentum, enabling you to get the most out of the exercise.'),
('Hanging L Sit',1,'Hang from a bar with arms fully extended.'),
('Hanging L Sit',2,'Lift legs to form an \"L\" shape.'),
('Hanging L Sit',3,'Hold for allotted amount of time keeping your abs flexed.'),
('Happy Baby',1,'Lie down on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor.'),
('Happy Baby',2,'Lift your feet off the floor and bring your knees towards your chest.'),
('Happy Baby',3,'Reach inside your knees and hold onto the outside edges of your feet.'),
('Happy Baby',4,'Gently pull your knees towards your armpits and rock side to side for a few breaths.'),
('Headstand',1,'Begin on your hands and knees with your wrists under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.'),
('Headstand',2,'Place your forearms on the floor and interlace your fingers.'),
('Headstand',3,'Place the crown of your head on the floor and tuck your toes under.'),
('Headstand',4,'Walk your feet towards your head and lift your hips up.'),
('Headstand',5,'Straighten your legs and find your balance. Hold for several breaths and then release.'),
('Hip Lift',1,'Lie supine with knees bent, feet hip-width and flat. Hips slightly off the carriage.'),
('Hip Lift',2,'Engage core and glutes, press through heels.'),
('Hip Lift',3,'Maintain hip position as you press.'),
