('Kettlebell Shrug (Single)',2,'Holding the kettlebell in both hands in front of your pelvis, engage your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to touch them together.'),
('Kettlebell Shrug (Single)',3,'Release the shrug and repeat'),
('Kettlebell Silverback Shrug',1,'Stand with feet hip-width apart, hold one kettlebell in each hand at your sides, and lean forward.'),
('Kettlebell Silverback Shrug',2,'Lift your shoulders backward while keeping arms straight.'),
('Kettlebell Silverback Shrug',3,'Lower shoulders back down, repeat for desired reps.'),
('Kettlebell Silverback Shrug (Single)',1,'Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.'),
('Kettlebell Silverback Shrug (Single)',2,'Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.'),
('Kettlebell Silverback Shrug (Single)',3,'Holding the kettlebell in both hands engage your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to touch them together. Release the shrug.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Calf Raise',1,'Stand tall with your feet on the ground. You can put the the balls of your feet on top of a plate to extend the range of motion.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Calf Raise',2,'Imagine you have a string attached to your heels and pull your heels up toward the ceiling.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Chest Fly',1,'Lie on the floor with your knees bent and feet firmly on the floor, with your arms to the side of your body.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Chest Fly',2,'Holding a kettlebell in one hand, keeping your arm fully extended with a slight bend in the elbow and your forearms facing upwards, lift the kettlebell above your chest.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Chest Fly',3,'Lower the kettlebell to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Chest Press',1,'Lie on bench holding one kettlebell above chest with arm extended.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Chest Press',2,'Lower kettlebell toward chest while keeping torso stable.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Chest Press',3,'Press upward, squeezing chest at the top without twisting.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Clean And Jerk',1,'Hold kettlebell between legs with one hand, hinge slightly at hips.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Clean And Jerk',2,'Pull kettlebell upward to shoulder, catching it in rack position.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Clean And Jerk',3,'Dip at knees, then drive upward to press kettlebell overhead.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Clean And Press',1,'Begin with the kettlebell between your legs.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Clean And Press',2,'Hinge at your hips, and lift to shoulder, then press overhead.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Curl',1,'Stand up straight with a kettlebell in one hand with your forearm facing out.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Curl',2,'Raise the kettlebell, bending your arm at the elbow and keeping your forearm vertical until your palm faces the shoulder.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Curl',3,'Lower to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Farmers March',1,'Standing straight with a kettlebell in one hand, lift the knee of one leg off the floor to knee height.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Farmers March',2,'Bring the leg back to standing and repeat with the other leg, keeping the kettlebell on the same side.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Farmers March',3,'Repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Farmers Walk',1,'Standing straight with a kettlebell in one hand, walk for a specified distance or duration.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Farmers Walk',2,'Stay upright and don\'t lean to one side.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Floor Fly',1,'Lie on your back holding one kettlebell above chest with slight elbow bend.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Floor Fly',2,'Lower arm out wide until elbow lightly touches the floor.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Floor Fly',3,'Bring kettlebell back over chest, squeezing pec at the top.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Floor Press',1,'Start flat on your back with a kettlebell extended over you.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Floor Press',2,'Bring your elbow to the floor, rest for a second to remove all the momentum from the rep, then press to a lockout.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Forward Lunge',1,'Stand straight with your feet slightly apart and hold a kettlebell in one hand.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Forward Lunge',2,'Bring the same leg as the arm holding the kettlebell in front of you, squat down until your thigh is parallel to the ground, keeping your back straight.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Forward Lunge',3,'Return to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Forward Lunge',1,'Hold kettlebell in front rack position.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Forward Lunge',2,'Step forward, lunge. Bringing your back knee to the floor.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Forward Lunge',3,'Extend your knee and return to the starting position.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Reverse Lunge',1,'Hold kettlebell in front rack position.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Reverse Lunge',2,'Step backward, lunge. Bring your back knee to the floor.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Reverse Lunge',3,'Extend your knee back into the starting position.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up',1,'Stand in front of a step or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a kettlebell at one shoulder.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up',2,'Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing off your foot to raise your body up onto the bench.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up Knee Drive',1,'Hold kettlebell in front rack position and place opposite foot on platform.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up Knee Drive',2,'Drive through front heel to step up while keeping chest tall and stable.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up Knee Drive',3,'Lift trailing knee high at the top, then step down slowly with control.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Hang Clean And Jerk',1,'Hold kettlebell in one hand at thigh level with slight knee bend.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Hang Clean And Jerk',2,'Pull kettlebell explosively to shoulder, catching it in rack position.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Hang Clean And Jerk',3,'Dip slightly, then drive upward to press kettlebell overhead.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm High Incline Chest Press',1,'Sit on high incline bench holding kettlebell at shoulder height.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm High Incline Chest Press',2,'Press kettlebell upward and slightly inward until arm fully extends.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm High Incline Chest Press',3,'Lower slowly to start position, keeping torso stable and controlled.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Incline Chest Press',1,'Sit on incline bench holding kettlebell at shoulder with elbow bent.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Incline Chest Press',2,'Press kettlebell upward and slightly inward until arm fully extends.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Incline Chest Press',3,'Lower slowly to starting position, keeping torso stable and controlled.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Larsen Press',1,'Lie on bench with feet off floor, holding one kettlebell above chest.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Larsen Press',2,'Lower kettlebell toward chest while keeping core tight and legs raised.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Larsen Press',3,'Press upward, squeezing chest at the top without twisting torso.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Pendlay Row',1,'Stand with feet hip-width, hinge forward until torso is nearly parallel to floor.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Pendlay Row',2,'Pick kettlebell from ground with straight arm, keeping back flat and core braced.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Pendlay Row',3,'Pull elbow straight up to ribs, then lower kettlebell fully back to floor each rep.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Press',1,'Laying on the floor with your knees bent and feet firmly on the floor, leave one arm resting to the side of the body.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Press',2,'Using the other arm, hold the kettlebell at arms length directly upwards of your shoulder.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Press',3,'Lower your arm until your upper arm to elbow is resting on the floor.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Press',4,'Return to starting position.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Pullover',1,'Lie on bench holding one kettlebell above chest with slight elbow bend.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Pullover',2,'Lower kettlebell in an arc behind head until you feel a deep stretch.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Pullover',3,'Pull kettlebell back over chest using lats and triceps, keeping control.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Push Press',1,'Hold kettlebell at shoulder height, feet shoulder-width apart.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Push Press',2,'Dip slightly at knees, then drive upward, pressing kettlebell overhead.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Push Press',3,'Lock out arm briefly, then lower kettlebell under control.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Rear Delt Fly',1,'Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Rear Delt Fly',2,'Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Rear Delt Fly',3,'Bring one arm behind you and rest this arm on your back. With the other arm, hold the kettlebell at arms length close to the floor.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Rear Delt Fly',4,'Swing the kettlebell out and up towards the side of your body and then return to centre. Repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Rear Delt Row',1,'Hinge at hips with back flat, holding kettlebell under shoulder.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Rear Delt Row',2,'Pull elbow out and back at a wide angle, targeting rear delt.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Rear Delt Row',3,'Squeeze at the top, then lower slowly to full stretch.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Reverse Curl',1,'Stand with feet hip-width apart.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Reverse Curl',2,'Hold a kettlebell with palms facing down.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Reverse Curl',3,'Lift kettlebell toward shoulders, squeezing biceps, then lower with control.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Reverse Lunge',1,'Stand straight with your feet slightly apart and hold a kettlebell in one hand.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Reverse Lunge',2,'Bring the same leg as the arm holding the kettlebell behind you, squat down until your back knee touches the ground, keeping your back straight.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Reverse Lunge',3,'Return to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Row',1,'Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, shifting one foot behind you. Hold the kettlebell in the same hand as the leg shifted backwards.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Row',2,'Bend forwards at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knee, keeping your back straight.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Row',3,'Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Row On Bench',1,'Start by standing in front of a flat bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a kettlebell in one hand.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Row On Bench',2,'Place your other hand on the bench for support, and bend at the waist so that your chest is parallel to the ground.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Row On Bench',3,'From this starting position, row the kettlebell up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blade together as you do so.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Row On Bench',4,'Make sure to keep your elbow close to your body and your core engaged throughout the movement.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Shoulder Extension',1,'Hold kettlebell at your sides with straight arms and palms neutral.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Shoulder Extension',2,'Move arm backward until you feel lats and rear delts engage.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Shoulder Extension',3,'Lower slowly to starting position under full control.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Snatch',1,'Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebell between legs.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Snatch',2,'Squat, grip kettlebell, explode hips, and lift kettlebell overhead.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Snatch',3,'Lower kettlebell safely to start position.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Step Up Balance',1,'Begin by standing in front of a sturdy box or bench that is about knee-height, holding a kettlebell in one hand'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Step Up Balance',2,'Place your right foot on the box and push through the heel to lift your body up and onto the box, keeping your left foot off the ground.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Step Up Balance',3,'Step back down with your right foot, lowering your left foot to the ground.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Step Up Knee Drive',1,'Hold one kettlebell at your side and place opposite foot on platform.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Step Up Knee Drive',2,'Drive through front heel to step up, keeping torso tall and core tight.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Step Up Knee Drive',3,'Lift trailing knee high at the top, then step down slowly with control.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Swing',1,'Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebell between legs, grip with one hand, hinge at hips.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Swing',2,'Swing kettlebell forcefully forward, using hip thrust, arm straight.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Swing',3,'Swing kettlebell back between legs, repeat for desired reps.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Thruster',1,'Hold kettlebell at shoulder height with feet shoulder-width apart.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Thruster',2,'Squat down, then drive upward, pressing kettlebell overhead in one motion.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Thruster',3,'Lower kettlebell as you descend into next rep smoothly.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Tricep Guilotine Press',1,'Lie on bench holding kettlebell above upper chest with palm facing in.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Tricep Guilotine Press',2,'Lower kettlebell toward neck or upper chest by bending elbow forward.'),
('Kettlebell Single Arm Tricep Guilotine Press',3,'Extend arm fully, squeezing triceps at the top while keeping shoulder stable.'),
('Kettlebell Single Leg Calf Raise',1,'Standing straight with a kettlebell in one hand, lift the same foot as the side without the kettlebell off the floor.'),
('Kettlebell Single Leg Calf Raise',2,'Raise your heel upwards while keeping your knees stationary.'),
('Kettlebell Single Leg Calf Raise',3,'Pause when your heels are fully extended and then slowly return to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Single Leg Deadlift',1,'Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, lifting one foot off the floor behind you. Hold the kettlebell in the same arm as the lifted leg.'),
('Kettlebell Single Leg Deadlift',2,'Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you extend your lifted leg behind you, keeping your back straight - holding out your arm to the side for balance.'),
('Kettlebell Single Leg Deadlift',3,'Return to the upright position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Single Leg Hip Thrust',1,'Sitting on the floor with one knee bent with the foot firmly on the floor and one leg extended, lean your back against the bench.'),
('Kettlebell Single Leg Hip Thrust',2,'Resting the kettlebell on your pelvis, raise your pelvis until your stomach, pelvis and thighs are in line.'),
('Kettlebell Single Leg Hip Thrust',3,'Slowly lower until you are in the starting position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Single Leg Single Arm Calf Raise',1,'Standing straight with a kettlebell in one hand, lift the opposing foot off the floor.'),
('Kettlebell Single Leg Single Arm Calf Raise',2,'Raise your heel upwards while keeping your knees stationary.'),
('Kettlebell Single Leg Single Arm Calf Raise',3,'Pause when your heels are fully extended and then slowly return to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Situp',1,'Lay flat on your back with straight legs and hold the kettle bell above your chest at arms length.'),
('Kettlebell Situp',2,'Draw your belly into the base of your spine to engage the muscles, then raise your head and shoulders off the floor with the kettlebell raised at arms length above your chest.'),
('Kettlebell Situp',3,'Return to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Snatch (Double)',1,'Begin with a two kettlebells between your legs, hinge at hips, then swing it upwards explosively.'),
('Kettlebell Snatch (Double)',2,'As they rise, lock out arm overhead, wrist straight.'),
('Kettlebell Snatch (Double)',3,'Control the descent, then repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Somersault Squat',1,'Start in a deep squat holding a kettlebell between your thighs.'),
('Kettlebell Somersault Squat',2,'Extend your knees until mostly extended without extending the hips.'),
('Kettlebell Spinal Jefferson Curl',1,'Stand tall holding kettlebells in front with feet hip-width apart.'),
('Kettlebell Spinal Jefferson Curl',2,'Slowly roll down through spine one vertebra at a time, reaching toward toes.'),
('Kettlebell Spinal Jefferson Curl',3,'Reverse the motion, rolling up through spine until standing tall again.'),
('Kettlebell Squat Clean And Jerk',1,'Start with kettlebells between legs resting on the floor with knee bend and flat back.'),
('Kettlebell Squat Clean And Jerk',2,'Pull kettlebells explosively to shoulder, catching it in a squat position.'),
('Kettlebell Squat Clean And Jerk',3,'Stand tall, dip slightly, then drive up to press kettlebells overhead.'),
('Kettlebell Staggered Deadlift',1,'Begin with feet hip-width apart, one foot forward, kettlebell between feet.'),
('Kettlebell Staggered Deadlift',2,'Hinge at hips, grip kettlebell, and stand tall.'),
('Kettlebell Staggered Deadlift',3,'Lower kettlebell with control, then repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Staggered Deadlift (Single)',1,'Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, shifting one foot behind you. Hold the kettlebell in both hands in front of your thighs.'),
('Kettlebell Staggered Deadlift (Single)',2,'Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees and keep your back straight.'),
('Kettlebell Staggered Deadlift (Single)',3,'Return to the upright position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Staggered Swing',1,'Lower kettlebell with control, then repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Staggered Swing',2,'Explosively thrust hips forward, swing kettlebell to chest height.'),
('Kettlebell Staggered Swing',3,'Repeat for desired reps, keeping core engaged and maintaining a staggered stance for balance.'),
('Kettlebell Staggered Waiters Bow',1,'Set up a bar at mid way up your quad. Place the working leg against the bar.'),
('Kettlebell Staggered Waiters Bow',2,'Place one foot behind. You should only be on your toes on that back foot. Your front foot should be planted flat the entire time.'),
('Kettlebell Staggered Waiters Bow',3,'Bend your back knee and push your hips back. Look for a stretch in your front hamstring.'),
('Kettlebell Staggered Waiters Bow',4,'When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward again until you\'re back in a standing position.'),
('Kettlebell Standing Tricep Extension',1,'Stand with legs shoulder width apart.'),
('Kettlebell Standing Tricep Extension',2,'Hold the kettlebell in both hands behind your head.'),
('Kettlebell Standing Tricep Extension',3,'Straighten arms bringing kettlebell above your head.'),
('Kettlebell Standing Tricep Extension',4,'Return to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Step Up',1,'Standing up straight, using a bench as a step, raise one foot onto the bench and hold the kettlebell in the same arm as the straight leg.'),
('Kettlebell Step Up',2,'Stand and bring both feet onto the bench. Slowly lower your leg back down to the starting position.'),
('Kettlebell Step Up',3,'Repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Step Up Double',1,'Standing up straight, using a bench as a step, raise one foot onto the bench and hold the kettlebell in the same arm as the straight leg.'),
('Kettlebell Step Up Double',2,'Stand and bring both feet onto the bench. Slowly lower your leg back down to the starting position.'),
('Kettlebell Step Up Double',3,'Repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Suitcase Deadlift',1,'Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and holding a kettlebell at one side of your body, with your palms facing your thighs.'),
('Kettlebell Suitcase Deadlift',2,'Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and knees to lower the kettlebell down towards the ground.'),
('Kettlebell Suitcase Deadlift',3,'As the kettlebell reaches the ground, use your legs and glutes to push through your heels and extend your hips and knees to raise your body back to the starting position.'),
('Kettlebell Suitcase Deadlift',4,'Repeat the movement for the desired number of reps, then switch sides and repeat the exercise with the kettlebell on the opposite side of your body.'),
('Kettlebell Sumo Deadlift',1,'Stand with feet wide apart, toes pointing slightly outward, and kettlebell on the floor between your feet.'),
('Kettlebell Sumo Deadlift',2,'Bend at hips and knees, keeping back straight, and grip the kettlebell handle.'),
('Kettlebell Sumo Deadlift',3,'Lift the kettlebell by extending hips and knees, stand up straight, and return to the starting position.'),
('Kettlebell Swing',1,'Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell between your legs, with your knees slightly bent.'),
('Kettlebell Swing',2,'Keeping your back straight, swing the kettlebell upwards until the kettlebell is level with your chest and carefully lower.'),
('Kettlebell Swing',3,'Repeat'),
('Kettlebell Swing (Double)',1,'Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebells outside legs'),
('Kettlebell Swing (Double)',2,'Hinge at hips, swing kettlebells forward, then back.'),
('Kettlebell Swing (Double)',3,'Thrust hips to swing kettlebells upward, keeping arms straight.'),
('Kettlebell Swing Lunge',1,'Stand with your feet shoulder-width. Kettlebell at your side.'),
('Kettlebell Swing Lunge',2,'Step forward with your right foot and bend both knees to lower your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground.'),
('Kettlebell Swing Lunge',3,'Push off your right foot to return to the starting position.'),
('Kettlebell Swing Lunge',4,'Step back with the same leg until the back knee taps the floor.'),
('Kettlebell Tate Press',1,'Lie flat on your back. Keeping your arm straight, hold the kettlebell above your chest with your palm facing away from your body.'),
('Kettlebell Tate Press',2,'Bend your arm, touching the kettlebell to the top of the shoulder opposite to the arm being worked.'),
('Kettlebell Tate Press',3,'Return to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Thruster',1,'Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a kettlebell in each hand.'),
('Kettlebell Thruster',2,'Bring the kettlebells to your shoulders, with your palms facing inward and your elbows bent.'),
('Kettlebell Thruster',3,'From this starting position, dip your knees slightly and then quickly extend them as you press the kettlebells upwards.'),
('Kettlebell Thruster',4,'As you press the kettlebells upwards, also push your hips forward to help generate additional power.'),
('Kettlebell Thruster',5,'Slowly lower the kettlebells back down to the starting position, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.'),
('Kettlebell Upright Row',1,'Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.'),
('Kettlebell Upright Row',2,'Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.'),
('Kettlebell Upright Row',3,'Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Upright Row Single',1,'Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.'),
('Kettlebell Upright Row Single',2,'Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.'),
('Kettlebell Upright Row Single',3,'Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Waiters Bow',1,'Place a barbell at about midway up your thigh. Press your quads into the barbell.'),
('Kettlebell Waiters Bow',2,'Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.'),
('Kettlebell Waiters Bow',3,'When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you\'re back in a standing position.'),
('Kettlebell Walking Farmers March',1,'Standing straight with kettlebells, start walking towards a set point. Pulling your knee up toward the ceiling.'),
('Kettlebell Walking Farmers March',2,'Make sure to keep your chest tall and shoulder blades pulled back.'),
('Kettlebell Walking Farmers March',3,'Try to keep your stride distance roughly the same.'),
('Kettlebell Walking Shoulder Flexion Bent Elbow Hold',1,'Stand up straight with the working arm in front of you and bent at the elbow (90°).'),
('Kettlebell Walking Shoulder Flexion Bent Elbow Hold',2,'Hold an inverted kettlebell in that arm. Walk around holding the kettlebell in that position.'),
('Kettlebell Walking Shoulder Flexion Bent Elbow Hold',3,'The goal is to maintain the position of the kettlebell without it falling over.'),
('Kettlebell Walkover Pushup',1,'Starting in a press up position with feet wide and one hand resting on the kettlebell, complete a full press up, lowering your chest towards the ground while keeping your body straight and returning to the starting position.'),
('Kettlebell Walkover Pushup',2,'Swap hands on the kettlebell, placing the hand originally on the kettlebell underneath your shoulder, complete another press up.'),
('Kettlebell Walkover Pushup',3,'Repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Windmill',1,'Stand with feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart. Hold the kettlebell in one hand and extend your arm above your head.'),
('Kettlebell Windmill',2,'Keeping your legs straight and the kettlebell above your head, lower the relaxed arm towards the ground, twisting your body towards the side of the raised arm.'),
('Kettlebell Windmill',3,'Return to the starting potion, tilt your pelvis forward and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Windmill Bottom Hand',1,'Stand with feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart. Hold the kettlebell in your bottom hand and extend the other arm above your head.'),
('Kettlebell Windmill Bottom Hand',2,'Keeping your legs straight and the kettlebell inside your thigh, lower the kettlebell towards the ground, twisting your body towards the side of the raised arm.'),
('Kettlebell Windmill Bottom Hand',3,'Return to the starting position, tilt your pelvis forward and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Wood Chopper',1,'Stand with feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart and hold the kettle bell with both hands against your hip.'),
('Kettlebell Wood Chopper',2,'Keeping your arms straight, swing the kettlebell upwards and across your body towards your shoulder, raising the kettlebell to head height rotating your hips as you do so.'),
('Kettlebell Wood Chopper',3,'Return to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Wrist Curl',1,'Stand up straight with a kettlebell in both hands in front of your pelvis, with your forearms facing outwards.'),
('Kettlebell Wrist Curl',2,'Flex your wrist towards your body until the kettlebell is level with your stomach.'),
('Kettlebell Wrist Curl',3,'Lower to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Kettlebell Wrist Extension',1,'Stand up straight with a kettlebell in both hands in front of your pelvis, with your forearms facing inwards.'),
('Kettlebell Wrist Extension',2,'Flex your wrist upwards until wrists are fully extended.'),
('Kettlebell Wrist Extension',3,'Lower to the starting position and repeat.'),
('Kickbacks',1,'Get down on all fours and position your hands under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.'),
('Kickbacks',2,'Kick back with one leg and squeeze your glutes.'),
('Kickbacks',3,'Slowly return to starting position by bending your knee and lowering your leg.'),
('Kickbacks',4,'Switch Legs. Repeat.'),
('L Sit Chin Up',1,'Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)'),
('L Sit Chin Up',2,'With your body in an \"L\" position and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.'),
('L Sit Chin Up',3,'Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.'),
('L Sit Pull Up',1,'Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, arms and shoulders fully extended. Pull your legs up until you\'re in an \"L\" position.'),
('L Sit Pull Up',2,'Pull your body up until your chin is above the bar.'),
('L Sit Pull Up',3,'Lower your body back to starting position.'),
('Landmine Alternating Lunge And Twist',1,'Set up the landmine attachment and load weight.'),
('Landmine Alternating Lunge And Twist',2,'Stand facing the landmine, holding the weight away from your chest.'),
('Landmine Alternating Lunge And Twist',3,'Step backward with one leg, lunge down while twisting your torso toward the front leg, return to starting position, and repeat on the other side.'),
('Landmine Alternating Lunge To Chest Press',1,'Stand facing the landmine with feet hip-width apart and holding the end of the landmine barbell with both hands, keeping elbows bent and close to your body.'),
('Landmine Alternating Lunge To Chest Press',2,'Step backward with the right foot, lunge down, and press the landmine away from your chest.'),
('Landmine Alternating Lunge To Chest Press',3,'Push through the left heel to return to the starting position while pulling the landmine back to your chest.'),
('Landmine Alternating Lunge To Chest Press',4,'Repeat on the opposite side, alternating for the desired number of reps.'),
('Landmine Bicep Curl',1,'Stand beside the landmine with your feet shoulder-width apart while grasping the end of the landmine barbell with the hand farther away from the landmine attachment, palm facing up and your elbow close to your side.'),
('Landmine Bicep Curl',2,'Curl the barbell up towards your opposite shoulder, contracting your bicep muscles, then slowly lower the barbell back down.'),
('Landmine Bicep Curl',3,'Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.'),
('Landmine Calf Raise',1,'Stand facing the barbell, holding the end of the barbell close to your chest in both hands with your elbows tucked in to your sides.'),
('Landmine Calf Raise',2,'Drive though the balls of your feet to raise your heels off the ground, squeezing your calves, with a focus on making sure your ankles do not turn out or in.'),
('Landmine Calf Raise',3,'Lower your heels back down to the ground and repeat for the desired number of reps.'),
('Landmine Concentration Curl',1,'Start on one knee facing the landmine, holding the end of the barbell with your hand on the side of your forward leg.'),
('Landmine Concentration Curl',2,'While keeping your elbow braced against the inside of your knee, curl the barbell upward towards your shoulder, then lower it back down with control.'),
('Landmine Concentration Curl',3,'Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.'),
('Landmine Curtsy Lunge',1,'Stand facing the barbell while holding the end of the bar at your side with one hand.'),
('Landmine Curtsy Lunge',2,'With the leg on the same side of your body as the barbell, lunge backward and across your body at a 45 degree angle while keeping your weight on your front heel to lower your back knee gently to the ground.'),
('Landmine Curtsy Lunge',3,'Drive through your front heel as you step back to the starting position, and repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.'),
('Landmine Glute Kick Back',1,'Start on your hands and knees perpendicular to the barbell with the end of the barbell resting on the inside of your knee that is closer to the bar.'),
('Landmine Glute Kick Back',2,'Keeping your core braced, your back flat, and your moving leg bent at a 90 degree angle, drive the heel of your working leg up the ceiling while squeezing your glute.'),
('Landmine Glute Kick Back',3,'Follow the movement path as you bring your knee back down to the ground beneath your hip, keeping your knee bent to maintain control of the barbell.'),
('Landmine Glute Kick Back',4,'Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.'),
('Landmine Goblet Curtsy Lunge',1,'Start facing the barbell while holding the end of the bar in the goblet position in front of your chest with your elbows close to your sides.'),
('Landmine Goblet Curtsy Lunge',2,'Step backward and across your body with one leg at a 45 degree angle while keeping your weight on your front heel to gently lower your back knee to the ground.'),
('Landmine Goblet Curtsy Lunge',3,'Drive through your front heel as you step back up and to the starting position.'),
('Landmine Goblet Curtsy Lunge',4,'Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching legs.'),
('Landmine Goblet Lateral Lunge',1,'Start facing the barbell while holding the end of the bar close to your chest in the goblet position with your elbows tucked in close to your body.'),
('Landmine Goblet Lateral Lunge',2,'Step directly out to the side with both toes pointing forward. Keep your weight on the heel of the leg you step out with as you sink down over that foot while your other leg remains straight for balance.'),
('Landmine Goblet Lateral Lunge',3,'Drive through the heel over which you have centered your body as you step back to the starting position.'),
('Landmine Goblet Lateral Lunge',4,'Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.'),
('Landmine Hack Squat',1,'Start facing away from the landmine attachment with the end of the barbell resting on one shoulder against the base of your neck while leaning slightly back into the weight of the barbell.'),
('Landmine Hack Squat',2,'Squat down with control while keeping the weight of the barbell as close to centered over your midpoint as possible, then drive through your heels to stand all the way back up and return to starting position.'),
('Landmine Hack Squat',3,'Repeat for desired number of reps, then switch the side of your body the barbell is on every subsequent set.'),
('Landmine Hollow Hold',1,'Start by lying flat on your back with your legs extended towards the landmine attachment and your arms overhead, holding the landmine barbell with both hands while engaging your core muscles by pressing your lower back into the ground and drawing your belly button in towards your spine.'),
('Landmine Hollow Hold',2,'Lift your legs off the ground, keeping them together and straight, and simultaneously raise your upper body off the ground, reaching the landmine barbell away from your face.'),
('Landmine Hollow Hold',3,'Hold this position for the desired duration, then carefully lower the barbell to the ground.'),
('Landmine Kneeling Overhead Press',1,'Start kneeling in front of the landmine, facing towards it, with your knees hip-width apart and your back straight while holding the end of the bar in both hands in front of your chest.'),
('Landmine Kneeling Overhead Press',2,'Push the landmine up overhead by fully extending your arms until the weight is directly over your head. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the landmine back down to the starting position.'),
('Landmine Kneeling Overhead Press',3,'Repeat for the desired number of reps.'),
('Landmine Kneeling Twist',1,'Kneel down facing the landmine with your knees hip-width apart and your back straight. Grasp the landmine barbell with both hands, interlacing your fingers and holding it above and slightly in front of your body.'),
('Landmine Kneeling Twist',2,'Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, twist your torso to one side, rotating your arms and the landmine along with it. Pause briefly at the end of the twist, feeling the contraction in your oblique muscles.'),
('Landmine Kneeling Twist',3,'Slowly rotate back to the starting position, then twist to the opposite side, repeating the same motion.'),
('Landmine Kneeling Twist',4,'Repeat both sides of the rotation for the desired number of reps.'),
('Landmine Lateral Lunge',1,'Stand facing the landmine with your feet shoulder width apart while holding the end of the barbell in your hands with your arms fully extended down towards the ground.'),
('Landmine Lateral Lunge',2,'While keeping your torso tall and core engaged, step directly out to one side, using the foot you have stepped out with to sit down into the lunge while keeping your other leg straight.'),
('Landmine Lateral Lunge',3,'Drive through your heel on your bent leg as your step together to return to the starting position.'),
('Landmine Lateral Lunge',4,'Repeat for desired number of reps on the same side before switching sides.'),
('Landmine Lunge',1,'Stand in front of the landmine with your feet hip-width apart and your back straight. Grasp the landmine barbell with one hand, holding it at at your side with your palm facing in towards your leg.'),
('Landmine Lunge',2,'Take a step backward with your foot on the same side that you\'re holding the barbell, lowering your body into a lunge position. Bend both knees to lower your body down until your front thigh is parallel to the ground, or as low as your flexibility allows. Keep your torso upright, your chest lifted, and your core engaged throughout the movement.'),
('Landmine Lunge',3,'Push through the heel of your front foot to return to the starting position. Repeat for desired number of reps before switching sides.'),
('Landmine Lunge To Overhead Press',1,'Stand facing the landmine attachment while holding the end of the bar with one hand at your shoulder on the same side with your elbow tucked to your body underneath your wrist.'),
('Landmine Lunge To Overhead Press',2,'Step back with the leg on the same side that you are holding the bar on and with control lower yourself down into a lunge position while keeping your core engaged and torso tall, then drive through your front heel as you step back to the starting position.'),
('Landmine Lunge To Overhead Press',3,'Once your feet are back in the starting position, drive the bar up overhead until your arm is fully extended, then lower the bar back down to the starting position.'),
('Landmine Lunge To Overhead Press',4,'Repeated for the desired number of reps, then switch sides.'),
('Landmine Lying Tricep Extension',1,'Start lying on your back perpendicularly to the barbell, holding the bar directly over your shoulder with the hand that\'s closer to the bar with your palm facing down towards your feet.'),
('Landmine Lying Tricep Extension',2,'While keeping your shoulder steady, bend your elbow and lower the end of the bar back towards your the ground next to your head. Keep your hinging elbow pointed down towards your feet.'),
('Landmine Lying Tricep Extension',3,'Drive through your palm to extend your elbow and return the bar to the starting position, then repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.'),
('Landmine Oblique Twist',1,'Stand facing the landmine, with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. Grasp the landmine barbell with both hands, interlacing your fingers and holding it at chest height. Position your arms straight out in front of you, parallel to the floor, with your elbows slightly bent.'),
('Landmine Oblique Twist',2,'While keeping your core engaged, rotate your torso and the landmine to one side. Twist through your waist, using your oblique muscles to generate the movement. Pivot on the ball of your opposite foot as you rotate away from it.'),
('Landmine Oblique Twist',3,'Rotate back to the starting position, then perform the same movement in the opposite direction.'),
('Landmine Oblique Twist',4,'Repeat for the desired number of reps.'),
('Landmine Overhead Press',1,'Stand facing the landmine, holding the end of the bar in both hands with your palms facing each other.'),
('Landmine Overhead Press',2,'Extend your arms upward, pressing the end of the bar up overhead. Pause at the top of the movement, then lower the bar with control back to the starting position.'),
('Landmine Overhead Press',3,'Repeat for the desired number of reps.'),
('Landmine Romanian Deadlift',1,'Stand in front of the landmine with your feet hip-width apart and your knees slightly bent. Grasp the landmine barbell with both hands, palms facing each other, and hold it in front of your thighs.'),
('Landmine Romanian Deadlift',2,'Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and push your hips back, allowing the landmine to travel down your thighs. Lower the landmine by bending forward at the hips while keeping your back flat, allowing the barbell to move closer to the floor. Continue the movement until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, keeping your legs relatively straight but with a slight bend in the knees.'),
('Landmine Romanian Deadlift',3,'Reverse the movement by pushing your hips forward and driving through your heels while keeping your back straight.'),
('Landmine Romanian Deadlift',4,'Repeat for the desired number of reps.'),
('Landmine Rotational Lift To Press',1,'Stand perpendicularly to the barbell with the end of the bar in front of your feet. Squat down and hold the end of the bar with your hand closer to the landmine attachment with your palm facing your body.'),
('Landmine Rotational Lift To Press',2,'Drive your feet into the ground to start the motion. As your legs fully extend, pull the bar upwards with your hand and start to rotate your torso in towards the landmine attachment. As you do so, bring your other hand up to the bar and switch your grip. Press through the bar to extend your arm all the way upright, pivoting your back foot to allow for more trunk rotation.'),
('Landmine Rotational Lift To Press',3,'Perform the movement in reverse to return to the starting position. Repeat for desired number of reps before switching sides.'),
('Landmine Russian Twist',1,'Start sitting on the ground facing the landmine attachment, holding the end of the bar in both hands slightly in front of and above your chest while holding your feet off the ground and knees bent.'),
('Landmine Russian Twist',2,'Bending your elbows as little as possible and keeping your core tight and feet elevated, lower the end of the bar with control to the ground on one side of your body, then contract your obliques to return the bar to the center. Repeat on the other side.'),
('Landmine Russian Twist',3,'Repeat for the desired number of reps.'),
('Landmine Seated Alternating Overhead Press',1,'Start sitting on the ground facing the landmine attachment with your legs open for stability while holding the end of the bar in a neutral grip with your hand resting at your shoulder and your elbow beneath your wrist.'),
('Landmine Seated Alternating Overhead Press',2,'Leaning forward slightly, press the bar up into the air until your arm is fully extended. At the top of the movement, switch which hand is holding the end of the bar and lower the bar back down to the opposite shoulder. Perform again to return the bar to the starting position.'),
('Landmine Seated Alternating Overhead Press',3,'Repeat for the desired number of reps.'),
('Landmine Seated Overhead Press',1,'Sit on the ground facing the landmine with your legs spread. Hold the end of the bar in both hands in front of your chest with your palms facing each other.'),
('Landmine Seated Overhead Press',2,'While keeping your torso tall and core brace, drive the end of the bar upward until your arms are fully extended. Lean forward slightly for full range of motion in the shoulder joints. Lower the bar back down to the starting position.'),
('Landmine Seated Overhead Press',3,'Repeat for desired number of reps.'),
('Landmine Seated Single Arm Overhead Press',1,'Sit on the ground facing the landmine with your legs spread. Hold the end of the bar in one hand in front of that shoulder with your palm facing across your body.'),
('Landmine Seated Single Arm Overhead Press',2,'While keeping your torso tall and your core braced, drive the bar upwards until your arm is fully extended, leaning forward slightly for full range of motion in the shoulder joint. Lower the bar back down to the starting position with control.'),
('Landmine Seated Single Arm Overhead Press',3,'Repeat for desired number of reps on one side, then switch sides.'),
('Landmine Single Arm Chest Press',1,'Starting lying on your back perpendicularly to the barbell while holding the end of the bar in your hand that is further away from the landmine attachment. Your elbow should be rest on the ground at a 45 to 60 degree angle from your torso, with your wrist stacked over your elbow.'),
('Landmine Single Arm Chest Press',2,'Drive the end of the bar upwards, squeezing your chest at the top of the movement. Lower the bar back down until your elbow gently touches the ground.'),
('Landmine Single Arm Chest Press',3,'Repeat for the desired number of reps on one side before switching sides.'),
('Landmine Single Arm Overhead Press',1,'Stand in front of the landmine with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. Grasp the landmine barbell with one hand, palm facing in, and bring it to shoulder height with your elbow tucked beneath your hand.'),
('Landmine Single Arm Overhead Press',2,'Press the barbell overhead by extending your arm fully, pushing the weight upward. Keep your core engaged, your back straight, and your shoulder down throughout the movement. Pause briefly at the top of the movement with your arm fully extended overhead. Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position at shoulder height with control.'),
('Landmine Single Arm Overhead Press',3,'Repeat for the desired number of reps on one side before switching sides.'),
('Landmine Single Arm Push Press',1,'Stand in front of the landmine with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. Grasp the landmine barbell with one hand, palm facing in, and bring it to shoulder height with your elbow tucked beneath your hand.'),
('Landmine Single Arm Push Press',2,'Dip your body slightly then drive up through the ground to generate momentum as your extend your arm fully upwards. Pause briefly at the top of the rep, then lower the weight back down to the starting position with control.'),
('Landmine Single Arm Push Press',3,'Repeat for the desired number of reps on one side before switching sides.'),
('Landmine Single Arm Staggered Overhead Press',1,'Stand facing the bar in a split stance with one leg forward and bent and the other back and straight. Hold the bar in the hand on the side of the leg that is back with the end of the bar at your shoulder with your elbow tucked beneath your hand.'),
('Landmine Single Arm Staggered Overhead Press',2,'Drive the bar upwards until your arm is fully extended. Pause briefly before lowering the end of the bar back down to the starting position with control.'),
('Landmine Single Arm Staggered Overhead Press',3,'Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.'),
('Landmine Single Leg Glute Bridge',1,'Setup a landmine with your back on a box.'),
('Landmine Single Leg Glute Bridge',2,'Lay the end of the bar over your hip.'),
('Landmine Single Leg Glute Bridge',3,'Push your hips toward the ceiling until you feel a contraction, then bring your hips back toward the floor.'),
('Landmine Single Leg Romanian Deadlift',1,'Grab the end of the landmine and stand perpendicular to the bar.'),
('Landmine Single Leg Romanian Deadlift',2,'Lift your inside leg and keep your outside leg planted.'),
('Landmine Single Leg Romanian Deadlift',3,'Push your hips back keeping your knees mostly extended. When you feel the stretch in your hams, push your hips forward until you are standing upright.'),
('Landmine Sit Up',1,'Lay flat on the ground and hold the end of the bar with your arms extended.'),
('Landmine Sit Up',2,'Raise your back off the ground until you are sitting at a 90 degree angle.'),
('Landmine Sit Up',3,'Then lower slowly back to the floor.'),
('Landmine Snatch',1,'Hold the end of the bar in front of you.'),
('Landmine Snatch',2,'Pop your hips, pull your elbows up to the ceiling, and get underneath the bar.'),
('Landmine Split Jerk',1,'Hold the bar over one shoulder. Stand with a shoulder width stance.'),
('Landmine Split Jerk',2,'Dip at the hips and knees, generate some momentum and press the bar.'),
('Landmine Split Jerk',3,'As you press, split your stance. Bring the leg of the working arm back and the other forward.'),
('Landmine Squat',1,'Hold the end of the bar in a goblet position.'),
('Landmine Squat',2,'Push your hips back and break at the knees.'),
('Landmine Squat',3,'Reach at least parallel with the ground before pushing through your heels back to the starting position.'),
('Landmine Staggered Romanian Deadlift',1,'Stand in a staggered position. With the back leg bent and the front mostly extended.'),
('Landmine Staggered Romanian Deadlift',2,'Push your hips back until you feel a stretch through your front hamstring.'),
('Landmine Staggered Romanian Deadlift',3,'Push your hips back forward until you are standing.'),
('Landmine Stationary Twist',1,'Hold the end of the bar. Start with a shoulder width stance.'),
('Landmine Stationary Twist',2,'Bring both arms to one side and keep your elbows mostly extended.'),
('Landmine Stationary Twist',3,'Rotate back and forth and try to resist twisting too much.'),
('Landmine Sumo Deadlift',1,'Stand with a wide stance and straddle over the end of the bar.'),
('Landmine Sumo Deadlift',2,'Bend at the hips and knees, and grab the bar.'),
('Landmine Sumo Deadlift',3,'Stand up with the bar.'),
('Landmine T Bar Rows',1,'Grab a v bar and place it under the bar\'s collar.'),
('Landmine T Bar Rows',2,'Hinge forward with a flat back and pull your elbows straight back toward the ceiling.'),
('Landmine T Bar Rows',3,'Fully extend your elbows before initiating the next rep.'),
('Landmine Thruster',1,'Hold the bar with a goblet position.'),
('Landmine Thruster',2,'Push your hips back and sink into a squat.'),
('Landmine Thruster',3,'Push through your heels and squat back up. Use the momentum you generate at the legs to push the bar over head.'),
('Landmine Thruster',4,'Let the bar return to the goblet position before starting the next rep.'),
('Lats Stretch Variation One',1,'Place both hands on the wall in front of you.'),
('Lats Stretch Variation One',2,'Slowly lower your body until you feel the stretch.'),
('Lats Stretch Variation One',3,'Hold at the bottom of the stretch, return to starting position.'),
('Lats Stretch Variation Three',1,'Find a wall to lean against, lay your tricep against the wall with your hand behind your back.'),
('Lats Stretch Variation Three',2,'Slowly lean into the wall.'),
('Lats Stretch Variation Three',3,'Return to starting position, then switch sides.'),
('Lats Stretch Variation Two',1,'Stand up right and raise your hand to a full stretch above your head.'),
('Lats Stretch Variation Two',2,'Slowly lean across your body and trace the opposite hand down your leg.'),
('Lats Stretch Variation Two',3,'Hold at the bottom of the stretch, return to starting position and then switch sides.'),
('Lawnmower Row',1,'Stand with feet staggered and one hand on a bench/box. Hold a dumbbell in the opposing hand.'),
('Lawnmower Row',2,'Hinge forward at the hips, keeping the back flat, and eyes facing forward. The weight should hang directly below the shoulders.'),
('Lawnmower Row',3,'Start with an overhand grip, as you pull rotate the dumbbell. When your upper arm reaches your side your palm should be facing forward.'),
('Laying Alternating Leg Raise',1,'Lie on your back, arms by sides, legs straight.'),
('Laying Alternating Leg Raise',2,'Lift one leg to a 45-degree angle.'),
('Laying Alternating Leg Raise',3,'Lower leg, lift opposite leg; alternate smoothly.'),
('Laying Bent Leg Raise',1,'Lie on your back, knees bent, feet flat on the floor.'),
('Laying Bent Leg Raise',2,'Raise both knees towards your chest.'),
('Laying Bent Leg Raise',3,'Lower back down without touching the floor; repeat for desired reps.'),
('Laying Cervical Extensor Mobilisation Peanut Tool',1,'Lie on your back with your knees bent and your feet on the ground to allow for a flat lower back'),
('Laying Cervical Extensor Mobilisation Peanut Tool',2,'Place the peanut tool under the base of your skull and lie back down'),
('Laying Cervical Extensor Mobilisation Peanut Tool',3,'Gently nod your head while the peanut tool is on the tender spot of the neck.'),
('Laying Cervical Extensor Mobilisation Peanut Tool',4,'Using a yoga block helps keep the head in a position which makes the movement easier and more effective'),
('Laying Cervical Flexion 2',1,'Lie on your back with your knees bent and your feet on the ground to allow for a flat lower back.'),
('Laying Cervical Flexion 2',2,'Tuck your chin in and raise the back of the head slightly off the ground before lowering back down.'),
('Laying Cervical Flexion 2',3,'As soon as you feel the ground with the back of your head, repeat the movement without resting on the ground.'),
('Laying Cervical Flexion Isometric',1,'Lie on your back with your knees bent and your feet on the ground to allow for a flat lower back'),
('Laying Cervical Flexion Isometric',2,'Elongate your neck as much as possible'),
('Laying Cervical Flexion Isometric',3,'Tuck your chin in and raise the back of the head slightly off the ground'),
('Laying Chin Tucks',1,'Lie on your back with your knees bent and your feet on the ground to allow for a flat lower back.'),
('Laying Chin Tucks',2,'Elongate your neck as much as possible'),
('Laying Chin Tucks',3,'Tuck the chin in and press the back of your head into the ground'),
('Laying Chin Tucks',4,'It helps having a folded towel under the head.'),
('Laying Lateral Raise',1,'Lay on your side on a bench or box. Place one hand on the floor and the other hand is holding the dumbbell.'),
('Laying Lateral Raise',2,'While keeping your elbow mostly extended, raise the dumbbell to the side.'),
('Laying Lateral Raise',3,'The end of the range of motion is when the dumbbell is pointed toward the ceiling.'),
('Laying Lateral Raise',4,'Make sure you don\'t flex and extend your elbow.'),
('Laying Leg Raises',1,'Lay on your back with your arms palms down on either side.'),
('Laying Leg Raises',2,'Keep your legs together and as straight as possible.'),
('Laying Leg Raises',3,'Slowly raise your legs to a 90° angle, pause at this position, or as high as you can reach your legs, and then slowly lower your legs back down.'),
('Laying Leg Raises',4,'Duration of these movements should be slow so that you do not utilize momentum, enabling you to get the most out of the exercise.'),
('Laying Levator Scapulae Mobilisation Massage Ball',1,'Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Keep your arm by your side'),
('Laying Levator Scapulae Mobilisation Massage Ball',2,'Place a massage ball under the area between the top of your scapula and spine with the other arm.'),
('Laying Levator Scapulae Mobilisation Massage Ball',3,'Once you find the tight/sore spot, move your arm over your head and back to starting position to mobilise your levator scapula muscle.'),
('Laying Ts',1,'Lie on your front, arms outstretched to the side.'),
('Laying Ts',2,'Raise head and chest off the ground.'),
('Laying Ts',3,'Raise and lower your arms (flapping wings motion) by contracting and relaxing the muscles in between your shoulder blades.'),
('Leg Raised Push Up',1,'Place your hands firmly on the ground, directly under shoulders.'),
('Leg Raised Push Up',2,'Flatten your back so your entire body is straight, raise one leg off the ground, and slowly lower your body'),
('Leg Raised Push Up',3,'Draw shoulder blades back and down, keeping elbows tucked close to your body'),
('Leg Raised Push Up',4,'Exhale as you push back to the starting position.'),
('Long Arm Adduction Side Kneeling',1,'Kneel sideways, supporting hand under shoulder, top arm reaching long overhead.'),
('Long Arm Adduction Side Kneeling',2,'Engage core, keep torso upright and shoulders stacked.'),
('Long Arm Adduction Side Kneeling',3,'Pull top arm down toward hip, using lats and obliques.'),
('Long Arm Adduction Side Kneeling',4,'Return arm overhead with control, maintaining balance and steady breathing.'),
('Long Lever Plank',1,'Start in a hand plank position and walk your hands further out until your ears are between your biceps.'),
('Long Lever Plank',2,'Hold in this position for the allotted amount of time.'),
('Long Lever Plank',3,'Make sure you keep a flat back for the whole set.'),
('Long Stretch Plank Position',1,'Place hands on footbar, shoulders over wrists, legs extended long.'),
('Long Stretch Plank Position',2,'Engage core and glutes, forming a straight line head to heels.'),
('Long Stretch Plank Position',3,'Press heels back, protract shoulders slightly, neck neutral.'),
('Long Stretch Plank Position',4,'Hold with steady breathing and full-body tension.'),
('Lord Of The Dance',1,'Begin by standing tall with your feet hip-width apart.'),
('Lord Of The Dance',2,'Shift your weight onto your left foot and bring your right heel towards your glute.'),
('Lord Of The Dance',3,'Reach your right arm back and grab onto the inside of your right foot or ankle.'),
('Lord Of The Dance',4,'Inhale and lift your right foot away from your glute while extending your left arm forward. Hold for 5-10 breaths before switching sides.'),
('Lower back Stretch Variation Four',1,'Lay flat against the ground with your knees at an angle and your feet flat against the floor.'),
('Lower back Stretch Variation Four',2,'Grab your legs just below the knees, and pull your legs towards your chest.'),
('Lower back Stretch Variation Four',3,'Pause at the apex of the stretch, then return to the starting position.'),
('Lower back Stretch Variation One',1,'Sit on the floor with the tops of your feet pointed and flat on the ground. Move your arms out in front of you in the diving position, placing your palms flat against the ground.'),
('Lower back Stretch Variation One',2,'With your arms fully extended, rest your buttocks on the heels of your feet, you can crawl your hands forward to extend the stretch if need be.'),
('Lower back Stretch Variation One',3,'Hold the extended position for a few seconds, and return to starting position.'),
('Lower back Stretch Variation Three',1,'Lay on your back with your arms at either side.'),
('Lower back Stretch Variation Three',2,'Raise your knees so that they are pointing straight towards the ceiling. Keeping your legs pressed together, rotate your hips to either side.'),
('Lower back Stretch Variation Three',3,'Repeat this motion as necessary.'),
('Lower back Stretch Variation Two',1,'Lay flat on the floor with your arms at either side.'),
('Lower back Stretch Variation Two',2,'With one leg, hook one foot under the joint of your other leg.'),
('Lower back Stretch Variation Two',3,'Rotate your hips so that your knees are pointing sideways, keeping your hooked leg flat against the floor.'),
('Lower back Stretch Variation Two',4,'Pause at the apex of the stretch and repeat with your other leg.'),
('Machine 45 Degree Back Extension',1,'Position your thighs on the padding and hook your feet on the platform supports.'),
('Machine 45 Degree Back Extension',2,'Keeping your back straight, slowly bend at your waist until your legs and back are at a 45° angle.'),
('Machine 45 Degree Back Extension',3,'Slowly raise your body to the starting position.'),
('Machine 45 Degree Calf Raise',1,'Adjust the machine in accordance with your height and sit.'),
('Machine 45 Degree Calf Raise',2,'The balls of your feet should be supporting your weight on the calve block, your heels extended off of it.'),
('Machine 45 Degree Calf Raise',3,'Extend your heels upwards while keeping your knees stationary, and pause at the contracted position.'),
('Machine 45 Degree Calf Raise',4,'Slowly return to the starting position. Repeat.'),
('Machine Assisted Chin Up',1,'Adjust weight for assistance. Stand on platform, grip handles above shoulder-width. Knees on pad if available.'),
('Machine Assisted Chin Up',2,'Slowly pull up until chin is above the bar. Keep elbows close, core engaged.'),
('Machine Assisted Chin Up',3,'Lower back with control. Pause at bottom. Repeat for reps.'),
('Machine Assisted Narrow Pull Up',1,'Adjust weight for assistance. Stand on platform, grip handles above shoulder-width. Knees on pad if available.'),
('Machine Assisted Narrow Pull Up',2,'Slowly pull up until chin is above the bar. Keep elbows close, core engaged.'),
('Machine Assisted Narrow Pull Up',3,'Lower back with control. Pause at bottom. Repeat for reps.'),
('Machine Assisted Neutral Chin Up',1,'Adjust weight for assistance. Stand on platform, grip handles above shoulder-width. Knees on pad if available.'),
('Machine Assisted Neutral Chin Up',2,'Slowly pull up until chin is above the bar. Keep elbows close, core engaged.'),
('Machine Assisted Neutral Chin Up',3,'Lower back with control. Pause at bottom. Repeat for reps.'),
('Machine Assisted Pull Up',1,'Adjust weight for assistance. Stand on platform, grip handles above shoulder-width. Knees on pad if available.'),
('Machine Assisted Pull Up',2,'Slowly pull up until chin is above the bar. Keep elbows close, core engaged.'),
('Machine Assisted Pull Up',3,'Lower back with control. Pause at bottom. Repeat for reps.'),
('Machine Back Extension',1,'Sit on the machine and place your upper back on the rolling pad.'),
('Machine Back Extension',2,'Extend your hips and lower back. Make sure not to hyperextend your spine.'),
('Machine Belt Squat',1,'Put the belt around your waist and hook the end of the belt onto the machines.'),
('Machine Belt Squat',2,'Stand up to disengage the holding mechanism. Hold the arms while you squat.'),
('Machine Belt Squat',3,'Once you\'ve completed your set, reset the holding mechanism.'),
('Machine Bent Arm Pec Fly',1,'Adjust seat height so handles align with chest. Put your elbows on the pads.'),
('Machine Bent Arm Pec Fly',2,'Slowly bring pads together in front, keeping tension. Focus on squeezing chest muscles.'),
('Machine Bent Arm Pec Fly',3,'Return pads to starting position with controlled motion. Keep chest up throughout. Repeat for reps.'),
('Machine Bicep Curl',1,'Adjust the seat to fit your height and place your elbows on the elbow pad.'),
('Machine Bicep Curl',2,'Grab the handles and flex your elbows.'),
('Machine Cable V Bar Push Downs',1,'Grip the pulley bar with palms facing down at shoulder width.'),
('Machine Cable V Bar Push Downs',2,'Stand straight with a small forward incline. Keep your upper arms close to your body, and slowly bring the pulley bar down until your arms are fully extended.'),
('Machine Cable V Bar Push Downs',3,'Pause when you are at the contracted position of the motion, then slowly raise the pulley bar back to the starting point.'),
('Machine Chest Supported T Bar Row',1,'Lay on the chest pad and grab the handles. Lift the bar out of the holding hook.'),
('Machine Chest Supported T Bar Row',2,'Pull the bar to your chest and then fully extend your elbows at the bottom of each rep.'),
('Machine Crunch',1,'Place your feet under the foot pads and grab the handles with your hands.'),
